title: festive date and nut roll(easy no-bake recipe)
directions: Combine all the ingredients; mix well and shape into a roll. Cover the outside of roll with remaining 1/2 cup of crushed Girl Scout cookies.
Wrap roll in waxed paper and put in refrigerator at least 5 hours.
Cut in slices and top with whipped cream. Makes 8 servings.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Beat all ingredients.
Grease and flour 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with favorite fruit and toppings.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Drain sweet relish in strainer.
Put all ingredients into a small container.
Mix together with a butter knife and cut the avocados up.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: barbecue country style ribs
directions: Cut meat in single rib pieces.
Place in Dutch oven and cover with water.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.

title: quick tamale pie
directions: Brown the ground beef in a large skillet.
Drain off fat.
Stir in the soups, onions and salt.
Heat.
Place 2 cups corn chips in bottom of a 3-quart casserole dish.
Top with half of the beef mixture and 1/2 cup cheese.
Top with 2 cups corn chips and the remaining meat mixture.
Top with remaining corn chips and remaining cheese.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 25 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Put crackers in a bowl.
In another bowl, combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour over crackers and mix frequently for 1 hour, until mixture coats crackers and is absorbed.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and cover with 2 cups of crushed potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until it bubbles around the edges.
Use a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Serves 8.

title: perfect roasted garlic
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove the outer layer of skin from 1 to 6 heads of garlic.
Cut 1/2 inch off from each head straight across top and arrange in a shallow baking pan.
Drizzle 2 teaspoons olive oil over each head, letting it run between the cloves.
Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 30 to 45 minutes, until garlic is tender when pierced with a toothpick.
Cool slightly.

title: sandwich a la maria(great for school lunch.)
directions: Cut bread slices with 3-inch doughnut cutter to make 12 rounds. Tear remaining bread into 1-inch pieces and arrange in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Sprinkle cheeses, ham and green onion over bread pieces. Arrange bread rounds over cheese/ham layer.
Combine milk, eggs, parsley and mustard.
Pour over bread and cheese layers. Seal and chill at least 1 hour.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 12.

title: honeydew biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured muffin pans in moderate (375°) oven until done.

title: sour cream banana cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Add bananas and pecans and mix well. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Ice with Caramel Frosting.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well and pour over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken dorito casserole
directions: Cook chicken, cool, remove bone and skin and dice chicken. Saute onion in 1 tablespoon oleo.
Mix soups, Ro-Tel tomatoes, green chiles, sauteed onion and broth.
Use extra broth if necessary.
Spray 9 x 13-inch baking pan with Pam.
Put layer of chips, chicken, soup and cheese.
Layer until all chicken and soup is used.
Then sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Grease sheet cake pan.
Beat eggs.
Add corn, sour cream and Jiffy muffin mix, stirring in between each.
Pour into baking pan. Pour melted butter or margarine over top.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown, 20 to 40 minutes.
Good warmed over.
Also freezes well.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Combine oleo, sugar, eggs, vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Grease 10 x 12-inch or 12 x 18-inch pan.
Spread 2/3 of mixture on sheet.
Spread pie filling over batter.
Drop remaining batter on top and spread out as thin as possible.
When baked, drizzle a glaze over top.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries and orange.
Add sugar and set in refrigerator.
Make jello and cool to syrup stage.
Add to cranberry mixture and chill.

title: very good casserole
directions: Mix together and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Toast nuts in 325° oven until lightly browned.
Fold sugar and salt into beaten egg whites and beat until soft peaks form. Fold toasted nuts into mixture.
Melt margarine in 10 x 15 pan (large cookie sheet will work).
Spread nut mixture over margarine.
Bake in 325° oven about 40 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes until nuts are coated with browned meringue mixture and no margarine remains.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium size bowl or pouring pitcher. Pour over meat to be barbecued.
Unused sauce may be kept in covered jar for 3 to 6 months in refrigerator.
Makes 3 cups.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, oil and crushed pineapple, saving the juice for glaze.
Add egg yolks, cinnamon and hot water.
Next add the egg whites that have been beaten stiffly and then pecans. Bake in tube pan that has been greased and floured for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in pineapple and blueberries with juice.
Chill until firm.
Top with sour cream, cream cheese and sugar that has been whipped.
Top with nuts.

title: louisiana frog poppers
directions: Cut meat from bones.
Marinate in hot sauce for 30 minutes. Mix flour and creole seasoning to taste.
Take meat from hot sauce, dip on corner in mustard, roll in flour and deep fry.

title: barbecue beef ribs
directions: Place ribs in a flat pan or dish.
Pour sauce over ribs, turning so as to coat both sides.
Pierce meat with fork. Marinate 8 hours, turning once.
Remove from marinade and brush off excess to avoid burning.
Broil or cook over coals for 10 minutes; brush with marinade and cook 4 to 5 minutes more.
Heat remaining sauce and serve with ribs.
(Ribs may be cooked in a covered pan in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours, if desired.)
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: the best pecan pie
directions: Cream butter (softened) and sugar.
Add corn syrup, flour, salt, cream, eggs, vanilla and pecans last.
Pour into unbaked pie shells (9-inch deep dish).
Bake on middle rack 1 hour at 325° or until set.
Makes 2 pies.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Sift flour with salt.
Cut in the shortening with a pastry blender until crumbly.
Mix in egg, water and vinegar.
Chill or roll out immediately and fit into pie pans.
Makes 4 (9-inch) crusts.
Prick bottoms and sides with fork.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
Leftover balls of dough can be wrapped and frozen for use later.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix.
Add salad oil and eggs; mix thoroughly.
Stir in strawberries and nuts.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Sit overnight wrapped tightly.

title: meatball stew
directions: Mix beef, egg, bread, onion and salt.
Shape into 24 meatballs.
Brown in shortening in skillet.
Pour off fat; add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes. Stir now and then.
Top with chopped parsley.
Serves 6.

title: praline cookies
directions: Melt oleo.
Add sugar; stir and bring to a rolling boil for 3 minutes.
Line cookie sheet with whole graham crackers.
Pour mixture over crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: raisin bread
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins, soda and oleo and let stand (overnight is best, but not necessary).
Add other ingredients and mix.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured pans for 25 minutes in mini pans.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease large shallow baking dish; cover bottom with dried beef.
Wrap bacon around chicken and place in dish.
Blend sour cream and soup.
Pour over top of chicken and bacon.
Bake at 275° for around 2 1/2 hours.

title: banana pudding
directions: In a deep 2-quart casserole, toss cookies and bananas.
Set aside.
In a 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt. Using a fork, beat in milk until blended and smooth.
Bring to a boil over medium-low heat.
Cook one minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.

title: gazpacho soup
directions: Chop all vegetables, except tomatoes.
Serve chilled.

title: velvet fig cake
directions: Combine the dry ingredients and sift 4 times.
Cream the shortening well and add the well beaten eggs.
Next, add the dry ingredients, alternating with the liquid.
Last, blend in the figs.
Bake at 300° until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: dried apple stack cake
directions: Cream margarine until light and fluffy.
Add brown sugar and molasses and continue creaming until mixture is fluffy.
Add eggs. Combine flour, soda, baking powder, ginger and salt and sift into creamed mixture.
This should be a soft dough and a few tablespoons of buttermilk may be added if dough is too stiff.
Divide dough into six equal parts.
Draw a 9-inch circle on a sheet of aluminum foil.
Lightly flour foil and roll dough to fit circle.
Bake on foil in oven at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool layers and stack layers with Dried Apple Filling.
Dust top layer with confectioners sugar. (Dough rolls better if chilled, and cake is more tasty if served a day or so after stacking.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil and boil hard for 8 minutes, stirring constantly. Cool completely. Wash and drain fresh strawberries on paper towel. Frozen strawberries cannot be used. Bake pie shell and cool. Place berries in pie shell. Pour syrup mixture over berries. Let stand in the refrigerator for 5 or 6 hours. Top with whipped cream before serving.

title: funnel cake
directions: Stir all dry ingredients, except powdered sugar, together in a bowl.
Blend egg and milk; add to dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.

title: holiday sage bread
directions: Scald milk with sugar, salt, onion and butter.
Cool to lukewarm.
In a large mixing bowl, sprinkle yeast into warm water; stir until dissolved, then stir in a cooled milk mixture.
Stir in flour and sage until well blended, then beat with a wooden spoon about 100 strokes.
Dough will be sticky and heavy.
Cover with a clean towel; let rise in a warm place, away from drafts, for about 1 hour or until doubled.
Stir down.

title: skillet cornbread
directions: Preheat greased 9-inch ovenproof skillet in 350° oven. Combine spread and eggs; mix until well blended.
Add milk and combined dry ingredients, mixing just until moistened.
Fold in corn and chopped green peppers.
Pour into skillet.
Top with green pepper rings.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix together white sugar, brown sugar, flour and oleo.
Take out 1 cup of mixture and add 1 teaspoon cinnamon to it.
Set aside and save for topping.
To the remainder, add 2 eggs, flour, buttermilk and soda.
Mix well.
Divide into 2 greased and floured round pans.
Cover with topping.
(May sprinkle nuts on top.) Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: gherkin cucumbers
directions: Note:
If you like a milder pickle, remove seeds from red hot peppers.

title: cocoa brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for about 25 minutes at 300°.

title: hominy grits and cheese
directions: Cook grits and directed.
While hot, add remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 250° in large, shallow buttered pan. Serves 12.

title: mary's hamburger dip
directions: Fry meat; drain.
Add chili.
Cut cheese into cubes; stir into meat.
Warm to melt cheese.
Keep warm in slow cooker.
Serve with nacho type chips.

title: stromboli
directions: Thaw and spread out bread dough on lightly greased cookie sheet to 10 x 14-inch size.
Layer sauteed mushrooms, onions and peppers, then Mozzarella shredded cheese, then sliced pepperoni, then shredded Cheddar cheese, then ham.
Roll jelly roll fashion from long end, pinch together seam.
Put in circle and put one end inside other.
Brush with beaten egg white.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Make sure it doesn't brown too much.

title: cheese danish
directions: Spread 1 can of rolls in bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Pinch edges together.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and 1 cup sugar.
Stir in egg and molasses.
Stir in dry ingredients, except 1/2 cup sugar.
Form into 1-inch balls and roll in remaining sugar.
Place 2 to 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet until firm.
Remove carefully with spatula.

title: chocolate nut pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add half the milk and beat thoroughly. Beat in egg yolks and add nuts.
Add rest of milk and vanilla. Pour in an unbaked pie shell and bake in a moderate oven until firm.
Then beat egg whites and spread on pie; brown slightly.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well. Fold in flour.
Bake for approximately 1 hour at 350° in a tube pan.

title: carambola jam
directions: Remove	stems from fruit.
Peel.
Remove seeds.
Crush. Measure fruit into a 6 or 8 quart pot.
Measure sugar and stir into
fruit.
Add
teaspoon
butter
or margarine.
Bring mixture
to a full boil over high heat.
Stir constantly.
Add Certo.
Return
to	a full, rolling boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.	Skim off foam.	Pour into jars.
Makes 7 cups.

title: marinated carrots (1)
directions: Combine all of the above ingredients.
Marinate overnight. Keeps indefinitely, but gets stronger with time.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomatoes.
Add tomatoes just before serving.
Chill well.
Any vegetables may be added or omitted.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix equal parts of apple jelly and ketchup to completely cover the number of meatballs needed in crock pot.
Slow cook for 5 to 6 hours.

title: oatmeal and butterscotch cookies
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar and sugar.
Add eggs and hot water, beat well.
Add flour, soda, oats and vanilla.
Mix well. Stir in chips.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients in a gallon ice cream freezer.
Freeze until firm.

title: poor man's fruit cake
directions: Simmer raisins in 2 cups water for 10 minutes.
Hold out 1 cup of raisins and water mixture for icing.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple fruit cake
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add apple pie filling and sugar. Continue heating, stirring occasionally, until sugar melts. Cool.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix raisins, currants, pecans, candied fruits and cherries with dry ingredients.
Combine apple mixture and dry ingredients.
Pour into foil-lined 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 90 minutes or until done.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soften bread with warm water; squeeze out water if too wet. Mix all ingredients together.
Bake on ungreased 8 x 8-inch square baking dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: "good-n-ugly" cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour batter over butter and nuts.
In a separate pan, melt the remaining stick of margarine.
Mix in cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar and beat with mixer until smooth.
Spoon over cake batter and bake at
250° to 275° for about 55 minutes.
Icing will go to bottom of pan.

title: pickaninny doughnuts
directions: Mix in order given, using only enough flour to make soft and pliable.
Too much mixing toughens doughnuts.
Roll a little at a time to 1/4-inch thickness.
Fry in deep fat at 360° for 2 to 3 minutes until lightly browned, turning several times.
Makes approximately 30.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In order listed, layer ingredients and beat until well blended.
Pour into greased crock-pot.
Cover and cook on high 1 hour, then on low 2 to 3 hours.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Mix together eggs, sour cream, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, flour and onion powder.
Stir in ham or crab and cheese. Pour into 9 or 10-inch quiche dish.
Bake at 350° until center is firm (approximately 45 minutes).
Let set for 5 minutes.

title: monkey-cake
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar with 2 teaspoons cinnamon in covered mixing bowl.
Take 2 cans of biscuits and cut each biscuit into 4 pieces. Put them into sugar and cinnamon mixture, cover the bowl and shake.
Place pieces in tube pan.
Mix margarine, 1 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour 1/2 mixture into tube pan.
Cut remaining biscuits and cover with cinnamon mixture and place in pan.
Pour rest of boiled mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes and let cool 5 minutes before removing.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients with 1 cup water in large nonstick skillet.
Cook until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add green pepper, celery and snow peas; mix well.
Cook for 3 to 5 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to serving temperature.
Serve over rice.
Yield: 3 servings.

title: muriel's pecan pie
directions: Mix together sugars and flour.
Beat in thoroughly the eggs, milk, vanilla and butter.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into a pastry lined pan. Bake 40 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together. Bake about 12 minutes or until edges turn brown.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion and drain.
Add salt, pepper, tomatoes and sauce.
Cook over medium heat for 30 minutes.
Add beans and pour into casserole dish.
Top with cheese and corn chips.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: leftover meat loaf parmesan
directions: Combine the saltine crumbs and Parmesan cheese in a shallow dish; set aside. Beat egg with water; dip meat loaf slices in egg mixture, then in crumb mixture. Heat shortening in a skillet. Brown meat loaf slices on both sides. Serve with ketchup, if desired. Yield: 2 to 4 servings.

title: spice cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with buttermilk.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until the cake tests done.
Cool.

title: preserve a husband
directions: Be
careful in your selection.	Do not choose too young and take
only	such
as
have	been
reared
in a good, moral atmosphere.
Some
insist
on
keeping
them in a pickle while others keep
them
in
hot	water.	This only makes them sour, hard and bitter.
Even
poor
variety may be sweet, tender and good by garnishing	them
with
patience,
well sweetened with smiles and flavored with
kisses
to
taste.
Wrap	them
in a mantle for charity, keep
warm with a steady fire of devotion. Serve with three good
meals
a day.
Thus prepared, they will keep for years.

title: potatoes o'brien
directions: Mix potatoes, peppers, onions, flour, salt, pepper and cheese in large mixing bowl.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Cover with milk and add bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: brown sugar drops
directions: Beat shortening, sugar and eggs; stir in milk.
Sift dry ingredients together and mix.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoonful about 2 inches apart on lightly greased sheet.
Bake only until set and when touched no imprint remains at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: aunt fannie's doughnuts
directions: Mix all ingredients together; knead well.
Let rise about 45 minutes.
Punch down mixture and roll out and cut doughnuts out and let rise again until double.
Fry in deep oil.

title: meat loaf pie
directions: Line a casserole dish with half of potatoes.
Season meat. Place on top of potatoes.
Cover with remaining potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dreamsicle cake
directions: Blend all ingredients on high speed for 3 minutes.
Use 3 pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: stuffed mushrooms ala houghton
directions: Remove mushroom stems.
Finely chop and saute in olive oil. Combine all ingredients except mushroom caps.
Fill mushroom caps with mixture. Sprinkle with bread crumbs or Parmesan cheese. Place in a greased shallow baking pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serves 4.

title: mini oreo magical pizza
directions: Reserve 20 cookies.
Prepare brownie mix batter according to package directions; stir in remaining cookies.
Spread batter in greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or until done.

Sprinkle marshmallows over top of hot brownies; bake for 3 to 5 minutes more or until marshmallows are lightly browned. Sprinkle with nuts, candies and remaining cookies, pressing lightly into softened marshmallows.
Cool slightly on rack.
Cut into wedges; serve warm or cooled.

title: sausage-veggie casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower according to package directions. Drain and put in a large casserole dish.
Steam bite size pieces of German sausage; add to broccoli and cauliflower.
Add carrots. Pour Cheez Whiz over top and warm in a 250° oven until Cheez Whiz is melted over all.
Stir and serve.

title: breakfast rolls
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Place frozen rolls in single layer around pan.
Sprinkle pudding, brown sugar and nuts on rolls.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Invert rolls onto flat plate immediately.

title: sausage and egg brunch
directions: Brown and crumble slightly the ground sausage. Drain off grease.
Cool. In bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and mustard. Add bread and stir.
Add cheese and sausage.
Put in glass baking dish, 8 x 12-inches.
Place in refrigerator overnight. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: deer stew
directions: Use about a pound of deer meat.
Cut the meat from the bones and into pieces about 1-inch cube or just larger.

Marinate the meat, covered, in a container in the refrigerator for 3 to 5 days. The marinade may be cooking wine, red drinking wine or vinegar. (If cooking wine is used, remember spices are already in the wine and will have an offset on the finished product.)
The tougher the meat, the longer it must be marinated.
Be sure to turn or shake the meat in the a.m. and p.m.
Remove the meat after soak and flour it heavily.
Brown the meat in a frying pan with 1 medium chopped onion.
Place the meat in a crock-pot or stew pot.
Add 2 medium chopped onions, 1 pound tomatoes (fresh or canned), 4 stalks celery, 1/2 green pepper (chopped) and 5 or 6 chopped white potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add garlic, a tablespoon brown sugar, 1/2 cup V-8 juice, 1 cup of the marinade and 1 cup chopped mushrooms.
The stew must be cooked slowly for 8 or more hours depending on the heat and the type pot used.
Add Bermuda rum or sherry and peppers to taste in each serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put cranberries and oranges through food chopper.
Add sugar and let stand overnight.
Prepare jello.
When cooked, add fruit and nuts.
Congeal.

title: chocolate snaps
directions: Melt chips and cool.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
With electric mixer on medium-low, beat butter and sugar until fluffy. Add vanilla, Karo and egg and continue mixing until well blended. Refrigerate until firm, about 30 minutes.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and roll in additional sugar.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet about 1 inch apart.
Bake until edges are lightly browned, 10 to 15 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute, then remove.

title: no cook peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix all together in a bowl.
Put out in pan and let harden.

title: marinade(for chops, chicken, fish, tofu)
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then marinate meat for 1/2 hour plus.
Then grill or broil as usual.

title: pecan pie
directions: Line pie plate with crust.
Cook sugar and syrup to 328° or until thick.
Beat eggs well.
Add hot syrup slowly.
Add nuts and vanilla.

title: butter balls
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light. Add vanilla and flour; mix well. Fold in nuts. Shape into balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar while still hot.

title: beef tips on rice
directions: Combine all ingredients except rice.
Put in crock pot. Cook on high for 1 hour and
then on low until meat is tender. Prepare rice as directed.
If
more gravy is desired, add more soup.

title: friendship cake starter
directions: Let set 2 weeks and stir daily.
Drain fruit; reserve juice for starter.
Fruit can be used on ice cream or served with whipped cream.
Start in a glass container with loose-fitting lid.
Keep at room temperature.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Beat together first 6 ingredients.
Sift together flour, soda and baking powder and beat into first mixture.
Add boiling water last.
(Add ingredients in order listed.) Bake in slow oven (350°).
This cake will stay moist for a week or so.

title: potato-cheese soup
directions: Cook potato and onion until very tender in smallest amount of water possible.
Cut Velveeta cheese into small pieces and add milk.
Simmer for 5 minutes (do not boil).
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 2.

title: the big bad wolf's brownies(from walt disney's mickey mouse cookbook)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Melt butter and chocolate in large pan over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar, flour, baking powder, vanilla and nuts. Add the eggs and beat well with an egg beater.
Pour the batter into the baking pan. Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove the pan from the oven and place it on a rack.
When the brownies are cool, cut them into squares.
Makes about 16 brownies.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs until light and fluffy.
Add milk and flavorings.
Add soda and baking powder to first cup of flour.
Stir in additional flour to stiffen.
The less flour and handling of the dough the softer the cookies.
Roll out and cut with a glass or cookie cutter.
Don't roll thin.
Bake at 400°.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix pretzels crumbs, butter and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes and cool.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Tear bread into pieces.
Mix first 4 ingredients, then add bread.
Bake in casserole dish for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with ham.

title: polish sweet bread
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Scald milk.
Add shortening, sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Add flour to make a thin batter.
Add yeast, eggs and rind; beat well.
Add enough flour or rest of flour to make soft dough.
Turn onto lightly floured board; knead until satiny.
Form into ball; place in greased bowl. Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Form into loaves and put on topping.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Yields 4 loaves.

title: ryan's breakfast shake
directions: Put in blender egg, banana and milk.
Blend until smooth.
Add ice cubes and sugar.
Mix until smooth and foamy.
Pour into large glass.

title: peach pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water in saucepan.
Stir until smooth.
Cook over medium heat until bubbly and thick.
Remove from heat.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chuckie's little pizzas
directions: Brown hamburger and drain well.
Brown sausage and drain well. Mix hamburger, sausage and cheese over medium heat until cheese is completely melted.
Add oregano to taste.
Spread mixture on small cocktail rye bread.
Broil approximately 5 minutes.

title: golden tomato pie
directions: Peel and slice tomatoes; sprinkle with salt and let stand while preparing crusts.
Rinse tomatoes; mix sugar, tapioca, cinnamon, lemon juice and raisins, then add to tomatoes.
Put into crust; dot with butter and put top crust on and slit for vents.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: burgundy stew
directions: Brown the beef; add soup, wine, mushrooms and onions.
Bake in pan or small roaster for 3 1/2 hours at 325°.
Thicken with tapioca.

title: ham and noodles
directions: In saucepan, brown ham and mushrooms in butter.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Heat.
Stir now and then.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: au gratin potato bake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into a buttered baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Serves 8.

title: banana split pie
directions: Combine bananas, pineapple, Cool Whip, cherries and pecans. Pour into pie crust.
Drizzle chocolate syrup over top.
Chill until time to serve.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a bowl.
Place mixture in a greased bread pan.
Let sit for 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (usually longer) until done.

title: sonora casserole
directions: Brown in skillet the hamburger meat and onion.
Add mushroom soup, chicken soup, evaporated milk and pepper to taste.

title: apple nut squares
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar.
Cool.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat (by hand).
Add all dry ingredients; mix.
Add nuts and apples. Pat into a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° until brown and will spring back when pressed in middle.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut into squares.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: fried chicken with cream gravy
directions: In a small bowl, combine 1/3 cup oil, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Place chicken pieces in a shallow baking dish and pour marinade mixture over.
Cover and marinate for 30 to 60 minutes. Dry chicken on paper towels.
Place 1/2 cup flour in a plastic or paper bag.
In a small bowl, combine eggs and milk; place bread crumbs in a shallow bowl.
Put several pieces of chicken in the bag and shake to coat thoroughly.
Dip in egg mixture, then roll in bread crumbs.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Blend eggs, milk and seasonings; set aside.
Trim crust from bread; cut into cubes.
Pour butter over bread cubes, stirring gently; let stand until butter is absorbed.
Layer half of bread cubes in lightly greased souffle dish; top with half of cheese. Repeat layers.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.
This is a never fail souffle.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour one 9 x 13-inch pan or two 9-inch pans or three 8-inch pans.
Measure all ingredients into large mixing bowl and blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes on high and then pour into pan(s). Bake oblong pan 45 minutes, layers about 35 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cake is good eaten without icing or can be iced with Caramel Fudge Icing.

title: chili with cornbread casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
About 2 hours before serving, in 5-quart pot over high heat in 2 tablespoons hot salad oil, cook meat, 1/3 at a time, stirring often, until browned on all sides; remove to bowl as it browns.

title: banana smoothie
directions: Freeze bananas that are getting too ripe, peel, cut up and stick in Baggie.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat at medium speed 2 to 3 minutes.
Bake in three 9-inch layer pans (floured) at 325° for 25 minutes.
Frost.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole or oblong glass pan, make a layer of broccoli, chicken and rice.
Make sauce of mayonnaise, soup, curry and lemon juice.
Pour over layers.
Top with grated cheese; sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk, lemon juice and egg yolks together. Pour in crust.
Beat egg whites until stiff and mix in sugar. Place on top of filling.
Bake at 425° until lightly brown.

title: sloppy joe squares
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet over medium-high heat, stirring until it crumbles.
Drain and return to skillet.
Stir in tomato sauce and next 3 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Unroll 1 package dinner rolls, pressing seams together; fit into bottom of a lightly greased 13 x 9 baking dish.
Spread ground beef mixture over dough; sprinkle with cheese.
Unroll remaining package of dinner rolls, pressing seams together; place over cheese.
Brush dough with milk and sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: fruit salad delight
directions: Mix together well and refrigerate.

title: kentucky barbecue
directions: Cook roast in crock-pot overnight or in pressure cooker for 2 hours.
Shred with fork and remove fat.
Set aside.
Cook onions and celery in broth until tender.
Mix all other ingredients in mixing bowl.
Empty broth from crock-pot and add all the ingredients together.
Stir well and cook in crock-pot for 3 to 4 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: german chocolate streusel
directions: Blend all together and bake about 10 minutes in cookie sheet. Crumble with fork.
Layer streusel on bottom of pan, then layer 1/2 gallon of ice cream on top of streusel.
Then sprinkle remaining streusel on top of ice cream.
Freeze (overnight is best).
Can double recipe.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown beef and bacon.
Add onion and cook until tender. Drain.
Add spices and stir in soup.
Cook slowly, uncovered, 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat, but don't boil (will curd).
Serve over hot noodles or rice.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: strawberry supreme pie
directions: Fold strawberry yogurt into topping.
Add strawberries and blend.
Spoon into crust. Freeze until firm, about 4 hours. Forty-five minutes before serving refrigerate.
Store leftovers in freezer.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Spread 2 cups mayonnaise over entire surface.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and cover.
Let stand 24 hours in refrigerator. Stir before serving.

title: ida craver's dill pickles
directions: Boil together the vinegar, salt and water. Slice cucumbers in half lengthwise.
Drop in vinegar mixture until color changes. Pack in jars.
Add to each jar 2 heads of dill, 1 small hot pepper, 1/8 teaspoon of alum and 1 grape leaf.
Pour hot vinegar over pickles.
Seal.

title: jambalaya
directions: Remove shells from shrimp.
Using point of sharp knife, cut a slit along outer curve of shrimp, deep enough to expose black vein.
Pull out vein and rinse shrimp under cold running water. Set shrimp aside.

title: spice cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, then cream.
Add sifted flour, spices, soda and raw apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (1 1/2 recipe for 40 minutes).

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Add
bread
to milk.
Mix in next 5 ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Chill.
Brown meat balls in oil in a large skillet. Prepare
gravy
according to directions, using 1 1/4 cups water. Blend in mayonnaise.
Add to meat balls and heat. Makes about 45 meat balls.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine squash, onion and water in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 to 15 minutes until squash and onion are tender; drain well and mash.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix Coca-Cola, catsup, salt and pepper in boiler.
Add chicken pieces and cook until tender.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil 10x sugar and milk for 5 minutes.
Add marshmallow and peanut butter; beat until smooth.
Pour into buttered dish and cut when cooled.

title: ice cream cake *
directions: In a very large container, combine softened ice cream, strawberries, pineapple and nuts, beat with mixer.
Add broken cake pieces and beat slightly.
Fold in whipped cream.
Freeze overnight in tube pan.

title: pecan logs
directions: Mix up in large pan and make into rolls and slice as wanted.

title: anise biscuit cookie
directions: Grease an 11 x 5-inch pan.
Spread the batter in strips.
Pat the top of each strip with a little milk and sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake at 350° until top is light brown.
Cut into strips. Leave plain or top with confectioners sugar and water frosting, so it's not too sweet.

title: candy cake
directions: Mix well all together.
Grease and flour cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or longer, depending on cookie sheet.
Spread peanut butter on cake while hot.
Cool cake.
Melt Hershey bar and spread over cooled cake.
Cut cake into small pieces.

title: taco dip(make night before.)
directions: Mix together the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix.
Let stand 2 to 3 hours or overnight in fridge!

title: butter balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients (except powdered sugar) together.
Roll dough into walnut sized balls.
Bake on a nongreased cookie sheet for 15 to 18 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.

title: beef casserole
directions: Put meat on bottom of dish. Sprinkle cheese over first layer. Mix milk with soup.
Pour soup over meat mixture.
(Poke holes so soup can seep down.)
Arrange Tater Tots on top. Bake at 375° for 55 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Brown flour and set aside.
Cut bacon into small pieces. Saute in small amount of bacon grease.
Add celery and onions; saute.
Add water, sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Add browned flour and stir until thickened.
Add ingredients to cooked potatoes.
May be eaten in 5 hours after cooked, but is better if served the next day.

title: grandma lora's christmas candy
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and 1 cup whipping cream together and bring to a hard boil.
Add another cup of whipping cream.
Bring to a hard boil.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Add butter.
Cook until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.

title: jalapeno spinach
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Make sauce of flour, butter and milk.
Cook until thickened.
Add seasonings.
Then add cheese, cut in small cubes.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Combine with spinach.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and chill 6 hours or longer (flavor improves with age). Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Melt margarine and pour over peanut butter and mix until peanut butter is well blended, then pour over confectioners sugar and mix.
Roll in small balls and place on waxed paper to dry. Melt square of wax and chocolate chips, then dip peanut butter balls into this mixture and put on wax paper to dry.

title: apricot salad
directions: Combine sugar, Jell-O and water; bring to a boil. Remove from heat and stir in fruit; set aside to cool.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Empty potatoes and sauce mix into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Heat tomatoes, water and oregano to boiling and stir into potatoes.
Arrange pepperoni on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake uncovered for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and drop teaspoonfuls of dough onto ungreased cookie sheet, about 2 inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pan to cool.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, salt, cinnamon, nuts and apples.
Beat eggs until foamy and add together.
Beat in oil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: one fruit cobbler
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add milk, stirring well.
Add vanilla.
Pour margarine into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour batter over margarine.
Top with cooked fruit.

title: coconut fruit squares
directions: Combine crumbs and butter; press firmly into bottom of 9-inch pan.

title: midget pot roast
directions: Sprinkle meat with 1 tablespoon flour.
Place in a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Mix 1 cup water, broth, soup mix, garlic, Worcestershire sauce and thyme.
Pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn meat.
Add potato, carrots and onions.
Cover.
Return to oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Remove meat and vegetables and keep warm.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Blend shortening and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat.
Stir in bananas and Special K.
Add dry ingredients with nuts.
Stir only until combined.
Spread in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Put into casserole dish.
Boil hot dogs.
Remove from water and slice lengthwise but not all the way through.
Add cheese strips into hot dogs.
Put hot dogs on top of the mashed potatoes and heat in microwave until cheese has melted, about 1 to 2 minutes.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix in a large container.
Makes approximately two quarts. Serve two teaspoons to each cup of boiling water.

title: tuna-clam spaghetti
directions: Add enough vegetable oil to tuna liquid to measure 1/4 cup. Heat in saucepan with butter.
Add garlic and parsley and saute 3 to 4 minutes.
Add flaked tuna including broth.
Heat gently; season with salt and pepper, if desired.
Serve on hot spaghetti. Makes 4 servings.

title: chili
directions: Saute garlic and onions in oil for 10 minutes.
Add beef and brown.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer about 30 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt
margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a casserole dish 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Combine chicken, tomatoes, soups and 1/2 cup cheese in bowl.
Dip tortillas in broth to soften slightly.
Layer tortillas, then mixture, until pan is almost full; cover with remaining cheese and sprinkle with broth (you may want to cover with foil so the tortillas don't get too dry).
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: icicle cucumber pickles
directions: You will need 8 pint jars.

title: cornbread
directions: Combine meal, 1 quart water and margarine; cook until thick. Add sugar, eggs, flour, baking powder, milk and salt.
Bake at 450° until it starts to brown, then finish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add milk and sugar; blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 25 minutes.

title: joe froggers(good)
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar until light and fluffy. Dissolve salt in water and mix with rum. Add soda to molasses. Sift flour with spices and add alternately with liquid ingredients to cream mixture. Stir well between each addition. The dough should be sticky and will be easier to handle if chilled overnight. Roll out to 1/2 inch thickness. Cut with large cutter, about 5 inches. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Measure 1 quart milk. Save out 1/2 cup and heat remainder in top of double boiler.
Sift together sugar, cornstarch and flour. Add egg yolks and the 1/2 cup milk that was retained.
Blend and add to heated milk.
Add butter.
Cook over hot water until thick, stirring all the time.
Then add vanilla.
Roll out graham crackers or vanilla wafers.

title: top-of-range pot roast
directions: Preheat family skillet over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Brown roast for 6 to 7 minutes per side.
Reduce heat to low.
Sprinkle roast with seasoned salt, pepper and soup mix.
Roast, covered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Do not add liquid.
Turn after 1 hour.
Raw vegetables may be added 1 hour before completion of roasting. Juices that accumulate may be used for gravy.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: creamy mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger mixture with onions and seasonings.
Drain and mix with tomato sauce (set aside).
Mix cottage cheese, sour cream, chiles and olives together (set aside).
Grate Jack cheese.
In cake dish, put a layer of chips, 1/2 layer of hamburger mixture, 1/2 layer of cream mixture and 1 cup of Jack cheese.
Repeat with other half.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted, about 10 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 teaspoon soda.
Add 7 to 8 cups popped popcorn.
Stir popcorn to coat.
Pour on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 1/2 hour, stirring once. When cool, store in airtight container, or in a plastic bag.

title: icebox cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and add egg yolks one at a time.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Add vanilla.
Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with ladyfingers, separated.
Add a layer of cream mixture, layer of pineapple and chopped cherries, then whipped cream.
Top with ladyfingers and decorate with cherries. Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.
Serves 15.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Use large mixing bowl.
Add bread crumbs, sugar and melted butter.
Beat 3 eggs and add to mixture.
Add one can of pineapple with its juice to bowl.
Mix in milk.
Mix well. Mix 1/2 cup of grated cheese into mixture.
Pour into baking dish. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes. Serve warm.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter biscuits and roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture (2 teaspoons cinnamon and 3/4 cup sugar).
Grease Bundt or angel food cake pan.
Layer in the dough balls.
Make 3 layers.
You can add brown sugar and pecans between layers.
Mix 1 cup sugar, margarine and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon; cook to a boil.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: "fast" food mexican
directions: Place tamales in greased casserole.
Top with chili and sprinkle with cheese and onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat 1 cup water to boiling.
Add cream cheese, sugar and jello.
Stir until cheese is dissolved.
Cool until partially thickened.
Add nuts, celery, pineapple and Dream Whip or cottage cheese.
I found for me, the cottage cheese is the best.

title: egg rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar together.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa together.
Alternately add eggs, milk and dry ingredients to creamed ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Pour into lightly greased and floured tube pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Cook macaroni according to directions on box; drain.
Mix ground beef, mushroom soup, 1/2 can of water, sour cream and cooked noodles.
Top with sliced cheese (approximately 8 to 10 slices).
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until cheese melts.

title: southern corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine corn, sugar, salt, pepper, green pepper and eggs.
Add butter to milk and heat until butter is melted.
Blend with corn mixture.
Bake in covered and buttered casserole for 1 hour.

title: grandma fulton's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Stir in beaten egg and water. Add sifted dry ingredients, then oats and chocolate chips.
Drop from a teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350 degrees for 10 - 15 minutes.

title: shrimp cocktail sauce
directions: Mix together and chill while preparing shrimp.
Add more horseradish if not hot enough.

title: lottie moon cookies(plain tea cake)
directions: Flavor to taste.
Roll thin and bake in quick oven.

title: mexican quesadillas with meat
directions: Save some Cheddar cheese for topping.
Brown meat in oil.
Mix in cheeses and salsa with browned meat.
Wrap in tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle some Cheddar cheese on top and melt.

title: crumb topped cherry pie
directions: Drain cherries, reserving 1 1/4 cups liquid.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add reserved liquid.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add cherries, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Pour into pie shell.

title: best baked brisket
directions: In a large foil-lined baking dish, place brisket.
Cover meaty side of brisket with brown sugar (massage in).
Then cover with garlic salt until white.
Turn meat over (fatty side up) and repeat previous steps.
Make sure that it is covered white with garlic salt.
Bake in oven on top rack uncovered and fatty side up at 350° for 2 hours for small brisket, 4 hours for large brisket.
Slice and serve as sandwiches or with a meal.

title: lemon nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Stir in extract.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder. Add flour mixture to sugar mixture alternately with milk.
Fold in lemon peel and nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 325° for 70 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Remove beet tops, leaving root and some stem.
Wash beets. Cover with boiling water and cook until tender-crisp.
Drain. Keep 1 cup cooking liquid. Remove skins.
Slice beets.

title: 1 2 3 casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni.
Drain.
In same pan heat soup, milk, cheese and tuna.
Stir in macaroni.

title: peanut butter cookie
directions: Mix eggs, water, oil and peanut butter well.
Add cake mix. Roll into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Start with potatoes on the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Put onion slices on top of potatoes.
Slice margarine and put on top of onions.
Add salt and pepper to pork chops and then place chops on top of onions.
Cover with foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for one hour.

title: c.j.'s bird nests
directions: Put the chocolate chips and peanut butter in a pan and melt over low heat.
Stir mixture well.
Add the chow mein noodles and mix well using two forks, or spoons to coat them evenly with the chocolate mixture.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Put all ingredients in a roasting pan.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 4 hours.
Remove meat and flake apart.
Put meat back into the sauce.
Serve on buns.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach as directed on package.
Drain well and squeeze out all water.
Mix with stuffing and the other ingredients.
Mix well and shape into balls.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Balls may be made ahead and frozen. Bake frozen balls for 25 minutes.

title: sausage quesadillas
directions: Brown ground beef with seasoning over medium heat. Drain and set aside. Divide meat and cheeses evenly over 12 tortillas. Moisten tortilla edges with water.
Moisten edges of remaining 12 tortillas, place over meat mixture.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix together and chill in refrigerator.

title: fig - strawberry preserves
directions: Wash figs and cut off any dark spots.
Mash and mix other ingredients together.
Cook 3 or 4 minutes at a hard boil.
Put in jars and cover with wax.
When cooled, store in refrigerator.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Beat together the sugar and egg.
Add flour.
Add rhubarb. Mix together well.
Bake in 2 crusts.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Set cheeses out to warm to room temperature.
Put Neufchatel in a bowl; grate Cheddar and crumble Blue vein into the bowl.
Add green pepper, spring onions and a daub of softened butter.
Add red pepper and all other ingredients except nuts.
Mix together with a wooden spoon until well blended and smooth.
Lay out a sheet of cling wrap (plastic), place mixture on it and mold into a ball. Refrigerate until firm, at least 45 minutes.
Toast almonds lightly in the oven and allow to cool.
Take plastic off the ball and coat well with the almonds.
Serve on a platter with a variety of crackers and crudities.
Use a knife to spread.

title: mexican-style black bean salad
directions: Drain the soaked beans and combine them with the onion, 2 garlic cloves and the water in a large soup pot.
Bring to a boil; reduce the heat, cover and cook for one hour or until the beans are just about tender.
Add salt (a teaspoon or more) and 2 more garlic cloves and continue to cook for 30 to 60 minutes longer, until the beans are tender.
Drain and reserve 1 cup of the cooking liquid.

title: mix-in-the-pan chocolate cake
directions: Measure into an oblong cake pan the flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Stir together.
Make 3 holes in the ingredients.
Put oil, vinegar and vanilla each into a hole.
Pour water over all. Mix well with a spoon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot and spicy syrup for pancakes
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon together.
Stir in water.
Bring to a boil.
Add candies, if desired.
Boil until clear and thick.
Best served hot.
Refrigerate to store.
Reheat in saucepan or in microwave.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place pork chops in medium or large baking dish with lid.
Cut potatoes into small pieces; chop up onions.
Put potatoes and onions over the pork chops, then pour mushroom soup over all.
Add salt and pepper and water.
Cover; bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours, or until potatoes and meat are tender.

title: chocolate bite cookies
directions: Cream shortening and add gradually the 2 sugars.
Beat until light.
Add egg and beat.
Sift flour mixture.
Add vanilla, nuts and chocolate bits.
Mix thoroughly and drop from teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 370° until brown.

title: russian eyeball
directions: Blend softened	cream
cheese
and sugar in bowl with a fork. Fold
in
chips.
Roll into balls.	Roll in coconut and place on cookie sheet and put in refrigerator until firm.

title: sweet and savory meatballs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Form into meatballs and brown in shortening.
Drain.
Mix last 5 ingredients and pour over meatballs in skillet.
Cook over low heat until well heated. Serve over rice.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss lightly.
Serve on lettuce if desired.
Mayonnaise may be substituted for French dressing.
This salad can be used to stuff tomatoes.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown chops for 15 to 20 minutes over medium-high heat.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with pepper, garlic and salt (optional; the mushroom soup has a lot of salt).
Top with onion slices and mushroom soup.
Cover.
Cook for at least 45 minutes (60 minutes is better) at 350°.

title: lentil spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onions, carrots and garlic in oil until tender; add remaining ingredients and simmer one hour.
Serve over hot, cooked pasta.

title: oven baked french toast
directions: Place bread in lightly greased 9x13 dish.

title: tandy cake
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat in flour and baking powder.
In saucepan, scald milk and add margarine.
Add to above batter.
Pour into greased high-sided cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 22 minutes.
When done, spread jar of peanut butter on top of cake.
Put in refrigerator until peanut butter is hard.
In double boiler, melt chocolate bar.
Spread on top of cake.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients (flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda), then add them alternately with sour cream to margarine mixture.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and syrup in a large skillet; turn stove on high.
When this mixture begins to bubble, add peanuts and time for 5 minutes or until a light golden brown, after cooking for 5 minutes.
Add soda and mix well.
Pour onto a greased cookie sheet.
Break and eat.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream well Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well between eggs.
In a separate bowl, mix cocoa and red food coloring together; add to first mixture.
Mix soda and vinegar and add to mixture.
Beat 2 to 3 minutes.
Grease and flour pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Bake or fry chicken wings until browned and tender.
Drain if you fry on a paper towel.
Set aside if you bake.
Mix vinegar, water, catsup, sugar, salt and soy sauce in a saucepan.
Mix cornstarch in a small amount of water to make a paste; stir into sauce.
Cook and stir sweet and sour sauce until smooth.
Serve hot or cold.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine pineapple with pudding mix until it thickens.
Add 2 cups marshmallows.
Add Cool Whip, pecans and cherries.
Mix well and chill.

title: large zucchini muffins
directions: Mix, with mixer, first four ingredients.
Add flour.
Continue mixing.
By hand, add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in a large muffin pan or 1 hour in loaf pan.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: basic fruit pie
directions: Bake in 425° oven for 50 minutes.

title: spicy corn
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and pour into greased baking dish. Top with bread crumbs and 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini - cheese casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook zucchini in boiling salted water, about 3 to 4 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain well.
In skillet, cook ground beef and onions until meat is browned and onion is tender. Drain off excess fat.
Stir in rice, soup, oregano, salt and garlic powder.

title: klemm family favorite cheeseball
directions: Fluff the cream cheese with a fork.
Mix other ingredients into it, excluding nuts.
Add 2/3 cup nuts.
Shape into a ball. Roll in remaining nuts.
Chill.
Great served with Ritz crackers.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix ingredients, except cukes and onions, then add cukes and onions.
Bring just to boiling point, lifting cukes and turning them over with a spoon as slices begin to curl.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal.
Do not use the same ingredients for second batch. Always make fresh.
Measure cukes in gallon jar, adding an extra cuke for 5 pints.

title: lasagne(noodles)
directions: Mix with mixer about 20 minutes.
In small skillet, about 6-inch size (hot and lightly oiled), pour about 1/4 cup mixture in. Let cook until edge turns.
Flip over for about 1 minute, take out and put on tea towel.
Let cool.
Continue until mixture is gone. Use in place of box noodles.

title: cherry punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
Serves 35.

title: golden fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake 2 1/2 hours in 275° oven.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with Melba toast or favorite crackers.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour in 13 x 4 x 2-inch pan.

title: micro cream style corn
directions: Dissolve flour in water.
Add all ingredients into 1 1/2-quart microwave covered dish.
Cook on High for 6 minutes.
Stir and cook for 6 more minutes.
Stir and cook 6 more minutes and serve.

title: chess pie(this recipe originally comes from england)
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and butter.
Beat on high for 5 minutes. Blend in remaining ingredients. Pour into pastry-lined pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° or until a knife comes out clean when inserted in the middle.

title: scandinavian noodles
directions: Cook noodles and drain. Cook meat with onions and seasonings. Stir in undiluted soup and sour cream. Mix with noodles.

title: pecan cheese ball
directions: Combine everything except 1/4 cup pecans.
After mixing well shape into ball and coat with remaining nuts.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, sugars, dressing and vanilla at medium speed.
Add flour and baking soda.
Set aside 1 cup of batter.
Spread remaining batter into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Melt caramels with milk over low heat, stirring frequently.
Top crust with caramel mixture; sprinkle with chips and pecans.
Spoon reserved 1 cup batter by teaspoonfuls over pecans.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry relish salad
directions: Chop cranberries in a food chopper fine.
Sprinkle sugar over cranberries and let sit 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Arrange 1/2 squash; cover with onions and sprinkle sugar over onions.
Crumble crackers and drop in open spaces.
Dot with oleo. Spoon 1/2 soup over all.
Put another layer.
Top with cracker crumbs and melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: walnut tarts
directions: Mix and refrigerate at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: 5 minute fudge
directions: Combine carnation with sugar in saucepan.
Heat to boiling. Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, add remaining ingredients.
Stir
until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into buttered 8 or 9 inch pan.

title: lemon barbecued meat loaves
directions: Combine meat, bread, lemon juice, onion, egg and salt.
Mix well and shape into 6 individual loaves.
Place in greased baking pans; bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef in oil in a large skillet.
Drain.
Add garlic, season salt and pepper to meat; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes and spaghetti sauce.
Stir thoroughly.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: carbonara-style fettuccine
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions.
About 5 minutes before pasta is cooked, gradually add sweet pepper to boiling water.
Meanwhile, whisk together the eggs, sour cream, cheese, salt and pepper in a medium-size bowl.
Drain pasta; return to saucepan.
Immediately pour egg mixture over pasta.
Add bacon and parsley.
Toss together until pasta is well coated with sauce.
Serve.

title: orange bow knot rolls
directions: Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm; soften yeast in mixture.
Add eggs, juice and grated peel.
Beat thoroughly; add flour and mix to soft dough.
Cover and let stand in bowl for 10 minutes.
Knead lightly on a floured board surface. Let rise until double.
Punch holes in after it rises.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Brown onions, peppers and hamburger.
Add Prego sauce.
Mix cheese.
Cook noodles.
Layer noodles, cheeses, noodles and sauce. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange drink
directions: Mix ingredients and enough water to make 1 gallon.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Mix everything in coffee urn, except cloves and cinnamon; put these in basket.
Turn on coffee urn 30 minutes before serving.

title: brown health bread
directions: Put in a greased bread tin.
Bake at 375° about 1 hour.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix all together and pour into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill 3 hours and serve.

title: cubed steak and new potatoes pizzaiola
directions: In covered large, heavy skillet over low heat, saute potatoes in oil for 10 minutes, shaking skillet occasionally.
Push potatoes to one side.
Add meat; brown meat quickly over high heat, turning once.
Reduce heat.
Add tomatoes, garlic, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, or until potatoes and meat are tender.

title: cream gravy
directions: Combine drippings and flour in skillet.
Heat and stir for a minute or two.
Add milk; cook until slightly thickened, stirring constantly.
Season well with salt and pepper.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage in a skillet; cook until done.
Drain well. In a large bowl, mix milk, eggs, salt and pepper, then stir in cheese, sausage and bread.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes, or until set.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco mix.
Spread on a pizza pan.
Spread on cut up lettuce, then a layer of tomatoes and shredded cheese.
Top with olive slices.
Use taco chips to dip.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Drain.
Mix soups, milk and taco seasoning together.
Add meat.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Then add to dry ingredients.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Roll dough out and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
You can also color the dough, but do so before you add flour.

title: chili dip
directions: In slow cooker or crock-pot, layer ingredients in following order: cream cheese, onion, chili and cheese.

title: ham bites
directions: Spread cream cheese on a ham slice. Place a pickle stick at one end; roll ham tightly and secure with toothpicks. Put 4 toothpicks along the ham roll. Chill 1 hour and slice between toothpicks, leaving toothpicks in place.

title: sour pickles
directions: Wash small cukes and pack in sterile jars.
Mix ingredients and pour over cukes cold.
Let age about 2 weeks.
Makes about 9 quarts.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain; melt butter, blend in flour and add milk.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add seasonings.
Add 1 1/2 cups of cheese; stir until melted.
Place cooked macaroni in greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over macaroni.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: slow cook pot roast(microwave)
directions: Sprinkle 1 tablespoon seasoning mix on each side of roast. Rub in gently.
Place roast in plastic roasting bag.
Place in 2-quart utility dish.
Add onion and water to roast in bag.
Close bag loosely, securing with string on 1/2-inch strip cut from open end of bag.
Cook on cook level 3 for 1 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours (about 40 minutes per pound) or until roast is tender.
Turn roast over 2 to 3 times during cooking time.
Let stand in bag for 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Yield: 1 (2 to 5 pound) roast.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and chopped pepper (to taste). Drain.
Mix flour, meal, eggs, oil, corn and milk together.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased pan.
Layer ground beef mixture, then Cheddar cheese.
Top with rest of batter.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes, until done.

title: grammy's cornbread
directions: Put sugar, soda, salt and baking powder in large bowl and add buttermilk.
Stir well.
Add cornmeal alternately with flour. Melt shortening in loaf pan and add to mixture.
Sprinkle a little cornmeal in loaf pan.
Heat pan and pour mixture into hot pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve with whipped butter and whipped honey.

title: custard mochi
directions: Mix all ingredients
together.	Grease	and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese and broccoli potato topper
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, combine soup, sour cream and mustard. Add broccoli.
Heat through; stir occasionally.
Serve over potatoes.
Garnish with chopped sweet red peppers, if desired.

title: norwegian apple crumb cake
directions: Melt butter in a pan.
Add crumbs, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In Pyrex cake pan, place layer of crumbs and layer of applesauce. Repeat, ending with crumbs.
Dot with a little more butter.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Serve warm with Custard Sauce.

title: poppy seed coffee cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in two greased and floured loaf pans at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pans 15 minutes, slice and serve.

title: spinach fantastic
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.

Press spinach between paper towels to remove excess water. Combine rice, spinach and remaining ingredients. Spoon into lightly greased 2-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Can be assembled ahead of time and chilled 8 hours.
Let stand for 30 minutes at room temperature before baking. Serves 6.

title: poor man's soup
directions: Put all ingredients except tomato juice in large pan (this includes raw hamburger and uncooked macaroni).
Cook for 20 minutes.
Take away from heat and immediately add tomato juice. Heat again, if needed.
Serve and enjoy.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken 30 minutes.
Skin and bone; break into small pieces.
Put in bottom of casserole pan.
Mix everything else together and pour over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: no peek pork chops or chicken
directions: Mix cream soups, water and rice together and put into a baking dish.
Lay pork chops or chicken on top.
Sprinkle the onion soup on meat.
Cover with foil and bake 2 or 3 hours at 275°.

title: cranberry fruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Break up and stir in cranberry sauce, undrained pineapple, orange juice, lemon juice and nuts.
Pour into a shallow casserole dish.
Chill until firm. Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaves with salad dressing.

title: scalloped asparagus
directions: Place asparagus in buttered casserole.
Blend melted butter, flour and milk.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese and salt.
Pour over asparagus.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: west virginia salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Cool; add 7-Up.
When it begins to set add pineapple (saving juice), banana slices and marshmallows.
Combine sugar, flour, pineapple juice and egg; beat slightly and cook over low heat until it thickens.
Add butter and set aside to cool.
Prepare Dream Whip and cream cheese and fold into cooled mixture.
Sprinkle nutmeats and coconut over top.

title: prune cake
directions: Beat well the first 3 ingredients, then add cinnamon, cloves, baking soda, nutmeg and the baking powder.
Add the prunes and flour, all the while keep mixing.
Finally, add sour cream and semi-sweet chocolate chips with a spoon.
Grease a tube pan and put batter in.
Sprinkle on top 1/2 cup chopped nuts and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in cake comes out clean.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, add the rest of the ingredients to it and mix well.
Bake in skillet or muffin tins at 450° until done.
This can also be used to make hushpuppies.
Just drop by spoonsful into hot oil and cook.

title: tortilla roll appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tortillas, together.
Spread on tortillas, roll tightly and chill.
Cut into 1-inch slices. Skewer each slice with colored toothpick, if desired.

title: easy party punch
directions: Mix kool-aid, sugar and water. Add pineapple juice. Chill-when ready to serve pour over ice in punch bowl. Add chilled ginger ale. Add two pints of raspberry sherbet.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Dot with butter. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300°, bake for 45 minutes more.

title: tutti frutti ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into 1 gallon freezer can. Freeze.

title: pineapple-strawberry punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large punch bowl.
Mix well.
Add ice.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: charlie browns
directions: Mix butter, salt, sugar and milk and bring to boil.
Stir in peanut butter, oats, nuts and vanilla.
Drop on waxed paper. Makes many!

title: buffalo wings
directions: Heat oil approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut wings apart and throw away tips. Fry wings 20 minutes for frozen and 12 minutes for thawed.
Fill bottom of 2 1/2-quart pan of red hot sauce and butter.
Drain excess oil from wings and place in pan with the hot sauce.
Cover and shake well.
Place in serving dish and serve with Bleu cheese dip, celery and carrots.
Use more or less hot sauce to taste.

title: traditional english yorkshire pudding(serves 4 people)
directions: (To cook with roast sirloin of beef.)

title: vegetable salad
directions: Use any or all or any other vegetable you want.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Dissolve yeast in 1/3 cup warm water.
Add milk and yeast mixture and oil to dry ingredients. Stir well.
Cover and store in icebox.
This will keep for up to 2 weeks.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Cook all ingredients of Pumpkin Mix until thick. Cool.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Beat half and half with eggs and flour until smooth.
Slit open chilies; rinse out seeds and drain on paper towel.
Mix cheeses; reserve 1/2 cup for topping.
Make alternate layers of remaining cheese, chilies and egg mixture in deep 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour tomato sauce over top and sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until cooked in center.
Makes 4 servings if used as main dish.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a saucepan until well blended (no lumps).
Add milk gradually.
Stir until smooth.
Cook slowly over medium to low heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks.
Cook and stir 1 minute longer.
Add margarine.
Blend until melted; add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell. Cover with meringue from 2 egg whites, a spoon of sugar and drop of vanilla.
Bake in 350° oven.
Cool.

title: bubble bread
directions: Thaw rolls completely and let rise.
In a bowl, put the melted butter.
In another bowl, combine the sugar and the cinnamon. Pinch off pieces of rolls.
Roll in butter and then roll in sugar mixture.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes in tube pan on lowest rack.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream sugar, margarine and oil until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture and beat until smooth.
Blend in milk and vanilla.
Drop about 3 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Flatten with glass bottom dipped in sugar. Bake at 400° about 12 minutes.
Yields 5 1/2 dozen.

title: buffalo potato wedges
directions: Mix margarine, vinegar, pepper sauce and salt in shallow dish. Cut each potato lengthwise into 4 wedges.
Pat dry with paper towel.
Dip potato wedges into margarine mixture.
Reserve any remaining margarine mixture.
Cook in 350° oven for 25 to 35 minutes, turning twice, brushing occasionally with margarine mixture.
Cook until tender.
Serve with dressing.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and simmer 3 hours.
Delicious on chicken and spareribs.
I keep this made up.

title: poppy seed dressing (sweet)
directions: Note:
Pure corn
oil is best.	Don't use canola oil or olive oil!

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.	Add egg, beat thoroughly and add thawed rhubarb.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover with top crust or lattice.
Bake in hot 425° oven for 10 minutes; reduce heat to moderate 350° and bake 35 minutes longer.

title: potato fingers(czech slaski)
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Add salt and flour.
Make a stiff dough using more flour, if needed.
Take about a 1/2 cup dough and roll into a rope on floured board.
Roll into finger thickness. Cut into 3-inch lengths.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° until brown on bottom.
Turn each one and brown other side. Remove from pan.
Place in greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Cover with 1 1/2 cups half and half or light cream.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: baked german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet; drain off fat.
Measure fat and return 1/4 cup to skillet.
Add celery and onion; cook 1 minute. Blend in flour.
Stir in water and vinegar; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick and bubbly.
Stir in sugar and pepper.

title: spring chicken 'n rice
directions: Cook rice as directed.
In a large skillet, saute onions and peppers, leaving firm.
Pull chicken off bones and set aside. Bring chicken broth to a boil.
Stir cornstarch into 1/4 cup water; mix thoroughly.
Pour into chicken broth; cook until broth thickens slightly.
Add chicken, peppers and onions.
Pour meat mixture over rice in a large serving bowl.
Place tomatoes over top to garnish.

title: steak supper special
directions: On wax paper, mix flour and salt.
Use to coat beef cubed steaks.
In 12-inch skillet over medium heat in hot salad oil, cook steaks until browned on both sides, about 4 minutes.
Place each steak on a slice of bread on warm platter.
Keep warm.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar and syrup in large bowl.
Cook 4 minutes on High.
Stir; cook 4 minutes more.
Add vanilla and butter; cook 2 minutes.
Add soda; stir.
Pour on buttered surface.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add other ingredients (except dough) and stir to mix.
Cut loaves of bread dough in small pieces.
Put one-half of dough pieces in bottom of greased cake pan.
Pour pudding mixture over bread.
Add remaining dough pieces.
Let rise.
Place pan in oven and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pork chops with stuffing
directions: Saute together butter, onion and celery.
Remove from heat. Combine onion and celery mixture in a bowl with bread crumbs, parsley flakes, salt, sage, pepper and hot water.
Mix lightly. Spread mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Season pork chops with salt and pepper and arrange on top of stuffing.
Spoon soup over chops.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chops are tender.

title: barbecue style pot roast
directions: Trim fat from meat.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In a Dutch oven, brown meat on all sides in margarine.
Remove meat. Add onions and garlic.
Cook until tender but not brown.
Stir in barbecue sauce, mushrooms, dry mustard, chili powder and 1/2 cup of water.
Add meat.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat; boil pan juices gently, uncovered, for 3 to 5 minutes or to desired consistency, stirring often.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Mix sugar with flour.
Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon and raspberries in a bowl.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with Crumb Mixture.

title: chocolate-caramel cake
directions: Bake cake in long pan according to instructions.
While cake is baking, warm caramel sauce for easy pouring.
Remove cake from oven; while hot, poke holes in it and pour caramel sauce over the cake.
Let cool to room temperature.
Spread Cool Whip topping over cake and sprinkle crushed Heath bars on top.

title: german potato salad
directions: Combine the ingredients and heat.
Salt and pepper to taste. Serves 16.
May be served cold.

title: chicken filled shells
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Stuff shells.
Arrange in single layer in baking dish.
Stir water into soup; pour over shells.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 325° oven for 25 minutes. Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: libyan bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl with hands, making sure yeast and salt are well distributed.
Add 3 cups very warm water (for 6 cup mixture, dough will be thick) and mix with hands, as it will be easier.
Cover and let set until dough is doubled in bulk.
Pour onto a floured board.
Roll out and cut into rolls. Place rolls in a greased or oiled pan (there should be enough oil to coat the rolls) and let set for 1 hour.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Ovens vary in temperature.
This bread does not contain any oil except for oil placed in pan.

title: thin layer chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, vanilla and milk.
Beat until well blended.
Put 4 tablespoons in a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes per layer.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Put first 4 ingredients into a bowl.
Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over ingredients and mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: ye elegant cherries-in-the-snow fudge(in honor of i.t.p.h.a. racing)
directions: Marinate the thawed and drained cherries (where necessary) in Kirsch for 1 hour, at least.

Drain thoroughly and chop coarsely. Break up the chocolate-by-the-pound "type" chocolate, for truly luscious candy fudge, or use the widely available chocolate chips. Combine with the marshmallow cream and set aside.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Combine salad dressing mix, oil and spices.
