Pour over crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir to coat. Bake 15 minutes, stirring halfway through.
Store in airtight container.

title: mom's barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer on low heat.

title: spaghetti chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken well done; remove from broth and cut in small pieces.
Add chopped onion to broth; add box of spaghetti.
Cook until done; drain.
Add all other seasonings to chopped chicken. Mix well, then add spaghetti and pour into casserole.
Spread grated cheese on top.
Bake at 400° until cheese is melted.
Serve hot.

title: key lime pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add lime rind and juice. Add egg yolk slowly, stirring constantly.
Add condensed milk. Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in beaten egg white.
Form into pie crust.
Chill several hours.
Top with whipped cream. Serves 6.

title: lasagna rolls
directions: Spread spaghetti sauce on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Saute beef and onion in butter until beef is brown.
Drain fat. Allow to cool slightly. Mix thoroughly with bread crumbs the egg, thawed and drained spinach, salt,
pepper and oregano.
Cut cooked lasagna noodles in halves.
Place 2 tablespoons of beef mixture on each half of noodles; roll and place seam down in spaghetti sauce. Cover rolls with cheese.
Cover baking dish tightly with foil and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and continue baking for an additional 20 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chinese almond biscuit cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Cream margarine and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Beat in 2 eggs and almond extract.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Form into balls an inch in diameter and place on greased baking sheet.
Place half almond on top of cookies.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until golden.

title: company potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on; cook in refrigerator.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch glass dish with Pam.
Peel potatoes and grate into dish. Season with onion salt, salt and pepper.
Pour whipping cream over all.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until brown.

title: flaky pastry
directions: Mix and sift flour and salt.
Cut shortening into flour with 2 knives or pastry blender.
Add enough water to hold ingredients together, sprinkling it in evenly and mixing with a fork.
Wrap dough in waxed paper; chill 1/2 to 1 hour before rolling.

title: whopper wafers
directions: Put icing on the bottom of the peppermint patty and place on the flat side of a vanilla wafer.
Ice the flat side of the second vanilla wafer and sprinkle outer edge with green coconut.
Place on top of peppermint patty.
Using a new paint brush, dab with light Karo and sprinkle with sesame seeds.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Chop vegetables into small pieces.
Cook spaghetti.
Combine all ingredients.
Add italian dressing according to taste.
Once all items are combined, refrigerate.

title: jerry's chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Butter a 9-inch spring-form pan (2 1/2 inches on sides).
Coat pan with sugar; tap out excess.
Melt butter and 1/4 cup sugar in heavy medium saucepan over low heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Add chocolate; stir until melted. Remove from heat.
Mix in brandy.
Whisk egg yolks in medium bowl until thick and pale yellow, approximately 4 minutes.
Whisk in warm chocolate mixture and vanilla (mixture will be very thick or may appear broken).
Using electric mixer, beat egg whites with salt in large bowl until foaming, gradually adding remaining sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Beat until soft peaks form. Whisk 1/3 of egg whites into chocolate mixture.
Gently fold in remaining whites.

title: elegant tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cook noodles al dente and drain.
In a 2-quart casserole, combine noodles, thyme and salt; set aside. Heat soup and milk in a saucepan, stirring until smooth.
Add tuna, celery, green pepper, chestnuts, scallions, mayonnaise and all but 2 tablespoons of the cheese.
Heat, stirring, until the cheese is melted.
Pour over noodles and mix.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and almonds over top.
Bake about 25 minutes, until bubbly and lightly browned.

title: muffin mix corn
directions: Bring sour cream to room temperature.
Melt margarine and saute onion.
Set aside.
Mix both cans of corn with the eggs. Add muffin mix and sauteed onion.
Stir in sour cream and pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle grated cheese over all. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: parmesan onion bread
directions: Combine onion,	mayonnaise
and cheese.
Slice bread in half lengthwise	and
spread
with
cheese
mixture;
place on baking sheet and bake
for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly and lightly
browned.	Cut crosswise into serving size pieces.
Makes 16 to 20 pieces.

title: dressing
directions: Mix together 1 can Campbell's cream of mushroom soup, 1 can water
and package of seasoning from the box of dressing. Simmer for
about	5
minutes
over medium heat. Add chicken, margarine and
bread crumbs from the box of dressing.
Put in casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: oven-barbecued beef
directions: Pour liquid smoke over brisket placed in a baking dish. Generously sprinkle meat on both sides with celery salt, onion salt and garlic salt which tenderizes it.
Place in refrigerator, covered, overnight.
Next morning, sprinkle both sides of meat with salt and pepper and a little Worcestershire sauce.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 4 to 5 hours in 275° oven.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Cream butter and beat in sugar.
Add vanilla, flour and pecans.
Roll in palm of hand the size of a butter ball.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: pancake zizzlees
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients.
Cook pancakes on griddle. While hot fold in half, then in quarters.
Set aside to reheat in sauce to serve.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch buttered baking dish.
Cover with 1/4 cup melted butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Cook milk and sugar together for 5 minutes.
Stir at all times on medium heat.
Have ready the nuts and chocolate chips.
Add marshmallows.
Grease pan with butter or margarine.
Set in cool place, not in refrigerator.

title: deviled eggs with zip
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks; mash in small bowl.
Combine mayo, salt, pepper and mustard.
Mix until very smooth.
Crumble bacon as fine as possible and add to egg mixture; stir until combined.
Using largest decorating tip possible spoon egg mixture into frosting bag and pipe into egg whites or spoon mixture into egg whites.
Cover and refrigerate until ready.
If desired sprinkle with a little paprika.

title: herbed green beans
directions: Wash beans; trim ends and remove strings.
Cut beans into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Combine beans and water in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly with heavy-duty plastic wrap; fold back a small edge of wrap to allow steam to escape.
Microwave at High 9 to 10 minutes, or until crisp-tender, stirring after 3 minutes. Let stand, covered, 2 minutes; drain.
Place green pepper, onions and oil in a small bowl.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap; microwave at High 3 to 4 minutes, or until tender.
Add green pepper mixture, tomato and remaining ingredients to beans; mix well.
Cover and microwave at High 2 to 3 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Yields 4 servings.

title: thompson temptation
directions: Combine crumbs with butter.
Press into 9-inch square pan. Grate or finely chop 1/2 package chocolate.
Heat remaining chocolate and mix.
Stir until melted.
Whisk in cream cheese until smooth and cool completely.
Fold in 3 1/2 cups Cool Whip. Spread over crumbs.
Sprinkle top with the shaved chocolate.

title: crab rangoon
directions: Beat cream cheese and milk together until creamy.
Add the cheese, garlic powder and crabmeat.
Pat 3/4 teaspoon mixture in center of wonton skin.
Use enough water on fingers to moisten corners.
Pinch together to form triangles.
Repeat until all filling and wonton skins are used.

title: crock-pot russian chicken
directions: Mix first three ingredients in a crock-pot.
Add chicken. Cook on low for 4 to 5 hours or until chicken is tender.

title: creamed celery with pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Boil celery until tender in enough water to cover; drain.
Melt butter; stir in flour and add milk slowly to make cream sauce, stirring until thick and smooth.
Add salt and well-drained celery.
Spoon into prepared casserole, top with pecans and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: grandma's homemade ice cream
directions: Beat thoroughly.
Pour into a 5-quart freezer.
Add milk to fill to mark.
Follow freezer instructions to freeze.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Cook beef and onion until meat is brown and onion tender; drain.
Add tomato sauce, parsley, salt, pepper and oregano; mix well.
Line bottom of 9-inch pie plate with 1 package rolls, pressing edges together to form pie shell.
Separate 1 egg; set yolk aside.
Beat white with remaining 2 eggs.
Pour 1/2 over pie shell.
Spoon in meat mixture.
Top with tomato slices.
Arrange cheese on top; pour rest of beaten egg over.
Mix yolk with water; brush over pastry edge.
Roll second package of rolls into pie crust top.
Trim, seal and flute edges.
Cut slits, brush with remaining egg yolk mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake 20 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: corn spaghetti
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes covered and 30 minutes uncovered.

title: meat loaf (large)
directions: Mix all ingredients together; by hand is the best method. Press into a baking dish. Cover top with ketchup and bacon strips. Cook for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: lemon garlic chicken
directions: Remove skin and excess fat from chicken; rinse and pat dry.
In small bowl, mix oregano, seasoned salt and pepper; rub into chicken using all of the mixture.
In large skillet over medium heat, brown in butter.
Transfer chicken to a slow cooker.
Place water, lemon juice, garlic and bouillon in skillet.
Stirring over medium heat, bring to a boil, loosening browned bits from bottom of skillet. Pour over chicken.
Cover and cook on high for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or low 5 to 6 hours.

title: thin french apple tart
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Place dough on a lightly floured surface; roll into a 12-inch circle. Place on a 12-inch pizza pan. Combine sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar mixture over dough. Arrange apple slices spokelike on top of dough, working from outside edge of dough to the center. Sprinkle apple slices with remaining sugar mixture. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: ranch salad dressing
directions: Combine
all ingredients in a small bowl.
Refrigerate. Yield: 2 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix and let set overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in large frypan.
Drain off fat. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Makes 6 servings.

title: hot ravioli salad
directions: In skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain fat, reserving 1 tablespoon.
Return the tablespoon of fat to skillet and add onion.
Saute about 2 minutes.
Add ravioli, sugar, vinegar and pepper.
Cover and simmer until ravioli is heated.
Serve on lettuce.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt and make a well in the center.
Mix egg, vanilla and fruit cocktail into the dry ingredients and pour into a flat greased pan.
Combine 1 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup nuts and sprinkle on top of cake.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
You can also use the cake recipe without the topping and when you are ready to serve it put hot butterscotch pudding over the cake.

title: batter bread(shared by mrs. glenn hill)
directions: Scald milk; add margarine, sugar and salt.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
When milk mixture has cooled to lukewarm, add to yeast mixture.
Stir in flour and mix thoroughly.
Cover mixture with wax paper and a towel and allow to rise until double in bulk, about 40 minutes.
After dough rises, stir down with spoon and beat vigorously about 1/2 to 1 minute.
Divide dough into two well-greased loaf pans.
(Dough will be sticky and heavy.)
You may either bake immediately at 375° until golden brown or allow dough to rise to tops of loaf pans, then bake.

title: easy cherry brownies
directions: Combine eggs, vanilla, pie filling and cake mix until just blended.
Spread out in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm to touch.

title: chicken and pasta presto
directions: In skillet, over medium-high heat, heat oil.
Cook chicken until browned, stirring often.
Add remaining ingredients; heat to a boil.
Reduce heat to low, cover and cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve.
Serves 4.

title: oyster stew
directions: Heat cream in 2-quart saucepan over medium heat until it just starts to simmer.
Add potatoes and oysters with liquid.
Cook over low heat 3 to 6 minutes or until oysters float to top.
Add butter.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Continue simmering until butter melts.
Remove from heat.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley.
Serve at once.
Makes 2 3/4 cups.

title: plain rolls
directions: Measure warm water in mixing bowl.
Add sugar, salt and yeast. Let
stand.
Measure
flour and combine with dry milk. Add butter and half the flour to liquid.
Mix.
Add remaining flour and mix with dough hook until dough leaves side of bowl. Cover and let rise until double in
bulk.
Punch	down;
knead on lightly floured board.
Shape as desired.
Place in greased pans;
brush with melted butter.
Let
rise
until
double
in bulk.
Bake at 400° until light brown.

title: turkey pie
directions: Toss turkey with flour.
In a saucepan, cook carrots, onions, celery, thyme and pepper in the butter until tender.
Stir in soup, turkey mixture and green beans.
Pour into 9-inch pastry lined pie plate.
Top crust can be regular or lattice crossed. Brush pastry with milk.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until crust is lightly browned.

title: caramel pie
directions: *I like to put in maple flavor, too.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In a large bowl, combine the peaches with 2/3 cup sugar; toss well. Spoon the fruit into a shallow 10-cup baking dish and dot with butter.

title: asparagusa bites
directions: Mix cream cheese with Blue cheese and add egg.
Count number of asparagus spears in can; count out same number of slices of bread.
Trim crusts from bread.
Roll trimmed bread as thin as possible with rolling pin.
Spread each slice with cheese and egg mixture.
Place asparagus spear on each bread slice and roll up. Cut each rolled slice into thirds.
Dip each roll into melted butter.
Place close together in shallow baking pan.
May be frozen at this stage.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes if not frozen.
Bake 30 minutes or until brown if frozen.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Bring water to a boil; add carrots.
Cook until tender. Meanwhile, in a skillet over low heat, cook maple syrup, butter, marjoram, salt and pepper until bubbly and caramel-like.
Drain carrots; place in a bowl.
Pour sauce over and serve hot.
Can be done ahead and simply reheated.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Put meat into bowl.
Add other ingredients.
Form into small balls.
Fry in a small amount of fat, then remove.
Add boiling water, beef bouillon and 1 teaspoon sugar to pan.
Stir until blended.
Pour over meatballs.
May be frozen and/or reheated.

title: vegetarian spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute mushrooms, celery, onion and green pepper in olive oil for 2 to 3 minutes in a large pan.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, covered, 1 1/2 to 2 hours on low heat.

title: overnight salad
directions: Drain fruit and combine with sour cream, marshmallows and coconut.
Chill overnight.

title: stuffed pepper cups
directions: Cut off tops of green peppers.
Remove seeds and membrane. Precook green pepper cups in boiling, salted water about 5 minutes. Drain.
Sprinkle inside with salt.
(For crisp peppers, omit precooking.)

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cover chicken with water.
Add salt and simmer until tender. Remove skin and bones and return chicken to pot.
Add parsley flakes and poultry seasons.
If more broth is needed, add 1 can chicken broth.
Bring to a boil and add the biscuits which have been slightly kneaded and pulled into pieces.
Stir enough to cover the dumplings with broth.
Simmer 10 minutes or until done.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Form into 1-inch balls and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 50 balls.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan in oven.
Mix baking mix, paprika, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken; place skin side down in pan.
Set oven at 350°.
Bake 35 minutes; turn and bake until done, about 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° until done.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix water, sugar and salt. Add yeast. Stir until dissolved. Stir in egg and shortening.
Gradually add flour.
Place in greased bowl.
Rub surface with soft shortening. Cover tightly. Place in refrigerator until ready to use.
Shape into rolls.
Let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Bake 12 to 15 minutes in a 400° oven. Dough is easier to handle if kneaded before storing.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Boil and debone chicken.
Layer chicken, broccoli and cheese in casserole dish.
Mix lemon juice, mayonnaise and soup.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.

title: heavenly fruit salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Chill until syrupy. Whip with electric beater until frothy.
In separate bowl, whip softened cream cheese and mayonnaise.
When well blended, add whipped jello and drained fruit cocktail.
Fold in whipped topping.
Mold in 2-quart salad mold or 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish.

title: norwegian apple pie
directions: Beat together well the sugar and eggs.
Add pinch of salt, vanilla or almond extract, flour and baking powder.
Add chopped nuts and apples.
Place in buttered pie plate.
Bake at 350°
for 35 minutes.
Top with whipped cream before serving.

title: chocolaty chocolate brownies
directions: Melt butter, margarine and chocolate.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar and vanilla to butter mixture.
Add baking powder and flour to chocolate mixture.
Add 4 eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: chicken pockets with cheese sauce
directions: Put equal amounts of chicken into each rectangle of crescent roll.
Fold and press sides together to form pockets.
Place into slightly greased 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Over medium heat in medium size pan, combine milk, 1 cup cheese, soup, onion and butter.
Stir until cheese melts.
Pour mixture over pockets; top with remaining cheese.
Lightly salt and pepper.
Bake uncovered approximately 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve with steamed rice or tossed salad.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add other ingredients, except margarine and cracker crumbs.
Put in baking dish.
Top with crushed crackers.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Mix with all other ingredients.

title: cherry angel cream cake
directions: Cut cake into 1/4-inch slices; arrange half the slices on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In large mixer bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, water and extract; mix well.
Add pudding mix; beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream. Spread half the cream mixture over cake slices; top evenly with 1 can cherry filling.
Top with remaining cake slices, cream mixture and cherry filling.
Chill 4 hours or until set.
Cut into squares to serve.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix syrup with eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cover with pecans.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then 30 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: annie wingate's chicken noodle supreme
directions: Cook chicken in salted water until tender.
Reserve broth. Cut meat into large bite size pieces and set aside.

title: tortilla de queso
directions: Combine and mix cream cheese, green chilies, green onions, garlic and salt. Spread a layer of cream cheese mixture on each tortilla. Roll up and slice into bite size pieces.

title: pudding bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together (cake mix, egg and margarine).
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream remaining ingredients together and pour on top of first layer.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool, then cut into squares.

title: coconut bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, cinnamon and baking soda.
Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Add milk and eggs.
Bake at 350°.

title: limeade
directions: Mix and serve over ice.

title: baked beans 2
directions: Shuck, silk and wash corn. Put on rack in the oven.
Cook until done and brown.
Take out of oven and "smear" butter and salt on the corn and eat while hot.

title: cold pound cake
directions: Cream crisco, sugar and margarine. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour, alternately, with milk very slowly. Add vanilla. Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour 15 minutes in tube pan.

title: strawberry pie with rice crust
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch pie pan.
Beat rice, vanilla and egg white with fork.
Turn mixture into pie pan. Spread evenly with rubber scraper on bottom and halfway up side of pie pan.
(Do not leave any holes.) Bake 5 minutes; cool.

title: pizza pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown ground beef well; drain.
Place beef in an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Top with Pizza Quick sauce and cheese.
Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs; pour over pizza.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pineapple dip
directions: Mix all together and serve with crackers.

title: honey dijon dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in an electric blender and process until smooth.
Chill.

title: champagne cocktail
directions: Chill 6 to 8 champagne glasses, depending on how many people you wish to serve.
Combine the cognac, vermouth, Grand Marnier and Curacao in a large pitcher; mix well.
Pour in the champagne; stir until the "fizz" is gone.
Place a sugar cube in the bottom of each glass; dot each cube with 1 drop of the Bitters.
Crush the sugar cube and pour in the champagne.
Stir to combine; garnish each cocktail with an orange slice or a strawberry. Yields 6 to 8 cocktails.

title: greek style manicotti
directions: Cook shells, drain and put aside. Grill steak and cut into bite size pieces. Mix spaghetti sauce and steak together, add vegetables if desired. Put manicotti shells in an oblong pan and stuff shells with meat mixture. (It's easier to slit shells length ways on the sides, put stuffing on bottom half of shell and cover with top half.)

title: aunt cele's gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins and cool. Shred on coarse grater. Combine cheese and 4 tablespoons margarine/butter in pan. Heat and stir until cheese is almost melted. Remove from heat. Blend in sour cream, onions, salt and pepper. Fold in potatoes. Spoon into a well-greased 2-quart casserole. Dot with 2 tablespoons margarine/butter. Cover and bake at 300° for about 25 minutes.

title: rose red punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, combine concentrates and water.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and ice.

title: chicken rococo
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cut cheese into 8 equal sticks.
Cut chicken breasts in half; flatten each to 1/4-inch thickness.
Roll each piece around stick of cheese; secure with toothpicks.
Dip in eggs, then in bread crumbs.
Brown in margarine.
Dissolve bouillon cube in water.
Cook onion and green pepper in 1/3 cup margarine until tender; add flour, seasonings and bouillon.
Cook until thickened.
Add rice and mushrooms; pour into large baking dish.
Top with chicken; bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: everett's potato soup
directions: Saute onions, green pepper and celery in butter for 5 minutes. Add potatoes and water; cook until tender, about 15 minutes. Combine milk, cornstarch, salt and black pepper; stir into other ingredients until thick.
Serve in warm bowl.
Top with grated cheese.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Add beef, eggs, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in the cornstarch covering thickly.
Add more cornstarch as needed.
Brown in butter until brown.
Shake pan often to retain shape of meatballs.

title: toffee crisps
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheets.
In large bowl, beat sugar, brown sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs; blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in baking chips.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.
Immediately remove from cookie sheets.
Cool completely.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen cookies.
Store tightly covered.

title: hot seafood dish
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in baking dish.
Top with buttered crumbs, Ritz or Triscuits crackers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Cover with layer of cheese. Mix together crumbs and margarine.
Put on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: celery amandine
directions: Melt butter over low heat; add almonds.
Saute until light brown, add celery, onion, sugar, garlic powder, ginger and bouillon cube.
Stir carefully until well mixed and cook until crisp-tender about 10 minutes.
Serves 4 people.

title: maids of honor tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Butter may be melted for easier blending.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Mix everything but 2 tablespoons Parmesan in large bowl.
Turn into 2 quart casserole.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Before serving, add rest of Parmesan.
Place in preheated oven at 350° and bake covered for 35 minutes.
Uncover and bake additional 25 minutes.

title: easy hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Stir over low heat until mixture is smooth and well blended.
Serve hot over any ice cream.

title: red potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water 30 minutes or until tender; drain and cool.
Cut into quarters.
Combine chives and rest of ingredients in a large bowl.
Add potatoes to mixture and toss. Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: oatmeal caramelitas
directions: Melt caramels and milk.
Cool slightly.
Combine remaining ingredients (except chocolate chips and nuts).
Put 1/2 of this in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on this crust.
Then put caramel mixture on.
Put the rest of the ingredients on and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Chill 2 hours before cutting.

title: gingered carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9 x 1 1/2-inch round pans.
Set aside.

title: cobbler pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar gradually.
Add milk.
Melt butter in deep pan.
Put in 1/2 butter in batter, then pour batter in pan.
Pour fruit in center and out toward edge.
Put fruit juice in but do not stir.
Bake at 450°.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: In a large kettle, cover chicken with water and boil until done.
Do not drain!!
Take chicken out and cool until you can handle it and tear into small pieces.
Save broth!! Put 2 cups chicken broth in a pan and add cheese and melt, then add Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Cook spaghetti in rest of chicken broth.
Saute onions, green pepper, mushrooms, small amount of margarine and seasonings.

title: supper casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
In large casserole, add layer of meat, potatoes, onion, pepper and soup.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in skillet or pan at 350° until brown.

title: 1, 2, 3, 4, birthday cake
directions: Butter and flour tube pan.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt and add it alternately with the milk.
Beat 3 minutes.
Pour into pan.

title: party pizza rye
directions: Brown meat together; crumble well and drain.
Add spices. While meat is still hot, add cheese and let it melt.
Spread on party rye bread and put on a cookie sheet; freeze.
When they are frozen, you can put them in plastic bags.
When ready to serve, bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes to warm.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: Bring the milk to a boil.
Add the grits; cook until thick, stirring constantly, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Turn into sprayed baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: kathy's cheese ball
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese.
Let all ingredients come to room temperature.
Mix all together in mixer bowl and mix well with mixer beaters.
Let
stand overnight in bowl in the refrigerator. Next day, roll into ball and roll in chopped nuts.

title: easy stew soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat until hot.

title: three bean soup
directions: Wash dried beans and cover with water.
Cover and soak overnight.
In the morning, drain and add fresh water.
Heat slowly to boiling.
Meanwhile, heat oil in heavy soup kettle.
Add garlic, onion and celery.
Saute for 2 to 3 minutes until golden. Drain beans and add to onion and celery mixture.
Pour in beef stock and water.
Add bay leaf.
Heat to simmering.
Over low heat, simmer for 4 hours.
Add tomatoes.
Cut sausages into 1/2-inch lengths.
Add to soup.
Heat through.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with a sprinkling of fresh parsley and Parmesan cheese.

title: brunch souffle(serves 8)
directions: Brown sausage; drain and cool.
Crumble sausage into bowl. Beat eggs in another bowl and add milk, salt, mustard and bread cubes; mix well.
Add cheese and sausage; mix again.
Spoon into 12 x 8 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake as directed using whole eggs and throw in a handful of coconut.
After cake is cool, punch holes with a fork.
Then pour in mixture of cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk.
Mix coconut with Cool Whip and frost cake.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: date nut candy loaf
directions: Cook sugar, milk and syrup until the hard ball stage.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add all ingredients; simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over egg noodles or rice.

title: shrimp and mushrooms with pasta
directions: Boil water for vermicelli.
Heat skillet and add butter and olive oil.
Saute mushrooms until brown and crispy, about 5 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Spray a large skillet with a nonstick coating.
Stir-fry beef strips until browned.
Add all but the last 3 ingredients and simmer, covered, for 5 to 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, mix cornstarch with soy sauce and water.
Stir into hot mixture and continue cooking until thickened.
Serve over noodles or quick cooking brown rice.

title: burrito yummy
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer with thawed burritos and browned and well drained hamburger in the bottom of the pan.
Add onion, enchilada sauce, tomato sauce, taco mix, salt and pepper. Simmer 10 minutes. Spread over burritos.
Grate cheese over top. Bake for 1 hour at 300°.
Kids love it!

title: refrigerator dill pickles
directions: Use 1 (5-quart) ice cream pail with cover.
Wash and quarter cucumbers.
Add onion.
Put 4 to 6 heads of dill in bottom of pail. Add cucumbers and onion.
Top with 4 heads of dill.
Pour boiling brine over cucumbers.
Let stand, uncovered, 3 days.
On the fourth day, cover and refrigerate.
Will keep up to 1 year.

title: savory butter
directions: Blend all the ingredients well.
Use on French bread.
Yields 1/2 cup.

title: mike's favorite chicken recipe
directions: Liberally sprinkle thighs (the chickens not yours!) with the above ingredients.
As a variation insert garlic slices under the skin and /or squeeze some fresh lemon on the chicken.

title: creamy baked chicken breast
directions: Place chicken in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Top evenly with cheese slices.
Mix soup with wine or water and spread over cheese.
Top with stuffing mix and drizzle melted butter on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: microwave soft smokey cheese ball
directions: Unwrap cheeses.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, place smokey cheese.
Microwave at High 1 minute.
Add cream cheese.
Microwave at High 1 to 1 1/4 minutes more until cheeses can be mixed together.
Add Worcestershire sauce and blend mixtures well; stir in shredded cheese.
Mixture should remain gold-flecked.
Chill cheese mixture about 15 to 30 minutes in freezer or about 1 hour in refrigerator until it can be formed into a ball with the hands. Roll cheese ball in parsley, then pecans.
Chill to set.
Serve with crackers.

title: mexican spoon bread
directions: Mix cornmeal, salt and soda.
Stir in milk and oil; mix well. Add eggs and corn, mixing well.
Spoon half of the mixture into a greased 9 x 9-inch baking pan. Sprinkle half of the chilies on top, then half of the cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Pare 2 cups zucchini, unpeeled and uncooked.
Mix with wet ingredients.
In separate bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Pour wet mixture into dry mixture and mix together until moist.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Pour ingredients into oiled loaf pan (2) and bake 1 hour or until done.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Put sour cream in
a large mixing bowl.
Drain juice from mandarin oranges.
Mix all ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and let stand overnight, then drain.
Place mix in large pan.
Mix the sugar, vinegar, turmeric, celery seed and mustard together.
Add to vegetable mixture. Simmer on stove until vegetables are cooked.
Add cornstarch to a little water and add to relish.
Cook until clear.
Seal hot.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate).
Tear bread into large mixing bowl; add milk and egg.
Mix well.
Add meat and seasonings; mix thoroughly.
Form lightly into loaf and place in shallow baking pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.
This is a moist meat loaf!

title: jello cake
directions: Mix cake mix as usual; bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan, following box directions.
Let cake cool.
Mix jello with 1 1/2 cups boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water.
Let jello mixture set out at room temperature.
When cake is completely cooled, make holes in entire cake with a meat fork, making sure holes go to bottom of pan.
Very slowly pour jello over cake so that it saturates cake.

title: scalloped potatoes and pork chops
directions: In a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, layer half the potatoes and onion.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Repeat layers.
Combine soup and sour cream; pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: no bake fudge cookies
directions: Boil together the first four ingredients.
Add the next four ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: cranberry-pineapple glazed chicken
directions: Wash, dry and then shake in mixture of flour, paprika, salt, pepper and sage which is in a bag.
Heat oil and brown chicken. Add stock or water.
When it boils, cover pan and simmer on low (200°).
Cook 20 minutes longer.
Add cranberry/pineapple and juice/syrup.
Cook 20 minutes longer until tender.

title: holiday cheese tree
directions: Combine cheese food and cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add 1 tablespoon of finely chopped pimento, green pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce and juice; mix well.
Chill.
tags: extra sharp Cheddar cold pack cheese food

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients; spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Freezes well.
Tastes better the next day.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat; add onion and cook until golden.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: microwave beef stroganoff
directions: In a two-quart casserole combine onion and butter.
Microwave on High for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes until onion is tender.

title: onion rings
directions: Soak sliced onion in milk for 30 minutes.
Drain.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Dip onion in egg whites and then in flour and season, then deep fry.

title: cranberry spiced tea
directions: Dissolve cranberry sauce with 1 quart of water.
Combine and heat before serving.
Add red food coloring, if desired. This recipe serves 25.

title: honey penuche
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter and nuts.
Cook over low flame to 240°.
Stir just enough to prevent sticking.
Remove from heat; add butter and cool to lukewarm.
Do not stir.
Beat until candy begins to thicken.
Add nuts and pour into greased, shallow pan.
Serves 12.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: While cake is baking, melt butter; add brown sugar, milk, coconut, nuts and vanilla.
When cake is done and still hot, pour over cake and return to broiler to brown for just a minute.

title: scripture cake
directions: Mix and bake until done.
Serve with a little prayer of thanks.

title: quick cheeseburger bake(serves 8 - 10)
directions: Pre heat oven to 400 degrees. Grease a 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish. Brown beef and onion. Drain. Stir in soup, veggies and milk. Stir baking mix and water in baking dish until moistened; spread evenly. Spread beef mixture over batter; sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: my friend shirley's sweet fruit dip
directions: Whip together until smooth.
For flavor variation, try one tablespoon orange juice or a dash of cinnamon.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in four pieces.
Place cut biscuits in bags with 3/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon of cinnamon.
Shake.
Put in Bundt pan.
Bring oleo, 3/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon to a boil and pour over biscuits.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Pieces just pull apart.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes and cut into cubes.
Sprinkle with salt.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, onion, garlic and 1 teaspoon salt.
Fold into potato cubes.
Put into casserole.
Top with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: biscuit tortoni
directions: Stir almonds, almond flavoring and cream into the ice cream. Fill cupcake tins, with liners, with mixture.
Top with crushed macaroon cookies.
Freeze.
Remove 5 minutes before serving.

title: spanish chicken and rice
directions: You will also need 1 Dutch oven-type pot.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Put pork chops n a shallow casserole dish.
Add both cans of soup and rice.
Put in oven and cook at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: oriental luncheon salad
directions: Shred or tear lettuce into large bowl.
Add thinly sliced green onions, also using green parts of the top.
Add shrimp or meat and partly thawed peas.
Just before serving, toss in the noodles and French dressing to taste.

title: chili con carne
directions: In Dutch oven, brown ground beef; drain fat.
Sprinkle meat with chili powder, salt and sugar and mix well.
Add onion, green pepper, tomato sauce, water and bay leaves.
Cover and simmer slowly for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: mild jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients except salt in a large bowl.
Heat milk with salt until hot.
Add jalapenos and onions.
Cover and cook 30 minutes over low heat.
Cool.
Combine eggs and Cheddar cheese.
Blend dry ingredients, liquids, cheese mixture and bacon drippings until smooth.
Pour into a well-greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Melt butter in electric skillet and add potatoes, carrots, onions and weiners.
Saute for a few minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cover then and simmer until potatoes are cooked.

title: hawaiian meatballs and rice(recipe from minute rice box many years ago)
directions: Saute garlic in salad oil.
(I use a nonstick pan, no oil, and add garlic powder to the meatballs.)
Cook meatballs until evenly browned.
Combine cornstarch, sugar, salt, soy sauce, 1 cup water and vinegar and add to meatballs.
Heat and stir until sauce thickens.
Make a well in the center of the mixture and add green pepper and boiling water.
Stir rice into water.
Cover and simmer, approximately 10 minutes.

title: sweet and sour brisket(taste it, it's great!)
directions: Place brisket on onions and garlic.
Mix other ingredients; pour over brisket.
Cover and roast in 350° oven until tender (approximately 4 hours).
Makes 10 to 12 servings.
Thicken gravy with flour and water mixture.

title: ruth griffin's turnips and greens
directions: Wash greens and turnips.
Cut turnips in quarters.
Cook roast in water until done.
Remove roast from pot; add turnips and greens to liquid.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Cook until done.
Add cut up pork in bite size pieces.
Serve with hot cracklin' bread.

title: chocolate crackers
directions: You will also need a nonstick cookie sheet with "sides" lined with parchment paper.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Spread pie filling in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl.
Mix until crunchy.
Spread over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until brown.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: rice supreme
directions: Use fresh or cooked drained fruit.
Mix with rice and sugar. Fold in whipped cream.
Chill.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix together everything except the cashews.
Be sure the peas are still frozen.
Refrigerate for at least 8 hours.
Add the cashews right before you are ready to serve.

title: sugarless bars
directions: Boil dates, raisins, prunes and water 5 minutes. Add butter and cool. Add remaining ingredients to the cooled fruit. Pour into a greased 7 x 11 pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: corn-black bean salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Chill up to 3 days. Yield: 4 cups.

title: jean's crab puffs
directions: Bring the water and margarine to a boil.
Add flour and beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Deep fat fry until golden brown.
Do not double the recipe.

title: breakfast tortillas
directions: Brown sausage in one frypan.
Saute in butter the chopped onions, peppers and mushrooms until tender.
Add meat to the vegetables and stir.
Remove from the heat.
Fry the tortilla shells in oil until it bubbles (about 10 seconds each side). Place fried tortillas on paper towels.

title: instant cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Store in airtight container.
To serve, combine 1/3 cup mix and 3/4 cup hot water in mug.
Stir to dissolve.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute first two ingredients. Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until broccoli is tender.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bread.
Crumble bread into mixture and stir.
If mixture is not soupy, add milk.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes in a Bundt pan.

title: sauerkraut and noodles
directions: Fry (cut up) bacon.
Add onion to grease and fry until translucent.
Add sauerkraut and fry for 1/2 hour.
Add cooked noodles and soup.
Add enough water to keep moist.
Add sausage, cut up and cooked.

title: nancy's fettucini
directions: Mix well together sour cream, mushroom soup, salt and pepper. Melt together the Cheddar, Jack and Mozzarella cheeses.
Add to sour cream and mushroom soup mixture.
Add warm noodles.
Blend together and add Parmesan cheese.
Stir until well mixed.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs until light. Blend in cocoa; stir in flour and nuts.
Bake in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool; cut into 16 squares.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine flour, oats, 1/2 cup light brown sugar and 1/2 cup butter in mixing bowl.
Mix until crumbly, using electric mixer on low speed.
Press into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15
minutes.

title: saltwater taffy
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Stir in next four ingredients.

Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and sugar is completely dissolved. Continue cooking, without stirring, until temperature reaches 260° or until a hard ball is formed in cold water.
Stir in flavoring.
Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Let cool enough to handle.
Grease hands; pull until a satin finish is seen.
Cut in 1-inch pieces.
Wrap in wax paper.

title: sweet potato or pumpkin pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; add sugar, salt, mashed potato or pumpkin, melted butter and flavoring.
Add egg whites with cream of tartar last.
Place in unbaked pie shell and bake at 400° for 5 minutes and at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 1 large pie or 2 small ones.

title: cheese logs
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; roll into a log shape and roll the log into the chili powder.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices and serve with crackers.
Makes a nice appetizer.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning mix until creamy.
Spread 1/2-inch thick in shallow dish.
Sprinkle the lettuce, Cheddar cheese and tomatoes on top.
Top with olive slices and spoonfuls of taco sauce.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: molasses cake
directions: Butter and flour a loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together until light and fluffy the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and molasses.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon, allspice, ground cloves and mace.
Mix together well.
Spoon into pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: plum cake
directions: Stir together the flour and sugar with spoon.
Add Crisco oil, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Stir in plums and eggs.
Mix well, then add chopped nuts.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: asparagus roll-up
directions: Roll bread flat with rolling pin.
Spread some mayonnaise on bread.
Place 1 spear of asparagus across the bread.
Roll bread up and dip in margarine, then roll in Parmesan cheese.
Cut rolled up bread into thirds.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
May be frozen without baking.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Boil noodles to desired doneness and drain.
While noodles are boiling, fry hamburger, onions, salt and pepper.
When cooked through, drain grease.
In a saucepan bring water to a boil; add bouillon and cornstarch.
Continue to boil and stir until it becomes a gravy like texture.
Add sour cream and mix well.
Mix hamburger, noodles and gravy mixture all together.

title: barbecue chicken(diet)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken.
Pour over chicken.
Let stand 1 hour.
Bake in covered dish at 350° for 40 minutes. Uncover and bake 20 minutes more.

title: chocolate chipper's cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Dissolve baking soda in warm water and add to mixture; add salt and flour a little at a time.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes. Makes 12 dozen.

title: cheese logs
directions: Cut crusts off each slice of bread and roll out flat with rolling pin.
Blend cream cheese, egg yolks and 1/3 cup sugar to consistency of mayonnaise.
Spread cream cheese mixture on bread slice and roll up, jelly roll fashion.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: bible cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Beat in the 3 Jeremiah, one at a time.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Beat well.
Sift together Kinds, 2 Chronicles, Leviticus and Amos.
Add to Jeremiah mixture.
Add Judges last.
Bake at 325° for about 90 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil hen until tender and cut into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients except spaghetti.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth until tender, then combine with other ingredients.
Cook on low heat until cheese melts or bake in casserole dish for 35 minutes at 325°.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Wash and cut celery into bite size pieces. Important: Refrigerate overnight in water with lid.

title: sweet apple face snack
directions: Wash apple.
Spread peanut butter all over apple.
Decorate with mini marshmallows and chocolate chips for eyes and eye brows. Use licorice for hair.
Have fun creating your own sweet apple face!

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Simmer soup meat in water for 2 hours.
Add all, except rice. Simmer 1 hour; add rice.
Cook 30 minutes longer.

title: san francisco chicken
directions: Cut up green onions and mix into softened cream cheese.
Put 1/8 of cream cheese mixture on each chicken breast half.
Roll up and wrap with slice of bacon to each half.
Bake at 350° to 375° until bacon is crisp.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Saute onions in pan with oil.
Add celery and broccoli with water.
Steam for 10 to 20 minutes.
Add soup, milk, rice and Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 350°
for 1/2 hour.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Core and wash peppers.
Set aside.
Cut turkey in bite-size pieces.
Saute onion and turkey.
Add tomatoes and simmer two minutes.
Remove from heat and add rice.
Stuff each pepper. Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes until almost done.
Top with cheese and bake until cheese is melted.

title: spaghetti sauce(for 50 people)
directions: Brown and drain ground chuck and sausage. Put browned meat in a large saucepan and add spaghetti sauce dry mix. Add tomatoes. Add tomato paste or tomato sauce and catsup.
I add oregano and garlic salt until it tastes like I want it to.

title: glazed coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, pudding mix, oil and water in mixer bowl.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating for 6 to 8 minutes. Beat in 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Spoon 1/3 of the batter into greased and floured Bundt pan. Mix sugar, cinnamon and pecans in small bowl.
Layer pecan mixture and remaining batter, 1/2 at a time, in
prepared pan.
Bake for 45 minutes. Cool on rack for 8 minutes.
Invert on serving plate. Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl and mix well. Spoon over warm coffee cake.
Serves 12.

title: no fry tacos
directions: Brown beef and turkey in nonstick skillet.
Drain and rinse meat.
Return meat to skillet and add all remaining ingredients except tortilla shells.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes. Meanwhile, wrap tortillas tightly in foil and warm in a 250° oven. Let your family roll their own tacos.
Garnish with shredded lettuce, tomatoes, green onions, shredded zucchini and grated nonfat cheese.

title: chicken taco soup
directions: Season chicken to taste and broil in oven until done.
Remove meat; cool and shred with a fork.
(Chicken may be covered with water and boiled on stove until done if preferred.
Remove from water; cool and shred with a fork.)
In a large skillet, combine shredded chicken, olive oil, taco seasoning, onions, and garlic. Cook until onions are clear.
While cooking chicken mixture, combine all the remaining ingredients in a pot and heat.
When skillet mixture is done, add to the pot and heat thoroughly.
Serve soup with cheese and chips or corn bread.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Combine Egg Beaters, flour, onion and pepper; set aside.
Pat shredded potatoes dry with a paper towel.
Stir into Egg Beaters mixture.
In a nonstick skillet that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray, pour 1 1/2 tablespoons of liquid Butter Buds.
For each pancake, spoon 1/3 cup potato mixture into skillet, spreading to a 4-inch circle.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes, turning once to brown on both sides.
Remove and keep warm.
Use remaining liquid Butter Buds as needed.
Serve with applesauce, if desired.
Yields 12 pancakes.

title: roll-up appetizer(pinwheels)
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spread on tortillas with a knife.
Roll up tightly.
Chill 2 hours.
Cut rolls into 1-inch slices.
Arrange on serving dish.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: raspberry jell-o salad
directions: Mix Jell-o first with hot water to dissolve and then in cold water.
Stir in orange juice and applesauce.
Let set.
This makes an easy, delicious accompaniment for ham, pork chops or roast.

title: double-chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 300°.
In a double boiler, melt the semi-sweet chocolate over hot, not simmering, water.
Set aside to cool to room temperature.
In a small bowl, whisk together the flour, baking soda and salt.
In a medium bowl, whisk together the brown and granulated sugars, then add the butter and beat until well combined.
Add the peanut butter; beat until smooth.
Add the eggs and vanilla; beat until just combined.
Add the flour mixture and the milk chocolate chips; beat until no streaks of flour are visible.
Pour in the melted chocolate; mix partially with a wooden spoon until marbled.
Drop the dough in 3 tablespoon mounds, 2 inches apart, on an ungreased baking sheet.
Top with 1 whole peanut.
Bake for 23 minutes, or until just set but still soft.
Cool on the cookie sheet for 30 seconds, then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Combine first six ingredients and spoon into crust.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°F.

title: marinade from gary's grill
directions: Mix together and pour over meat (any with exception of fish). Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Place on grill and watch closely, turning often.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cut up cooled, cooked chicken.
Cook spaghetti in broth and drain.
Saute onion and celery.
Combine all the ingredients in a large casserole dish.
You may add a can of English peas, if you wish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves about 12.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine sugar, oil and eggs. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Add dry ingredients and beat at low speed for 1 minute.
Stir in grated carrots and nuts. Spread in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake about 1 hour or until cake tests done with a toothpick.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: beat and eat frosting
directions: Mix egg white, sugar, cream of tartar and vanilla in a deep bowl; add boiling water.
Beat until peaks form.
This frosts a 2 layer cake.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Layer egg noodles, chicken and bell pepper in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over top. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: five can casserole
directions: Mix first 4 cans together and put in casserole pan. Top with noodles.
Heat until bubbly and serve.

title: chicken n biscuit casserole
directions: In saucepan combine soup, flour, onion and milk.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Blend cheese until melted, stir in peas, chicken and salt and pepper.
Heat through.
Place in 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Place biscuits around edge of dish. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, until biscuits are done.

title: no flour peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let sit 5 minutes.
Shape into 30 balls.
Crisscross with fork.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10-12 minutes.

title: drop dumplings with eggs
directions: Put butter into dry flour.
Add salt, baking powder and egg, well beaten.
Stir all together with a fork and add enough milk to the mixture will drop from wet tablespoon.

title: hunter spuds
directions: Slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Chop onion.
Place in large pot and fill with water to cover.
Cook until tender.
Dice bacon and fry until desired doneness.
Mix bacon and grease into pot with potato onion mixture.
Mix lightly so potatoes will not mush. Serve with catsup.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together, one at a time.
This will become very stiff as you get it mixed together.
Then put it into a loaf pan and pack it down and refrigerate overnight.

title: daddy's doo
directions: Heat
bacon
grease.
Add
all ingredients and anything else you
might find in refrigerator or cabinet and fry until golden brown.

title: fettucini
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Begin to boil water for noodles and cook according to box instructions.
With stove on low-medium, heat milk slowly.
When the milk is hot, break up the cream cheese and add to the pot.
After cream cheese melts, add the Parmesan cheese.
After that cheese melts and when noodles are almost ready, put vegetables into sauce and cover the pot until the veggies are as tender as you like.
Serves 3 to 4 (unless one of those people is a teenager).

title: marathon key lime pie
directions: To beaten egg yolks, add condensed milk, lime juice and Cool Whip.
Blend well.
Pour into prepared pie shell.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Garnish with additional Cool Whip if desired.

title: dumplings ahead of time
directions: Mix chicken broth with eggs.
Add enough flour to make dough that will roll out like biscuits.
Roll out to your liking.
Cut in 2 inch wide strips.
Layer between wax paper and freeze until ready to use.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Slice peaches and place in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add sugar, then sprinkle Jell-O on top of peaches.
Sprinkle the cake mix on top of Jell-O, then drizzle margarine over cake mix. Pour water over top and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fudge cake
directions: Combine chocolate, 1/2 cup milk, well-beaten egg and 2/3 cup sugar in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Thoroughly cream shortening, 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Beat in 2 eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, soda and salt together; add to creamed ingredients alternately with 2/3 cup milk.
Blend in chocolate mixture and pour into two 9-inch pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When cool, frost with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: five soup mix-up
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add soups and mix well.
Fold in 2/3 of chow mein noodles.
Place in large casserole.
Top with remaining noodles.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: golden chicken casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine soup, sour cream, 1/2 cup of milk, and all of the chicken, veggies, salt and pepper. Mix well and pour into a greased or sprayed 9x13 pan. In a separate bowl, combine Bisquick, cornmeal, egg and remaining 3/4 cup of milk. Mix well and spread over the chicken mixture. Sprinkle with cheese and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375 degrees. May need to add a little more time, if the veggies are frozen. Serves: 6.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: *I use unsweetened frozen ones (6 ounces).
You can also use a box of lightly sweetened raspberries, thaw them.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Moisten with Miracle Whip salad dressing.

title: hot mustard
directions: In a small bowl, stir vinegar slowly into dry mustard until smooth. Cover and let stand 6 hours or overnight
at room temperature.
Pour into saucepan with sugar and egg yolk and cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cover and refrigerate up to 2 weeks.

title: my homemade fudge
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar and blend well, then add milk and cream. Cook over low heat until mixture forms a soft ball when dropped in water.
Remove from heat and set in a pan of cold water.
Beat candy while adding rest of ingredients.
Candy will loses its luster and get dull when it is ready to pour on wax paper or buttered dish.
Cool and cut into desired squares.

title: catherine's fresh corn
directions: Cut corn off cob; scrape cob for juice.
Bring milk and butter to a boil.
Add all ingredients in a heavy 2-quart pot.
Cut heat down to medium-low.
Cook, uncovered, for 45 minutes, stirring often.
Don't allow to stick and burn.
Ready to serve.

title: great tuna salad
directions: Open the tuna cans but do not remove lids.
Use lids to squeeze off excess oil.
Do not squeeze tuna dry.
Remove tuna from can.
Place in medium bowl.
Crumble with a fork.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot pineapple. Let cool until it begins to thicken. Add buttermilk; fold in Cool Whip and nuts. Pour into large 8 x 13-inch pan. Let set in refrigerator until firm. Cut into squares and serve.

title: crispies
directions: Cream sugars, margarine and oil.
Stir in flour, soda, etc., then stir in oatmeal, coconut, etc.
Chill in fridge.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Help with fingers if crumbly.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Good to eat from freezer, too!

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Put sliced cucumbers in lime water and let stand 24 hours. Drain.
Soak 4 hours in cold water, changing water very hour. Bring vinegar to a boil. Add sugar and spices.
Pour over cucumbers and let stand overnight.
Next morning, bring to a boil and boil slowly for 1 hour.
Pack into jars and pour syrup over pickles and seal.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil except corn and soda; cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Pour over popped corn in large pan or roaster.
Stir well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Cool.
Break apart.
Salted peanuts may be added. Store in airtight container.
Freezes well.

title: hominy soup
directions: Saute
stew
meat
in oil until
lightly
browned.
Mix together the beans, hominy and tomatoes, using
all
liquid on canned vegetables.* Mix meat and vegetables
together.
Simmer for 3 hours (a crock-pot is great or until meat is cooked).

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour once; measure.
Add baking powder, salt and nutmeg and sift again.
Cream shortening.
Add sugar, gradually creaming until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla. Add flour, a small amount at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Chill until firm enough to roll.

title: quick sour cream pound cake
directions: To cake mix, add eggs, one at a time, with oil, water, sugar and sour cream.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 375° for approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spread green beans in casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken (cut in small pieces) on top.
Mix soups (undiluted) and sour cream together.
(I usually add some onion flakes and grated cheese to the soup mixture.)
Spread on casserole.
Mix stuffing according to package directions; cover chicken.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: fiesta rice
directions: Brown hamburg, onion and pepper. Add other ingredients with juice in the cans. Bring to a boil. Cover with rice 1 to 2 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain off grease.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.

title: rabbit-cider casserole
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter.
Cook rabbit or chicken pieces until browned on all sides.
Transfer meat to a 3-quart casserole dish, reserving drippings in skillet.
Add the onion, carrot and walnuts to drippings.
Cook until vegetables are tender, but not brown.
Stir in mushrooms.
Spoon vegetables and nuts over meat in the casserole dish, reserving drippings in skillet.
Blend flour, salt and pepper into drippings.
Add apple juice, all at once.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until meat is done. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: coconut crunch
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar; beat until stiff (until peaks form).
Mix in nuts, coconut and wafer crumbs; mix well.
Pour into well-greased pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
When cool, top with sliced bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip; garnish with nuts.

title: vegetarian cabbage rolls
directions: Core and steam cabbage.
Saute onion in butter, add parsley, garlic and mixed Nature's Burger.
Add cooked brown rice and mix well.
Remove from saute pan.
Drain steamed cabbage and cool. Mix tomato sauce, tomatoes, water, brown sugar, salt and pepper, if desired.
Make cabbage rolls with steamed cabbage, rice and burger mix.
Cut remaining cabbage up and place in bottom of pot with a little of tomato sauce mix to moisten.
Layer cabbage rolls with tomato mix, sauerkraut and raisins until finished.
Cook in large pot until well cooked, about 45 minutes.

title: seven layer blueberry crunch
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Spread undrained pineapple over bottom of pan. Add layer of blueberries and 3/4 cup of sugar. Sprinkle cake mix on top of fruit. Pour melted butter over cake mix. Top with nuts (pecans are good). Sprinkle 1/4 cup of sugar over nuts. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes. Enjoy.

title: angel salad
directions: Mix whole egg, milk and dry mustard.
Heat to boiling, then cool.
Whip the cream; add cooled mixture and marshmallows, then drained fruit and nuts.
Make night before serving.

title: oven fried chicken with biscuits
directions: Set oven to 425°.
Melt shortening and butter in oven in oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2.
Blend 1/2 cup Bisquick, salt, paprika and pepper.
Coat chicken.
Place chicken, skin side down, in shortening mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 35 minutes.
Insert a clove in each peach.
Stir 2 cups Bisquick and water to soft dough. Gently smooth dough into a ball on floured board.
Knead 5 times. Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch cutter.
Turn chicken, pushing pieces to one side.
Spoon excess fat from pan.
Place biscuits in a single layer next to chicken.
Place peaches on top of chicken.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream cheese must be at room temperature.
Mix all well; shape into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Melt margarine and chocolate and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.

title: buttermilk dressing
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together mayonnaise, sour cream with chives, buttermilk, tomato juice, Parmesan cheese, dry mustard, paprika, celery seed, garlic powder, 1/8 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Store in a tightly covered jar in the fridge.

title: coconut pie
directions: Add coconut to milk while mixing other ingredients.
Cream sugar, margarine and flour; add eggs and vanilla.
Then add coconut and milk.
Mix well and bake in a pie crust at 350° until set (30 minutes or longer).

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: In a bowl, put cottage cheese and then pour dry jello mix right from the box over.
Mix well.
Drain pineapple, then add pineapple to mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: kielbasa casserole
directions: Fry bacon crisp; drain on paper towel.
Add marjoram to bacon drippings.
Saute carrots, potatoes and broccoli in bacon drippings until tender.
Add water and kielbasa; cover and cook 10 minutes.
Top with crushed bacon pieces.

title: apple butter bread
directions: Combine pancake mix, spice, brown sugar and orange rind.
Add beaten egg, milk and apple butter.
Bake in a greased 1 quart mold or a greased and floured loaf pan in 350° oven, 30 minutes for mold and 40 minutes for loaf.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray cookie sheet with cooking spray. In a big bowl, cream margarine and sugars.
Add egg.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat.

title: italian cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and add chocolate chips, nuts or fruit.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: olive puffs
directions: Cream butter and cheese. Work in flour and paprika with hands. Chill about 15-30 minutes. Mold about 1/2 tsp. of dough around olive. Chill overnight. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes. To freeze: cool puffs and pack in airtight container. To serve, thaw and place on serving dish.

title: cottage pie
directions: Cook carrots first, then brown beef and onions.
Add carrots, salt, pepper, cinnamon, herbs and parsley.
Stir in flour; add beef stock and tomato puree.
Transfer to casserole dish.
Boil potatoes, mash; cook leeks in butter and add to potatoes.
Spread potato mixture over meat mixture and bake for 25 minutes at 400°. Serves 4.

title: pineapple-cottage cheese salad
directions: Prepare jello using reserved pineapple juice to which water has been added to make 4 cups.
Add cottage cheese, salad dressing, pineapple and carrots to almost set jello.
Chill and serve.

title: fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken thoroughly.
Salt chicken as usual.
Fill the Fry Daddy with oil up to line.
Mix egg and milk together.
Beat well. Add pepper to flour.
Dip your chicken in the milk mixture and roll into flour.
Cook for 20 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Drain pineapple.
Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Cover and blend for 30 seconds.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight. Serve with fresh fruit.

title: cheese patties
directions: Mix flour, oleo and seasoning.
Add Rice Krispies and mix thoroughly.
Make small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Mash down with fork dipped in cold water.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: hamburg corn potatoes(serves 8)
directions: Cook potatoes, mash with butter and a little milk, salt and pepper.
Fry hamburger with salt, pepper and garlic powder; drain off fat.
Mix corn together well.
Layer a large casserole with potato, hamburger and corn, in that order until you end up at top with potatoes.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Broil for about 5 minutes, until brown.
Remove from oven, let stand for 15 to 20 minutes.
Good eating!

title: strawberry-grapefruit drink
directions: Break up strawberries.
Place them and 1 cup of grapefruit juice in a blender.
Cover and blend on high speed about 30 seconds or until smooth.
Add remaining grapefruit juice.
Cover and blend until mixed.
Serve over ice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: regina's chicken cordon bleu
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pound out chicken; lay flat and put a slice of ham on top, then put a slice of cheese on top.
Roll the chicken over tight so that the ham and cheese are inside.
Stick a toothpick through to hold.
Wet with milk or water, then roll in breader and fry until golden brown.
Place in browning pan and bake for 25 minutes.
Then pour can of soup over and bake for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: coffee chiffon
directions: In a medium saucepan, beat the milk and egg yolks.
Add sweetener, coffee powder, salt and softened gelatin.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and gelatin is dissolved.
Chill until partially set.

title: soft raisin cookies
directions: Combine raisins and water; bring to a boil.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool (do not drain).
Cream butter; add sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add gradually to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Drop onto cookie sheet and bake at 350°.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix for 2 minutes at low speed with mixer; set bowl aside.
In large bowl, place 7 cups flour, sugar and water; mix for 3 minutes.
Add yeast mixture to flour mixture; mix at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Let rise for 2 to 3 hours.

title: asparagus with orange butter sauce
directions: Combine butter, orange rind and juice in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until mixture is reduced by half and slightly thickened.
Set aside but keep warm.
Cook asparagus. Arrange in a serving dish.
Pour sauce over asparagus.
Garnish with orange slices.
Serves 6.

title: barbecued beef roast
directions: If
roast
is tied, remove string and flatten.	In bowl slightly
larger than the meat, mash garlic with salt, pepper, chili
powder
and	thyme.	Gradually
beat
in
oil;
add the vinegar and
stir well.
Add meat to the marinade.	Pierce all over
with	long
fork
so that seasoning will penetrate.
Let stand
in
refrigerator several hours or several days, turning periodically.

title: mexican mess-up
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Cook rice and broccoli.
In a saucepan, mix and heat 2 cans of soup and garlic.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients. Place in two loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: famous rotel cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese spread in a double boiler. Stir in tomatoes. Serve warm with tortilla chips, crackers or assorted raw vegetables.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups dip.

title: party cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease pan(s) with shortening and lightly flour.
If making cupcakes, grease and flour muffin pan or line with paper baking cups.

title: easy lemon pound cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix cake mix and pudding.
Add eggs, oil, water and butter.
Pour butter into greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: In a big bowl, mix butter, peanut butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and then blend in bowl with wet ingredients.
Shape in small balls (about 1-inch size). Roll balls in granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with fork.
Do not put on bottom rack in oven.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool slightly on a rack. Makes 8 dozen cookies.

title: sopaipillas(deep fat fried bread)
directions: Combine dry ingredients and cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add to scalded milk, cooled to room temperature.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients.
Add liquid to dry ingredients and work into dough.
Knead dough 15 to 20 times and set aside for approximately 10 minutes.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness or slightly thinner, then cut into squares or triangles and fry in a melted shortening at 420°.
Fry only a few at a time so fat stays hot.
If the fat is hot, the sopaipillas will puff up and become hollow shortly after adding to fat.
Drain sopaipillas on absorbent towels and serve as a bread with any New Mexican meal. They are especially good served with honey.

title: macaroni and cheese without cheese(non-dairy)
directions: Blend water, cashews and salt in blender.
Add oil slowly, then add lemon juice, pimentos, onion salt or powder, garlic powder and food yeast.
Whiz together, mix with macaroni and cook for 1/2 hour or until done in a moderate oven.
This sauce will keep in refrigerator for 1 to 2 weeks.

title: pot roast dinner
directions: Put meat in pan and add the soups.
Cover and bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Add peeled carrots and potatoes; cover and continue to bake 1 hour or until vegetables are cooked through.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts and cut into bite size pieces.
Melt margarine and mix with dressing mix.
Dilute soup with broth. Layer in baking dish in this order:
Layer of crumbs, layer of chicken.
Pour part of broth mixture and layer again.
Be sure to have enough crumb mixture to cover top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mandarin orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add plain gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add sherbet and syrup from oranges.
Stir until sherbet is dissolved.
Chill until partially thickened.
Fold in oranges and pour into mold.
Refrigerate until solid.

title: 4 layer delight
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Spread over cheese mixture, then spread rest of Cool Whip over pudding layer.
Top with nuts.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan. Dump undrained pineapple into pan.
Spread evenly. Dump in pie filling and spread into an even layer.
Dump dry cake mix onto cherry layer; spread evenly. Sprinkle pecans over cake mix.
Put oleo evenly over top. Bake for 45 to 55 minutes.
Serve warm or cool with ice cream, if desired.

title: fish fillet with peppers
directions: Season fish with salt and pepper and dip in flour.
Fry in oil until golden.
Add chopped onion and thin strips of pepper
and fry until soft.
Add skinned and chopped tomatoes.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Thicken with remaining flour and serve.

title: marinated cucumber salad
directions: One day head:
With tines of fork, score cucumbers lengthwise, then cut crosswise into thin slices.
Slice onions thinly and separate into rings.
In large bowl (do not use aluminum bowl), combine water, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Whisk until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in cucumbers and onion rings.
Cover and marinate salad in refrigerator for at least 5 hours.
Makes 8 servings.
I place a breakfast plate on top of vegetables to keep them under the marinade.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Mix together peppers, sugar and vinegar in large pan.
Heat to boiling and boil for 1 minute.
Cool 5 minutes.
Add pectin and a few drops food coloring.
Pour into Mason jars or baby food jars and seal with paraffin.
Recipe makes 7 cups.
To serve:
Pour over crackers spread with cream cheese.

title: favorite buns
directions: Dissolve 2/3 of cake of yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
In a large bowl, mix the sugar, shortening, salt, eggs and hot water. Cool until lukewarm.
Add yeast and flour; stir until dough leaves sides of bowl.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onions and carrots in boiling salted water. Drain. Add remaining ingredients.
Melt butter and mix well with dressing mix.
Grease pan and spread with layer of dressing mix on bottom.
Pour in squash mixture and cover with remainder of dressing mix.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Add margarine and sugar; add syrup.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat thoroughly.
Add vanilla and pecan halves.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 300° for 50 minutes or until set.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Put pineapple with juice and Jell-O in saucepan.
Heat and stir until Jell-O is dissolved.
Cool.
Stir in buttermilk, whipped topping and nuts. Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate until set.

title: date sponge squares
directions: Mix flour,
baking powder, soda and salt and set aside. Cream butter
and
sugar.
Add
egg and mix well; add vanilla. Pour boiling
water
over
dates
and
cool.
Mix walnuts with flour. Mix
date
mixture alternately with nuts to butter and sugar mixture.
Bake
in	greased 9 x 12-inch pan for 30 to 40 minutes in	350°
oven.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine vegetables and olives in large bowl.

title: make-ahead brunch bake(refrigerate overnight; bake next day)
directions: Crumble sausage into large skillet.
Cook over medium-high heat until browned; drain well.
Stir in eggs, cream, salt, mustard, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions; mix well. Pour into a greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate, covered, 8 hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Wash zucchini; trim ends, then parboil whole in boiling salted water for about 15 minutes.
Drain.
When cool enough to handle, cut lengthwise in halves.
