With a teaspoon, carefully scoop out pulp, leaving a thin wall of the squash.
Arrange shells in a greased shallow baking dish.
Mash the scooped out pulp; add all the remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle zucchini shells with salt and pepper, then fill with pulp mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers. Pour melted margarine over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown and drain hamburger.
Bring a large pan of water to boil.
Boil lasagna strips until tender (approximately 15 minutes).
Mix Prego with hamburger and let sit. Drain water from lasagna.
Using a regular cake pan (glass or metal) lightly cover bottom of pan with hamburger and Prego mix. Lay 3 strips side by side over mixture.
Cover with mixture.
Add 1 cup of each cheese.
Layer with strips.
Add mixture; top with cheese again and then strips.
Use remaining mixture (hamburger and Prego) and top with remaining cheeses.
Cover pan loosely with aluminum foil.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake an additional 30 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes for better consistency.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar and Crisco.
Mix as usual for cake.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine warm water, dry yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in 1-quart jar. Let set until bubbly and jar is full. Scald milk.
Add shortening and let melt. Cool.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon and remove from pan, reserving drippings. Stir in remaining ingredients. Continue stirring until thickened. Use for spinach salad with Hot Bacon Dressing or German potato salad.

title: selah's no guilt banana split
directions: Dissolve Jell-O completely in boiling water.
Stir in cold water.
Pour into square 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm, about 4 hours.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Divide into 4 dessert dishes.
Half and split bananas just before serving.
Place 2 pieces on each dish.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with walnuts.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown sausage of your choice. Mix eggs, mustard, pepper, milk and cheese. Tear up bread into small pieces and put into liquid mixture. Add sausage. Mix well. This recipe can be made the night before or same day. You can also add onions, peppers, mushrooms, etc. Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: german crushed banana cake
directions: With an electric mixer, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, bananas and vanilla.
In a cup, stir baking soda into sour milk until dissolved.
Add to butter mixture.
Stir or sift together flour and cinnamon; add to butter mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Stir nuts into batter, then fold in egg whites.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch round cake pans. Bake in a preheated 350° oven until done, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool in pans 5 minutes, then turn out onto a wire rack.

title: stovetop roast beef & gravy
directions: Rinse off roast and coat with flour.
Place roast and onion in large pot.
Brown on all sides in oil.
Remove excess oil from pot, cover roast with water.

title: iced pecan halves
directions: Grease a foil-lined baking sheet.
Melt butter in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat.
Stir in pecans and sugar.
Cook 7 to 9 minutes, stirring constantly, until sugar is syrupy and golden brown and nuts are toasted.
(Candy thermometer will register 300°).
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Immediately spread candy mixture in a thin layer on prepared baking sheet.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cool completely, then break into small nut clusters.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat all ingredients real good.
Pour in loaf pans.
Cover with 8 ounces tomato sauce if you like the flavor.
Cover with 3 strips of bacon.
Keeps top soft.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake 1 hour.

title: bob-andy pie
directions: Combine sifted flour, salt and sugar in bowl.
Cream with margarine.
Add eggs and beat mixture until smooth.
Stir in milks and vanilla.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until firm, approximately 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream
sugar
and
lard.
Add beaten eggs and pineapple. Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Add vanilla.
Drop from fork on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Cook sausage in skillet on stove, stirring until well done. Saute onion.
Drain oil from cooked sausage, add onion.
Beat eggs, milk and Bisquick; set aside.
Put a layer of sausage, then a layer of cheese until all is used.
Pour milk and egg mixture over sausage and cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: chocolate chip cookie cake
directions: Slice 1 roll of cookies on bottom of 9 x 13-inch buttered pan and mash together to form crust.
Mix eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar together and pour over crust.
Sprinkle brown sugar, coconut and nuts over this.
Slice the other roll of cookies and cover the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cover top if it begins to get too brown.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar,
baking powder, soda and salt.
Beat eggs; add sour milk
and
shortening.
Mix in apples, nuts and vanilla. Bake in loaf pan at 350° for one hour.

title: glenn's impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender and pour into a pie pan. Cook for about 35 minutes in a 400° oven.
It makes its own crust while baking.

title: canned salmon
directions: Clean and cut in chunks the salmon and pack in a quart jar. Add rest of the ingredients.
Cook at 10 pounds of pressure for 90 minutes in a pressure cooker.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
Beat eggs with sugar for 2 minutes. Gradually add oil and beat for 2 minutes.
Add extract. Alternately fold in flour mixture and zucchini until moist.
Stir in pecans and raisins.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Wash chicken, pat dry and split chicken breasts in half.
Beat eggs with 1/2 cup milk.
Dip chicken into mix and then into bread crumbs, coating well.
Put breasts in well-buttered baking dish with a pat of butter under each one.
Sprinkle each breast with garlic and onion powders.
Cover well with Mozzarella, then salami, then pepper.
Combine remaining milk with rest of beaten milk and eggs.
Add 3/4 cup bread crumbs and Parmesan to create thick batter.
Mix well and pour over each breast.
Top each with a pat of butter.
Bake at 400° to 450° until golden brown (20 to 25 minutes).
Yields 4 servings.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate and peanut butter morsels in a microwave, a few at a time until all are well mixed.
Stir in peanuts.
Place spoonfuls at a time on wax paper.
Cool until hard.

title: chocolate pistachio cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients; stir in the sour cream, oil and creme de menthe.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat for four minutes. Turn half the batter into a greased floured tube or Bundt pan. Grate the chocolate bar on half the batter.
Pour remaining batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Place chicken in shallow casserole dish.
Mix sour cream and soup; pour over chicken.
Mix crumbs and poppy seed with melted butter (mix with mixer).
Cover chicken with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream.
Mix in rest of ingredients. Spread on tortillas and roll up.
Chill.
Slice and serve with picante sauce.

title: honey curried chicken
directions: Melt butter in small pan; add wine, honey, mustard, salt and curry powder and mix well.
Pour sauce over chicken in shallow baking dish.
Bake covered at 375° for 45 minutes, then uncover and bake another 45 minutes.
Serve with rice and condiments such as chutney and peanuts.

title: cucumber party sandwiches
directions: In a bowl, combine cream cheese, dressing mix and mayonnaise. Allow to stand at least 30 minutes.
Spread on rye bread.
Top with a slice of cucumber and sprig of dill.
Cover.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Yields 30 appetizers.

title: rigatoni
directions: Add bell pepper and onion to meat and cook until meat is done. Mix all ingredients, using only half of the cheese, in a large baking dish. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake at 350° until mixture is bubbly and lightly browned on top.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes slightly.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4
cup warm water.
Mix all dry ingredients and sift.
Cut in Crisco.
Add yeast and buttermilk. Mix well.
Place in refrigerator.
To cook, remove amount of dough needed and knead lightly on wax paper with flour.
Cut out with biscuit cutter.
Put on a greased cookie sheet.
Let rise for 1 hour and bake at 400° until done.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Large bowl, use electric mixer.
Beat butter, 1 1/3 cups sugar until creamy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
In other bowl, stir together flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Gradually add to butter mix, blend thoroughly.
Small bowl combine cinnamon and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Roll dough into balls, then roll in cinnamon-sugar mix to coat.
Place at least 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: ham and cheddar pie
directions: Combine Bisquick, milk, salt, pepper and eggs.
Mix with fork (mixture will be lumpy).
Add ham, green pepper and onions.
Heat margarine in 10-inch skillet until melted and bubbly.
Slowly add ham mixture into skillet.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat until almost set (10 to 12 minutes).
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and cook until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: harvest cake
directions: Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
A lemon icing is good. This is an excellent cake to freeze.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add salt, flour and milk gradually.
Mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate overnight.
Beat one egg white until stiff.
Divide dough into 4 rolls; roll out 1/4 dough. Brush with 1/4 egg whites.
Sprinkle with plenty of sugar; pat sugar well.
Then sprinkle with nuts.
If dough is sticky, add a little flour while rolling.
Cut into narrow strips diagonally, scoop up sticks with spatula and place on cookie sheet.
Let stand for 10 minutes before baking.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: tomato relish
directions: Combine vegetables and salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain, do not press vegetables.
Place in large kettle; add sugars, pepper, vinegar and spices tied in cheesecloth.
Bring to a boil, reduce and simmer uncovered 15 minutes.
Ladle into jars.
Process in boiling water 10 minutes.

title: heavenly rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Stir well. Chill and serve.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Wash and remove seeds from peppers.
Put in blender until chopped.
Drain.
Mix vinegar and sugar with pepper pulp and bring to a rolling boil.
Add Certo and food coloring and bring to another boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Skim and pour into sterilized jars. Seal with paraffin.
Good with cornbread.
Makes 4 to 5 pints.

title: prison dip
directions: Smear cream cheese in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour 2 jars of salsa over cream cheese.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top of salsa.
Layer sausage, then pepperoni next.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips and fried Polish sausage strips.
Delicious.

title: crispy cheese balls
directions: Mix in order and form into tiny balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 100 bite-size pieces.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Put yolks
of
eggs, sugar, grated lemon rind and juice in a saucepan.
Let
come
to
a boil, stirring all the time. Beat egg whites
separately	and
fold
into the hot mixture. Having removed the mixture from stove, whip the cream and fold into mixture.
Pour into dish or tray that has been lined with graham or	vanilla wafer cracker crumbs.
Roll crumbs finely. Fill with lemon mixture, cover with more crumbs and freeze.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake partially covered in a 2 1/2-quart casserole at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ma jus' pound cake(this is a real old recipe)
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and flavor to taste.
Bake on low to medium heat until a straw comes out clean.

title: curry vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients together; chill for several hours before serving.
Delicious with raw vegetables.

title: hot apple cider punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan and simmer for 20 minutes. Serves 20 to 25.

title: chili
directions: Simmer tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, bouillon, chili powder, kidney beans and Tabasco sauce in large pot for 1 hour.

title: fried pie dough
directions: Cut together with knife until crumbly and add ice water to mix.
Handle as little as possible.
Makes 18 to 20 balls.
Roll out to size of saucer, then put filling in between and go around edge with water on fingertips, then fold and crimp with fork. Have grease in skillet hot.
Fry until browned.
Drizzle with powdered sugar, water and vanilla, mixed together as soon as done.

title: bible cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and honey.
Blend well.
Mix fruit and nuts with 1 tablespoon of flour.
Add dry ingredients (flour, salt, baking powder and spices) and milk, blend well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix. Add fruit and nut mixture and mix well.
Fold in beaten egg whites gradually.
Bake at 350° in a greased loaf pan for 1 hour.
Let cool before removing from pan.
Have fun and God bless you.

title: almond cheese fruit dip
directions: Blend together and chill. Makes 1/2 cups.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 50 minutes at 375°.

title: meaty cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage in a large skillet, stirring until it crumbles; drain and return to skillet. Add remaining ingredients and cook over low heat, stirring constantly until cheese melts. Serve warm with corn chips.

title: "no cook" peanut butter kisses
directions: Mix syrup and peanut butter in small bowl.
Stir in gradually dry milk and powdered sugar.
Shape into a roll about 3/4-inch in diameter.
Roll may be decorated with chopped nuts.
Chill.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
(I roll mine in powdered sugar.
It helps to keep them from sticking together when you cut it.)

title: enchilada's
directions: Brown hamburg.
Fry tortillas in hot oil by flipping over after 3 seconds (or when small bubbles form in the tortilla).
Mix hamburg, onion, beans and a small amount of cheese together in a bowl.
Spread a large spoon 1 to 2 tablespoons of mixture on tortilla and roll up.
Place in baking dish until full.
In same bowl, mix the 3 sauces together, then pour over enchiladas. Spread evenly, then sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Cream oleo, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add other ingredients. Take 1/2 batter and spread on greased cookie sheet.
If batter is too stiff, add a little water to thin.
Spread cherry pie filling (or any other flavor) over batter.
Spread remaining batter over cherry filling and sprinkle nuts over top.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Spoon onto cookie sheet by teaspoonful.
Flatten out.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine
bananas,
oil,
sugar, milk, vanilla and eggs; mix. Combine
flour,
soda
and salt.
Add to banana mixture; add nuts. Bake
in
greased	loaf pan for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hot bean and cheese dip
directions: In saucepan, combine first 5 ingredients and 1/4 cup water. Heat slowly, stirring constantly, until heated through.
Transfer to fondue pot or small chafing dish.
Keep warm over fondue or chafing dish burner.
Add water to thin, as necessary.
Serve with chips.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: icebox sandwiches
directions: Mix pudding and milk according to package directions. Refrigerate until set.
Fold in whipped topping and chocolate chips.
Place 24 graham crackers on a baking sheet!
Top each with about 3 tablespoons filling.
Place another graham cracker on top. Freeze for 1 hour or until firm.
Wrap individually in plastic wrap and freeze.
Serve frozen.
Children love them.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: taco stew
directions: Brown meat.
Mix meat and all ingredients in crock-pot and heat on high for 3 to 4 hours.
Or simmer slowly in large pot at least 1 hour.

title: breaded chicken
directions: Wash and pat dry chicken breast.
Dredge in beaten egg.
Dredge in bread crumb mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: country vanilla ice cream
directions: Add sugar gradually to beaten eggs.
Continue to beat until mixture is very stiff.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into can and freeze.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Mix all together. Dot with 1 stick of butter and grated Parmesan cheese. Put in 10 x 13-inch casserole. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: dilly artichoke rice salad
directions: Bring chicken broth to boil, add rice and cook over low heat for 20 minutes or until rice is tender and broth is absorbed. Remove from heat and cool.

title: a bear's heart
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 5-inch heart shaped baking tin. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool and turn out on a platter. Serve.

title: cherry delight pie
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine to make crust. Press into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°, then allow crust to cool.
Mix powdered sugar, milk and cream cheese in small bowl.
Beat with mixer until creamy and smooth.
Spread over cooled crust.
Sprinkle pecans on top and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Mix package of whipped topping and spread over nuts. Top with one can of cherry pie filling.
Your pie is ready to live up to its name, a real delight.

title: quick fruit crisp
directions: Pour fruit into buttered casserole.
In mixing bowl, mix sugar, flour and margarine with fingers until crumbly.
Sprinkle on fruit.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes until brown and bubbly.
Can use any kind of fruit.

title: no shell coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees:
Beat together flour, sugar, eggs, and milk.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Pour into 8 inch deep pie pan and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Or until knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean.

title: spaghetti with eggs and bacon
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Meanwhile, cook bacon; drain and crumble, then set aside.
Combine eggs, Parmesan cheese and milk in a small bowl.
Drain spaghetti and return to cooking pan.
Stir in egg mixture.
Quickly toss and cook until egg mixture is done and coats spaghetti.
Stir in bacon and serve immediately with additional Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cranberry jelly
directions: Cook the cranberries and water until soft.
Puree in food processor. Add the sugar and juice.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Boil briskly for 5 minutes.
Pour into molds.
Cover with paraffin.

title: ripe tomato pickle
directions: Peel and chop tomatoes.
Chop peppers and onions.
Mix all together. Sprinkle salt over mixture and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Drain and rinse salt off mixture.
Add vinegar, sugar and spices to mixture.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Pour into canning jars.
Cook in jars for 10 minutes.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients and let set in refrigerator overnight. Shape into rolls. Wrap in foil. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Reduce heat to 250° and bake 30 minutes longer.
Open foil; drain. Let rolls set out until dry.

title: janice's shrimp dip
directions: Drain shrimp; put vinegar over shrimp.
Drain out vinegar; rinse shrimp.
Put on clean paper towel.
Pour into mixture of mayo and sour cream.
Add onion and garlic powder.

title: cake that never lasts
directions: Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes.
Watch closely the last 15 minutes.
May burn.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix well (with hands, if necessary) after it softens well. Roll into marble size balls.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: duchess potatoes
directions: Combine
mashed
potatoes,
butter and salt with beaten egg yolks and form into balls, hearts or other shapes.	Place in
a greased
baking
dish and brush with beaten egg whites. Brown in a 350° oven.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in pan; stir in water and peaches.
Bring to boil and boil 1 minute, stirring gently. Remove from heat; stir in butter or oleo, lemon rind and juice and almond flavoring.
Cool.
Bake in 425° oven for 40 to 45 minutes, using your favorite pie crust recipe.

title: cheese soup
directions: Place celery, carrots, and green onions in a pan with water. Bring to a boil. Lower heat and simmer 5 minutes. Drain and set aside.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Dissolve butter in boiling water.
Beat eggs with sugar, salt and cold water.
Dissolve yeast into warm water.
Combine mixtures in large bowl, then add in plain flour.
Cover bowl with foil and raise overnight in refrigerator.
Take out only 1/4 part of dough. Knead and shape.
Cut out with biscuit cutter; let raise 1 hour. Bake at 425° until brown.

title: saucy steak
directions: Cook steak in flour; pound into beef.
Brown in oil in 10-inch skillet; push beef to side.
Cook onion in oil until tender; drain.
Drain potato liquid in measuring cup.
Add enough water to make 1 cup.
Mix potato liquid, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, bouillon, salt, marjoram and pepper; pour on beef and onion.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Rinse beans under running water to separate.
Add potatoes, beans and pimento to skillet.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until beans are tender, 10 to 15 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and white rice
directions: Prepare Minute rice as directed.
Cook green peppers and onions in oil over low heat until tender, but not browned.
Blend cornstarch with small amount of chicken stock.
Add remaining stock and soy sauce.
Gently stir chicken and stock into vegetables.
Cook and stir until sauce is clear and thickened.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breast on slice of chipped beef. Mix together sour cream, mushroom soup, mushrooms and sherry. Spoon mixture over chicken. Top each serving with a half strip of bacon. Bake, covered, for 3 hours at 300°. Remove cover and brown.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, soda and salt; set aside. In a mixer bowl, beat together eggs, pumpkin, sugar and oil.
Add flour mixture; beat well. Stir in pecans. Spread in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.

Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on wire rack.	Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting. Sprinkle with additional chopped pecans. Cut into squares.
Makes 24.

title: sunflower cheese ball
directions: Mix 1 cup sunflower kernels and next 7 ingredients.
Shape into a ball.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Unwrap and roll top side in remaining sunflower kernels.
Place on a large plate.
Using the chips, about 1 inch from the bottom of the cheese ball stick on flat edge of each chop into cheese ball so the point is sticking out.
Continue around the cheese ball until it resembles a sunflower.
Serve immediately.

title: hamburger & tomato paste
directions: Cook meat in frying pan and drain off grease. Add flour and stir. Then add tomato paste with small can of water. Stir. Then add about two small cans more of water. Delicious over rice.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound chicken breast and place a piece of ham on top.
Cube cheese and place on top of ham.
Fold chicken over top and anchor with toothpicks.
Roll in Shake 'n Bake and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: beef rouladen
directions: Put a portion of stuffing in center of meat.
Tie meat in roll with a string.
Brown meat rolls in a large pan.
Saute onions; add water to pan.
Add seasonings and gravy mix.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Add mushrooms 15 minutes before serving.
Be sure to cut strings before serving rolls.
Serve gravy separately.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat thoroughly.
Let drain in colander.
Brown onions in margarine (for lower fat recipe, omit and use 1 teaspoon minced onions, don't brown).
Let sour cream sit at room temperature and mix with flour.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar. Let stand. Beat eggs slightly. Beat in oil and vanilla. Mix and sift flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; stir with apple mixture. Stir in walnuts. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch oblong pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven about 1 hour or until cake tests done. Let stand in pan until cool.

title: meat loaf 'n cheese roll-up
directions: Crumble crackers and mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pat meat mixture into a rectangle (on waxed paper).
Top with cheese and roll like a jelly roll.
Seal ends and side.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and let cool for about 5 minutes before slicing.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage well and drain. Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish or casserole dish. Sprinkle breadcrumbs over butter. Sprinkle sausage over breadcrumbs. Sprinkle cheese over sausage. Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper well. Pour egg mixture over cheese. Chill for 8 hours or overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients and sprinkle 1 box Jiffy cornbread mix on top. Press down until moist.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Put in quart jar and shake.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar; continue creaming until light and fluffy.
Add buttermilk.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add fruits and nuts.
Dredge into flour mixture.
Add this to other mixture; blend thoroughly.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets or into greased miniature muffin pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble up the breads in large bowl.
Add onion, celery and salt and pepper.
Add chicken broth, mixing well.
Add butter, milk and the soup.
Taste of additional salt and pepper.
Pour into a greased pan and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Add salt, soda and brown sugar. Stir in pecans until lightly covered.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: texas cavier dip
directions: Drain the peas and mash.
Add the remaining ingredients to the melted Velveeta, then fold into mashed peas.
Serve hot with corn or flour tortilla chips.

title: bonnie's chicken casserole
directions: Fix noodles according to package directions.
Drain and put back on stove.
Add chicken, undrained, soup and Velveeta.
Heat until blended. Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line bottom of pan with chicken; spread can of soup on chicken.
Mix 1 stick of margarine in warm chicken stock.
Mix stuffing mix with liquid.
Put on top of chicken in pan.
Make sure dressing mix is moist.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, until brown.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: With rolling pin, crush gingersnaps between two sheets of wax paper.
Measure 1 1/4 cups.
In large bowl, combine gingersnap crumbs with milk and egg.
Add chuck, pork, onion, salt, pepper and allspice.
Using hands, mix well to combine.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
With moistened hands, shape mixture into meatballs, 1 1/2-inch in diameter.
Preheat oven to 325°.
In hot butter in large skillet, saute meatballs until brown.
Remove to a 2-quart casserole as they brown.
Remove skillet from heat; pour off drippings.
Measure 1/4 cup, adding more butter if needed.
Pour back into skillet.
Add flour stirring to make a smooth mixture. Gradually stir in 1 1/2 cups water.
Add bouillon cubes.
Bring mixture to boiling, stirring constantly.
Strain over meatballs. Bake covered 1 hour.
Garnish with parsley sprigs.
Serve with noodles if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: after-school gingersnaps
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter, sugars, molasses and egg. Combine flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and ginger; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour. Roll out the dough on a lightly floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness and cut into desired shapes.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 5 or 6 minutes or until set (do not overbake).
Remove from pan to cool on wire racks.
Yields about 6 dozen.

title: vegetable surprise
directions: Saute celery and onion in skillet until tender.
Mix all ingredients together and bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chili pepper rice
directions: Cook rice, jalapenos and onion together until rice is fully cooked.
Drain water off rice if needed.
Then mix sour cream into rice.
Then put in casserole dish in 2 layers.
After first layer, top with queso dip and grated cheese.
Then put the second layer on and top once more with queso dip and grated cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: ginger creams
directions: Mix and spread on cookies while slightly warm.

title: mexican burger
directions: Mix ground beef with cumin, salt and pepper.
Stir in picante sauce.
Cook hamburgers for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with mild chili peppers or picante sauce.

title: fudge
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa, salt, vanilla and milk.
Continue to stir until it boils.
Do not stir for 1/2 hour or until it forms a hard ball in cold water.
Butter plate to pour on.
Add vanilla; beat together well, pour on buttered plate.
Let harden, cut and enjoy!

title: under-the-sea salad
directions: Combine jello with cream cheese, using juice off of pears as liquid for jello and 1 cup boiling water.
Add crumbled cream cheese, mashed pears and ginger.
Let set, preferably overnight. Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut the tomatoes crosswise into 3/8-inch thick slices.
In small bowl, beat together eggs, salt and pepper until frothy.
In separate small bowls, place bread crumbs and flour.

In a large skillet, melt tablespoon oil or shortening over medium heat. Dip each tomato slice into egg, then flour, then egg again and then crumbs. Fry tomato slices until golden brown on one side. Turn and fry to golden on remaining side, 4 to 5 minutes total, adding more oil as needed. Serve immediately or keep warm in a 300° oven no longer than 15 minutes. Serves 4.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Add all the ingredients together and mix well. Pour into a 4-quart greased and floured casserole and bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until tested done. Or pour into 2 greased and floured layer pans.

title: wassail punch
directions: Pour cider into large kettle.
Add spices, fruit and salt. Bring to hard boil.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove from stove.
Cool and then strain.
Serve hot.
May add vodka or gin before serving.

title: dinner in a dish
directions: Place chopped onion in buttered casserole.
Slice potatoes and place on top of onion.
Pour can of cream-style corn on top of potatoes.
Top this mixture with browned sausage and cover with tomato juice.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) until potatoes are done (1 1/2 hours).

title: strawberry angel food cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in frozen strawberries.
Cool until mixture begins to thicken.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Cover bottom of 8 x 10-inch pan with half of the torn cake. Pour over half of the strawberry mixture.
Make another layer of cake and pour remaining mixture over.
Refrigerate 4 or 5 hours to set.
Cut into squares.

title: caramel coconut pie
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add coconut and chopped pecans.
Cook until golden brown, stirring frequently.
Set aside.

title: corn pudding(side dish)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix egg yolks and sugar in large bowl. Add drained corn and mix.
Pour milk in until it comes to top of corn.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish and sprinkle with cinnamon and chips of butter.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dump-it saladgroves, texas
directions: Dump together, chill and serve.

title: carrot fondant
directions: If you've made jelly and it refuses to jell, don't bother emptying it out of glasses to boil again.
Just put in the oven, glasses and all, at 250° for about an hour.
Put a small portion of water in the bottom of the pan.

title: steak 'n rice
directions: Cut steak or chicken into strips.
In a large skillet, brown meat in oil, using medium heat.
Add onions.
Saute until tender or crisp.
Blend soup, sherry and liquid from mushrooms and garlic salt.
Pour over steak or chicken.
Add mushrooms.
Reduce heat. Pour in large baking dish.
Cook for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Blend eggs and sugar together.
Add Eagle Brand milk, chocolate, vanilla and milk together.
Fold in whipped cream. Freeze with electric freezer.

title: rancho baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add onions and simmer.
Add to all other ingredients and pour in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover with sliced smoked sausage, if desired.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix well until completely coated.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Cream together oil, sugar and eggs; blend in baby food.
Mix in flour and cinnamon.
Stir in carrots and nuts; pour into pan.
Bake on middle rack for 45 minutes to 1 hour; test with toothpick.

title: white loaf bread or rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, stir in shortening and sugar, salt, eggs and potatoes into yeast water.
Then add 4 cups flour. Beat until smooth.
Mix in more flour to make easy handling. Knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl.
Let rise until doubled.
Knead down and shape into loaves or rolls.
Place in pans and let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° until golden brown (about 30 minutes).

title: the recipe(sauce)
directions: Simmer sugar, water and instant coffee 30 minutes in a large saucepan.
Cool.
Add vodka, brandy and vanilla.
Refrigerate. Use 1 cup of the syrup to 1 quart of vanilla ice cream.
Blend just until mixed and serve in footed goblets along with a short straw.
Chill goblets in freezer.
Makes a super gift.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix flour and shortening together; add egg.
In separate bowl, mix salt, vanilla and sugar.
Combine all together and add pineapple.
Drop by spoonfuls and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rice krispies treat
directions: Melt margarine; add marshmallows.
Stir until mixed well. Take off heat and add Rice Krispies.
Pour into buttered pan. Press down and then cut into squares and serve.

title: pot roast
directions: Coat roast with flour.
Add oil to hot pan, preferably a dutch oven.
Brown roast on all sides in hot pan on top of stove. Remove from pan and drain off any remaining oil.
Add meat back to pan along with seasonings, 1/2 c broth and wine.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Add vegetables to pot and continue to bake for about 60 minutes or until meat reaches desired doneness. Check pot occasionally to make sure there is
1/2 to 1 inch of liquid in pan; add additional broth if necessary.

title: zucchini bread (squash)
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add all this to egg mixture. Beat.
Add vanilla, grated zucchini, nuts and raisins.

title: bread dip
directions: Prepare 24 hours before.
Cut large round ring in bread (not all the way through bread, leaving bottom of bread).
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill overnight.
Let stand 1 hour before serving.
Pour bread dip in center of cut out bread.
Use 2 loaves of bread to dip into; cut bread into cubes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar, then add flour and eggs in order, then the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake to a golden brown at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: almond butter crunch
directions: Toast almonds in 350° oven and set aside.
Mix together remaining ingredients, except chocolate.
Cook to 275°.
Stir to 300° (use candy thermometer).
Pour on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cool fast.
Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Spread on cold candy and sprinkle with nuts.
Crack into pieces before chocolate is set.
May make 2 or 3 batches at once.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat the sugar, oil, pumpkin and eggs well.
Add the dry ingredients and mix.
Bake at 350° for exactly 30 minutes in a 10 x 15-inch pan.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in the 1/3 cup butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine the egg and light cream.
Add all at once to flour mixture, stirring with fork just to moisten.
Spread dough in greased 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pan and bake 15 to 18 minutes at 450°.

title: dessert pudding
directions: Mix all together and put into 9 x 13 pan.
Prick crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool.

title: house dressing
directions: Put ingredients into the bottle of dressing and shake well. Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: brownie cake
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs one at a time. Sift flour and cocoa together and add alternately with milk. After pouring into greased pan, sprinkle pecans over the top. Place in cold oven.
Bake at 300° for approximately 2 hours.

title: lasagna(italian)
directions: Heat oil; brown hamburger, garlic and onion until brown.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder, oregano and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Mix cheeses.
Put alternate layers: meat sauce, cheese, noodles and ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: cheese and pasta in a pot
directions: Cook ground beef in a little vegetable oil in a large, deep frying pan until brown, stirring often with a fork.
Drain off excess fat.
Add onions, garlic, spaghetti sauce, stewed tomatoes and undrained mushrooms; mix well.
Simmer 20 minutes or until onions are soft.
Meanwhile, cook macaroni shells according to package directions; drain and rinse with cold water.
Pour 1/2 the shells into a deep casserole.
Cover with half the tomato meat mixture.
Spread 1/2 the sour cream over sauce.
Top with slices of Provolone cheese.
Repeat, ending with slices of Mozzarella cheese. Cover casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove cover; continue baking until Mozzarella melts and browns slightly.
Serves 8.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Saute sausage.
Drain well and crumble.
Add margarine, onion, bread crumbs, oregano and Parmesan cheese to sausage and mix well. Mix egg with water and add to sausage mixture.
Stem and wash mushrooms.
Stuff stem side of mushroom with sausage mixture. Arrange in baking pan.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a greased dish in a pan of water at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve with butter.

title: impossibly easy cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease a 9 in. pie plate. Cook ground beef and onion until beef is brown, then drain. Stir in salt and spread in pie plate, sprinkle with cheese. Stir remaining ingredients until blended. Pour into pie plate. Bake 25 minutes or until knife inserted in the center comes out clean. Serves 6. High altitude bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in an unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 45 minutes.

title: sour cream potato toss
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and 1/8 teaspoon of pepper. Separate whites of hard-cooked eggs from yolks; chop whites and add to potato mixture.
Chill thoroughly.
Reserve 1 hard-cooked egg yolk.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar and syrup.
Cook over medium heat and boiling until it forms a ball when dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Set in cold water until cool, then beat until thick.
Spread in buttered pan and refrigerate. Cut into squares.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift flour, salt and cocoa together.
Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and red food coloring; mix well. Fold in soda and vinegar; do not beat the dough.
Bake in three 9-inch greased and floured round pans for 25 to 30 minutes, or in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple-cheese pizza
directions: Scald milk.
Add the next 3 ingredients; cool to lukewarm. Place water in large bowl; sprinkle in yeast and stir until dissolved.
Add milk mixture, egg and flour; beat until smooth. Brush top of dough with oil.
Cover; let rise until doubled in bulk.
Combine cheese and the next 5 ingredients; set aside. Drain pineapple (well).

title: corn bread bake
directions: Coarsely shred enough zucchini to make 1/3 cup, set aside.
Cut remaining zucchini into 1/4-inch slices.
In a 10-inch skillet brown sausage.
Remove sausage from skillet.
Reserve drippings. To drippings in skillet add zucchini slices and onion, stirring to coat.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat about 5 minutes, or until zucchini is slightly softened.
Stir twice.
In a greased 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking dish starting center of dish, arrange cooked zucchini slices in circles around pan using all slices. Prepare corn muffin mix as directed.
Stir in shredded zucchini and sausage and shredded cheese.
Spread mixture evenly around on top of zucchini slices, bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put ground beef in kettle.
Add 6 cups water, dry soup mix and all the rest, any kind of vegetables you desire.
Also, add some onion as desired.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top mixture with 1/2 cup of chopped nuts.
Cut up apples and dip.

title: taffy
directions: Boil until it spins a thread.
Pour in a pie tin until cool enough to pull, then cut into pieces with scissors before it becomes too brittle.

title: potato cheese pie(diabetic recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, beat eggs well.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to combine.
Spray 4 (5 1/4 x 1 1/2-inch) foil tart pans with nonstick cooking spray.
Divide potato mixture into pans and bake until top of each pie is golden brown and mixture is set, about 45 minutes.
To serve, invert pies onto serving platter.
Makes 4 servings.
One serving equals 1 bread, 1 vegetable and 2 meats.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix everything but cheese.
Pour 1/2 of batter in a greased dish.
Add 1/2 of cheese on batter, then pour remaining batter on cheese.
Cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana walnut bread
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs.
Beat hard until light.
Blend in bananas.
Add sifted dry ingredients, beating until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: cheddar turkey bake
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Mix lightly and spoon into 10 x 16-inch baking dish.
Toss cornflakes with butter.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Top with tomato slices. Bake again 5 minutes.
Top with additional cheese if desired. Serves 6.

title: onion lovers twist
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water (no need to sift flour; measure by lightly spooning into cup).
Add 2 cups flour, sugar, salt, water, milk, butter and egg.
Blend on low speed until moist; beat for 2 minutes.
By hand, stir in remaining flour to form soft dough. Cover and rise in warm place until doubled.

title: "pine" chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate chicken overnight.
Cook over coals, basting frequently with marinade.

title: delicious brown rice
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in an 11 x 13-inch baking dish. Cook at 350° for 1 hour. Stir slightly after it has cooked 15 minutes.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender. Add water gradually to make a stiff dough, adding more water if necessary.
Knead dough on lightly floured board. Cover with cloth and let rest 15 minutes. Roll dough out on floured board until very thin.
Cut into 2 or 3-inch circles or squares.
Drop into hot oil and fry until browned, turning often. Dough will puff as it fries.
Serve with warm butter and honey.

title: fiddle-faddle
directions: Place the popcorn in a large bowl and set aside.
Place the pecans and almonds on a large cookie sheet.
Toast at 350° for 10 minutes to make crisp.
In a saucepan, combine the butter, sugar and salt and melt, but do not boil.
Stir briskly to blend well. Remove the nuts from the oven and add to the popcorn.
Pour the butter mixture over the popcorn mixture and stir with a large spoon until well coated.
Spread out as thinly as possible onto a cookie sheet and return to the oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from the oven and cool slightly.
Remove from the pan with a spatula. It will continue to get crisp as it cools.
Serve within a few hours, as it does not keep well.
Serves 6.

title: salad bowl puff
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Generously grease 9 x 1 1/4-inch pie plate.
Heat water and margarine to boiling in 2-quart saucepan. Add baking mix all at once.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball, about a minute and a half.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Continue beating until smooth.
Spread in pie plate.
Do not spread up side.
Bake until puffed and dry in center, 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Just before serving, fill with either salad.

title: rhubarb torte
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, butter and 2 egg yolks.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix rhubarb, flour, 2 cups sugar and 2 egg yolks.
Put on crust and bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: corn chowder soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt margarine over medium heat.
Add onion, celery and green pepper.
Cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until vegetables are soft.
Blend in flour and paprika; cook, stirring for 3 minutes.
Gradually stir in chicken broth and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes or until comes to a boil.
Add corn; cover and cook for 5 minutes. Stir in milk, lemon juice and pepper.
Reduce heat to low and heat soup to serving temperature.
Do not boil, mixture will curdle.

title: green christmas punch
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Before serving, add 1 quart of pineapple sherbet.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Mix jello and Kool-Aid and 2 1/2 cups sugar together and dissolve with 1 cup boiling water.
Add 2 quarts water and can of pineapple juice.
Chill.

title: grandma's cookies
directions: Combine Crisco, sugar, baking powder, egg and vanilla.
Add flour gradually, then milk.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Drop with spoon or roll them.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until done in boiling water.
Peel and cut crosswise into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Preheat oven to 375°. Using butter, thoroughly grease a 2-quart deep casserole dish. Peel bananas and cut crosswise into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Place in a medium bowl and toss with orange juice.
In another small bowl, mix brown sugar with cinnamon.
Set aside.
In bottom of prepared casserole dish, arrange 1/3 of the potato slices in a single layer, overlapping slightly.
Top with half the banana slices; sprinkle with 1/3 of the sugar mixture.
Dot with 1/3 of the butter.
Repeat layering again with the potatoes, bananas, sugar and butter.
Reserve 12 banana slices for top.
Top with remaining potatoes.
Arrange reserved banana slices on top. Sprinkle with remaining sugar; dot with remaining butter and pour on rest of orange juice.
Bake for 45 minutes or until bubbly and very hot.
Serves 12.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix vegetables, cheese and bacon.
In another bowl, combine Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar.
Mix well.
Pour over vegetables and mix well.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: jello salad
directions: Put pineapple and sugar in blender.
Pour dry Jell-O in 1 cup measuring cup and add boiling water.
Stir well.
Put in blender and mix well.
Add cream cheese and nuts.
Put into bowl or mold. Chill.

title: rice parmigiana(adopted from "the vegetarian epicure")
directions: Toss rice with parsley, onion and cheese.
Beat eggs with milk and add salt and pepper, if desired.
Combine 2 mixtures and pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or so until firm.

title: derek's hot mexican bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients (except cheeses) with mixer or blender. Sprinkle Monterey Jack and Cheddar cheese on top of bean mixture that has been poured in 1-quart size baking dish.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° (uncovered).
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: moussaka(greek eggplant casserole)
directions: Brown potatoes in butter or oil until light brown, for 3 minutes.
Arrange in bottom of pan (9 x 12-inch) with 3 tablespoons bread crumbs.
Brown the onions and hamburger in half of the butter.
Add parsley, tomatoes, wine, salt and pepper to taste and cook on low flame until liquid is absorbed.
Set aside to cool, then add 3 tablespoons bread crumbs.
Mix well; season to taste.
While this is being prepared, slice eggplants lengthwise. Fry each slice in butter, browning each side.
Cover potatoes with 1/2 meat mixture, then add layer of eggplants and meat again, until all is used, ending with eggplant.
Top with cream sauce (see following).
Bake at 350° to 400° for 1 hour.

title: old fashioned egg custard
directions: Combine sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Beat 3 egg yolks and 3 egg whites.
Add to dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Add milk.
Stir in melted butter; pour into pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: lemon-herb chicken(microwave)
directions: Place breasts in cooking dish.
(You may wish to cut in strips.
They go further and are more tender.)
Pour lemon juice over chicken.
Combine spices and sprinkle over chicken.
Place mushrooms on top.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 15 minutes.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Serve.

title: chocolate sundae cake
directions: Combine brown sugar, cocoa and water; mix well. Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan. Place marshmallows evenly on top. Prepare cake mix, following package directions. Pour over marshmallows. Top with pecans. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pickle relish
directions: Grind pickles and onions.
Let stand 1 hour.
Put in colander and drain.
Cook vinegar, sugar, salt and spices.
Cook a few minutes.
Add pickles and onions and cook 5 minutes.
Put in pint jars and seal.

title: harvest-of-fruit parfaits
directions: Thaw berries in a small bowl in microwave on Low for 1 to 2 minutes.
Cut strawberries in half.
Set berries aside.

title: ham dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayo; add ham, onions and sugar.

title: green cabbage in cream
directions: Cook onion in butter.
Add thinly sliced cabbage.
Cook until wilted, about 10 minutes.
Add cream, salt and pepper.
Cook about 5 minutes more.

title: paska(traditional slavic easter bread)
directions: Scald milk and let cool.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Cut butter into dry ingredients until crumbly. Place 1/2 cup of milk (at lukewarm temperature).
Add yeast (crumbled) and 2 teaspoons sugar into a medium sized saucepan or bowl.
The yeast will be activated and mixture will become foamy.
This may take 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hot broccoli soup
directions: Take broccoli from package; place in a 2-quart casserole dish. Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave at High 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir to break apart and drain, if necessary.
Add soup, milk, butter, basil and pepper.
Microwave at High 4 to 5 minutes; stir after 3 minutes.
To serve, ladle soup into serving bowls.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato wedges
directions: Arrange potato wedges in shallow pan; spray with vegetable spray and sprinkle with salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: "jack cheese and hot pepper" quiche
directions: Bake pricked pie shells until just crisp.
Combine mayo and milk; add eggs.
Add flour.
Add cheese, ham and broccoli.
Pour in shells.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: diet soup
directions: Dice vegetables and cover with water.
Cook until tender, but don't overcook.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until firm peaks form. Fold in sugar, chocolate and nuts.
Make sure you fold in and do not beat.
Put on cookie sheet with parchment paper or on aluminum foil sprayed with Pam.
Cook at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: essie's pound cake
directions: Use small amount of water with sugar and butter. Heat until dissolved.
Mix with 1/2 cup white wine (Zinfandel). Use fork and punch holes in cake. Then pour glaze over cake while in pan. Cool before removing from pan.

title: strawberry butter
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter until light and fluffy; gradually add sugar.
Slowly add strawberries to creamed mixture; beat well.	Serve with French toast, waffles, muffins, biscuits or bagels.

title: chicken and shrimp roma
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter; set aside.
Add garlic and saute until soft, not brown.
Add oil to butter in skillet.
Cook chicken strips for 10 minutes.
Add shrimp and saute until just pink. (Steam or microwave broccoli until just slightly softened.)
Add to the chicken.
Return mushrooms to skillet and add wine, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over cooked linguine or rice.

title: black bean soup
directions: Bring beans to a boil in twice as much water as beans.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 1 hour.
Drain.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Heat chicken stock and milk in large saucepan over medium-high heat to almost boiling.
Remove from heat and set aside.
In large soup pot over low heat, melt butter.
Add flour, stirring constantly 3 minutes to cook flour and make a roux.
Gradually add milk mixture to roux, pouring in a slow steady stream while stirring vigorously.
Add bay leaves and white pepper, diced potato and salt.
Continue to simmer over low heat 15 to 20 minutes, until potatoes are tender and soup thickens.
Lightly mash potatoes in soup and stir to blend well.
Pour soup into ovenproof crocks and top with sour cream, Cheddar cheese, green onions and bacon bits.
Bake in oven to melt cheese.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, butter and 10x sugar. Line bottom of spring-form pan. Pack firmly. Do not bake yet.

title: easy potato salad
directions: Mix mayo, onion, celery, sour cream, mustard, pepper and salt.
Add to potatoes that have been peeled, cubed, and boiled.
Mix well. Add chopped eggs and blend gently.
Refrigerate at least one hour before serving.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Bake at 350° in 9 x 13 pan about 30 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: chunky applesauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in large glass bowl.
To cook by microwave:
cover with wax paper.
Cook at high 7 to 10 minutes, or until apples are tender; stir once.
Let stand, covered 7 minutes. Mash apples until chunky; serve warm or chilled.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomato sauce together well with hands.
Form into balls (walnut size).
Place in pan or on cookie sheet.
Brown on all sides on top rack in a hot oven.
Pour off excess fat.
Place in large cooking pot tomato sauce, bring to a boil.
Add meat balls and simmer 1 hour.

title: texas chocolate cake
directions: Sift sugar with flour.
Mix soda with buttermilk.
Mix margarine, Crisco, cocoa and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Pour over sugar and flour; mix well.
Add other ingredients; beat well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°.
Start making icing 5 minutes before cake is done.
Ice in pan while cake is hot.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil
potatoes
until
done (to prevent breaking do not stir while cooking);
drain.
Mix milk
and soup.
In a baking dish, layer potatoes, butter, salt
and
pepper as desired and soup mixture.
Continue alternating
layers.
Place
cheese on top; bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: cheesy lemon pudding
directions: Combine Ricotta cheese and lemonade concentrate in a small mixing bowl.
Set aside.
Prepare vanilla pudding according to package directions.

title: lazarus cheese cake
directions: Mix together graham crackers, sugar and butter and line a 9-inch spring-form pan; refrigerate to cool.

title: coconut pie(no crust to make)
directions: Mix together and pour in pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli with bacon bits and onion; add cheese.
Make dressing with Miracle Whip, vinegar, sugar and celery seed.
Mix and shake and add to broccoli mix.
Serve cold.
May be marinated overnight.

title: cocoa pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa; use enough hot water to mix, then add 2 egg yolks.
Mix well.
Add milk and butter.
Pour in unbaked pie crust and bake in a preheated oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Add meringue and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add whole eggs, one at a time, and beat after each.
Add half of flour and buttermilk.
Beat for one minute.
Add remaining flour and buttermilk and the flavoring. Beat 2 minutes more.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°. Toothpick test when done.

title: pepper relish
directions: Remove seeds from peppers and chop peppers and onion really good. Pour boiling water over them and let stand for 10 minutes. Drain and add to the above mixture. Boil for 20 minutes and put in jars. Put in hot bath for 20 minutes.

title: top of stove cornbread(ho cake)
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding milk until soft.
Pour into hot, greased skillet.
Turn over when first side is brown.
Delicious with greens!

title: better than love cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package.
Cool 20 minutes, then poke holes with handle of wooden spoon.
Drizzle milk on cake.
Now drizzle topping and refrigerate.
When cake is cool, spread on whipped topping, then sprinkle candy.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Melt butter in water and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add flour, stirring until you can form a ball.
Beat eggs into mixture, one at a time.
Spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° to 425° for 25 minutes or until done.
Cool completely.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Mix together dry ingredients in plastic bag.
Add applesauce, one tablespoon at a time.
Dough will seem dry, but will form a ball.
Pat a small amount on cutting board 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Cut a small piece of wire and bend to form a "U" shape.
Insert into top of shape.
Let air dry for 1 or 2 days. Makes about 20 small ornaments.

title: old south cucumber lime pickles
directions: Soak clean cucumbers in water and lime mixture in crockery or enamelware for 12 hours or overnight.
Do not use aluminum ware.

title: butterfly pork chops
directions: Heat oil in large skillet and brown chops. Add water, soup mix, soy sauce and ginger.
Cover tightly and simmer 45 to 60 minutes.
Make gravy and serve with rice.

title: ramen noodle cabbage salad
directions: Heat the first 6 ingredients until dissolved; cool.
Toast almonds and sesame seed in oleo; cool.
Chop cabbage coarsely; do not shred.
Break up noodles.
Toss with dressing.

title: coated mixed nuts
directions: Beat the egg white and orange juice with fork until foamy. Stir the sugar, orange peel, ginger and allspice into egg white and orange juice; mix well.
Pour over nuts in a bowl; stir to coat.
Spread in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes, until crisp and lightly browned.
Yields 4 cups.

title: decorating cookies
directions: You will need 1 bowl for each color to be used, Ziploc bags and scissors.

title: (3) bean salad
directions: Whip vinegar, sugar and Wesson oil thoroughly.
Mix and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: sharon's strawberry dessert
directions: Combine Jell-O and boiling water.
Add strawberries; chill until mixture starts to thicken.
Beat Cool Whip into mixture. Break angel food cake into small pieces.
Layer in large truffle bowl cake pieces and strawberries.
Refrigerate until set.
Top that with fresh strawberries.

title: texas corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together; let sit in oiled pan or glass dish 20 minutes.
Cook at 420° for about 40 minutes or until you can pull a clean toothpick in center.
Butter top when removed from oven; let stand 5 minutes and enjoy! So good.
Serves 6. Everyone will want more!

title: turkey loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well and place in a greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or 25 minutes at 70% power in microwave. Rotate 1/4 turn after 15 minutes.
Hold 10 minutes.
If microwaving, cover with plastic wrap.

title: classic fettucine alfredo
directions: In medium sized skillet over medium-low heat, heat oil and butter until butter melts.
Add shallots or onions and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to low.
Add cream and cook about 4 minutes, stirring constantly with wire whip.
Stir in cheese.
Meanwhile, cook fettuccine according to package directions; drain.
To serve, in large bowl, toss hot fettuccine with cream sauce.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Remove from heat and add the poppy seeds.
In each bread slice, fill with a slice of cheese and onion mixture.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: honey-oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients until smooth.
Mix together the flour, salt and baking soda; add to creamed mixture. Add the oats and raisins to the mixture.
Drop onto cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: chicken vol-au-vent
directions: In a medium skillet, brown chicken on both sides in butter or olive oil.
Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water.
Add to chicken. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until meat is tender.
Remove chicken from broth; let cool until cool enough to handle.
Remove bones carefully (boneless chicken thighs may be used).
Measure broth from skillet and add water to equal 1 cup liquid.
Pour liquid into skillet.
Combine flour, salt, paprika and pepper; stir in cream.
Add to chicken broth in skillet.
Cook quickly, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Stir in mushrooms and wine.
Set aside to cool.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and salt. Microwave on High 5 minutes. Stir until sugar dissolves, then microwave on High for 6 minutes. In a large bowl, beat the egg whites until stiff. Pour hot mixture into egg whites a little at a time. Continue to beat mixture until it loses its gloss. Blend in vanilla and stir in nuts. Press candy into buttered dish and cut when firm.

title: zucchini walnut bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Gradually beat in sugar, then oil.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture alternating with zucchini.
Stir in raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Divide into 2 greased and lightly floured loaf pans (9 x 5 x 2 3/4-inch).

title: oatmeal-pecan pie
directions: Combine
eggs,	sugar,	syrup, margarine, milk, vanilla, salt, oats,
coconut and pecans in bowl in order listed; mixing well. Pour
into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until set.

title: pinto bean goulash
directions: Cook pinto beans by your usual method.

Saute hamburger, onion and pepper until meat loses its red color. Combine pinto beans in slow cooker (or large pot) with other ingredients except wieners. Cook at low temperature until about done. Add wieners and cook 30 minutes longer.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Saute onions in butter until transparent.
Add chilies, garlic and cheeses.
Heat until cheeses melt on low heat.
Blend in evaporated milk.
Serve with corn chips.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cut candy, dates and nuts in small pieces.
Leave cut up overnight in pan.
Sift 2 cups flour over mixture. Cream butter and sugar with eggs.
Add soda, remaining flour and buttermilk to butter and sugar mixture.
Pour over fruit mixture.
Mix well and bake for 2 1/2 hours at 275°.
While hot, mix the glaze and pour over cake.

title: rich potato casserole
directions: Bake potatoes (I use microwave).
Cook, peel and chop as for potato salad.
In saucepan, cook onions in the butter; add cream, potatoes, milk, salt and pepper.
Cook until thickened.
Pour into buttered dish.
Cover with Swiss cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Can drizzle butter on top.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 15 to 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: miniature cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Bring to boil in 2-quart pot, 1 cup water. Reduce heat to low.
Add oil, salt and flour.
Cook, stirring vigorously, until mixture leaves sides of pot and forms compact ball.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition, until smooth and glossy.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet by half teaspoons and bake about 30 minutes. Cut off tops and fill with custard.

title: dorito casserole
directions: Simmer all ingredients in a pan for 20 minutes.
Add bag of broken Doritos chips.
Put in a casserole and top with cheese. Bake in a 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: curried rice and carrots
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add shallots and garlic.
Cook briefly, stirring.
Add bay leaf.
Sprinkle with curry powder. Add rice and thin carrot strips, stirring.
Add broth.
Cover; bring to a boil.
Let simmer for 17 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut round steak into small pieces.
Put in skillet with a little water; add onion and green pepper; add salt and black pepper to season to taste.
Cook for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix and cook to hard boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Beat on high speed to spreading consistency.
Spread on cake.

title: quick clam or crab dip
directions: Let
cream
cheese
stand
at
room temperature and mix cream cheese,
sour cream, seasoning and meat (either clams or crabmeat) together
and chill in refrigerator for 1/2 hour and serve.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out.
Cut into doughnut shapes and fry in hot oil.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Mix ground beef with salsa.
Place tortilla in 8-inch square casserole dish that is at least 5-inch deep.
Top with hamburger, then peppers, onions and tomatoes.
Top with each type of cheese. Place another tortilla and repeat layer.
End with cheese on top of beef.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand 15 minutes.
Top with sour cream.

title: easy tuna-cheese-broccoli pie
directions: Prepare your own pastry shell or use a frozen one.
In bowl, beat eggs, blend in milk with whisk, add mayonnaise, mustard, flaked tuna and thawed broccoli.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake in moderate oven for 30 to 40 minutes, until custard is set in center.
Remove from oven, let stand 10 minutes and cut into wedges to serve.
Yields 6 servings.

title: spaghetti pasta salad
directions: Cook shells; drain.
Add other ingredients and mix well.

title: jason duke's green bean casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package.
Saute onion and mix with rice.
Combine all other ingredients.
Place in a greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom soup

title: chocolate-pecan brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 9 inch square baking pan.
In a small bowl, mix together flour and baking soda.
In a small saucepan, combine sugar, butter, and water.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; remove immediately from heat.
Stir in 1 cup of chocolate morsels and vanilla extract until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth.
Transfer mixture to a medium bowl, cool completely.
Stir in eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually stir in flour mixture until smooth.
Stir remaining chocolate morsels and nuts into batter.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Transfer pan to a wire rack to cool completely.
Cut into squares.

title: pasta bolognese
directions: In a skillet, saute ground beef in 1 tablespoon oil until meat loses its pinkness.
Transfer to a pan.
Peel and chop onion. Dice celery and carrot.
Chop ham into small pieces.
Saute in remaining oil with onion, celery and carrot.
Transfer to pan with ground beef and combine.
Add water, tomatoes, garlic, salt, pepper and thyme.
Cover and cook about 20 minutes.
Add chicken broth and cook for a few more minutes.
Cook pasta and drain well. Serve with sauce.

title: apple cake
directions: Peel and cut the apples into cubes.
Mix cinnamon with 5 tablespoons sugar and sprinkle over apples; set aside.
Measure flour, sugar, oil, eggs, orange juice, baking powder, vanilla and salt into a large mixing bowl.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Slice apples thin and spread in an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread apart each biscuit (into thin sections) and spread over apples.
Melt a stick of butter or margarine.
Stir together sugar, cinnamon and water.
Pour over biscuits and apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: pasta with garden vegetables
directions: Pour cooking oil into a wok or large skillet. Add more oil as needed. Preheat medium-high. Stir-fry garlic in hot oil for 15 seconds. Add zucchini and summer squash. Stir for 3-4 minutes. Add mushrooms and green onions; stir-fry until veggies are crisp-tender. Add tomato, oregano, and pepper. Stir-fry 2 more minutes. Remove from heat. Add hot cooked pasta and cheeses into the vegetable mixture. Toss to combine. Sprinkle with mozzarella cheese.

title: 2 tone summer squash loaf
directions: Grate squash separately.
Salt and drain in separate bowls. Squeeze squash.
Heat 2 tablespoons butter.
Cook 1/2 of shallots until wilted.
Add zucchini.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Cook remaining shallots.
Add yellow squash.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Season.
Mix 1/3 cup cream into each squash mixture.
Beat eggs.
Add 1/2 to each bowl. Butter a 1 1/2-quart 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Line with buttered wax paper.
Spread 1/2 of zucchini mixture.
Sprinkle with 1/3 cheese. Gently spread on half of yellow squash without disturbing lower layer.
Sprinkle on another 1/3 of cheese.
Repeat the layering once, ending with yellow.
Place loaf pan in water.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.
Let rest 15 to 20 minutes.

title: aunt bill's microwave candy
directions: Combine sugar, soda, buttermilk and butter.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Punch holes in wrap.
Microwave for 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir and turn dish.
Continue cooking for 15 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Return to oven for 2 minutes or until soft ball forms in cold water or it tests 236° on candy thermometer (do not put thermometer in microwave).
Add vanilla and beat with electric mixer until soft peaks form.
Stir in pecans and spread in 12 x 7-inch dish.
Cool and cut into pieces.
The container needs to be about 3 times the amount of the ingredients or it may boil over.
I cooked mine on the High temperature in a large Corning Ware dish.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with broccoli.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine soup and milk and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine butter and bread crumbs and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon puffs
directions: Drain salmon, save 1/4 to 1/3 cup liquid.
Flake salmon in bowl.
Stir in 1 egg.
Add flour a little at a time.
Mix thoroughly.
Add baking powder to liquid, stir with a fork until foams.
Add to salmon mixture.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil, fry until golden.

title: stewed potatoes or potato soup
directions: Cut potatoes and onion.
Add all other ingredients, except cornstarch and water.
Cook until tender.
Mix cornstarch with water.
Add to stew.
Serve immediately.

title: semi-sweet dipping chocolate(diabetic recipe)
directions: Combine milk powder, cocoa and wax in food processor or blender; blend to soft powder.
Pour into top of double boiler. Add water, stirring to blend.
Add liquid shortening.
Place over hot (not boiling) water; cook and stir until wax pieces are completely dissolved and mixture is thick, smooth and creamy. Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar replacement; let cool slightly. Dip candies according to recipe.

Shake off excess chocolate. Place on very lightly greased wax paper; allow to cool completely. (If candies do not remove easily, slightly warm the waxed paper over electric burner or with clothes iron.)
Store in a cool place.

title: turnip souffle
directions: Boil turnips and carrots together until tender.
Mash and add other ingredients.
Place in greased casserole and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350°.
(Beat egg and mix with the milk before adding to turnips and carrots.)
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture. Mix thoroughly.
Spread batter in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan (jelly roll pan).
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool completely.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing. Cut into bars.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add soup, Ro-Tel, chicken broth and deboned chicken.
Cook 20 minutes.
Layer buttered dish with floured tortillas, mixture and Cheddar cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crumble cookies (you may use blender).
Melt margarine; pour over crumbled cookies to make a crust; set aside some cookie crumbs to garnish cake.

title: shrimp quiche
directions: Put the oil over the frozen potatoes and let set until potatoes thaw. Line greased 10-inch pan. Put cheese over potatoes. Beat together milk, eggs, salt, pepper, nutmeg, sherry, parsley and onion. Sprinkle shrimp over cheese layer and then pour egg mixture over. Bake in 425° oven for 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean 1-inch from edge. Let stand for 5 minutes before slicing.

title: pineapple halwa
directions: Drain the canned pineapple in a colander for about 45 minutes.
Melt 1/2 the stick of butter and add 1 tsp. sooji.
Stir this continuously until aroma arises.
Then add pineapple.
Keep stirring for 10-15 minutes.
When it becomes sticky, add condensed milk and keep stirring until the milk forms lumps.
Add the remaining 1/2 stick of butter.
Keep stirring until golden in color, about 10-15 minutes.
Decorate with almonds or pistachios if desired.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: Approximately 1 hour.

title: mom's cut-out cookies
directions: Cream the first 2 ingredients.
Add eggs, vanilla and water. Add flour.
Chill dough.
Roll and cut.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: barbecued pork in buns
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Use to coat pork cutlets.
Heat oil in a large skillet and cook cutlets until well browned on both sides.
Stir in ketchup, molasses, lemon juice and 1/4 cup water. Heat to boiling, stirring to loosen brown bits from bottom of skillet.
To serve, place cutlet on hamburger bun and spoon sauce over it.

title: southern barbecue
directions: Cook meats until tender.
Cool.
Shred or cut meat up into large pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low for 2 to 3 hours until it reaches consistency you want.

title: grandma's bread and tomatoes
directions: Bring tomatoes and juice to a boil. Add bread and seasonings. Grandma Swango would make this and if she had a 1/2 cup of corn leftover from a past meal, she would add it also. Take about good!

title: strawberry sorbetta (ice)(sherbet)
directions: Puree strawberries.
Make sugar syrup with water and sugar. Cook until clear.
Mix strawberry puree, syrup and lemon juice. Taste; may need more sugar due to tartness of lemon.
Freeze in home ice cream freezer until firm enough to hold shape.
Put in freezer.
Serve as soon as possible.
Nectar of the gods!

title: diabetic cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook raisins in water until water evaporates.
Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener, oil and mix well. Blend in baking soda and flour.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple pumpkin muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine egg, pumpkin, milk, butter, pineapple, flour, sugar and spices; mix well.
Spoon batter into buttered muffin tins.
Fill almost to the top.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dark cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Roll out to about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into squares.
Bake at 350° for a few minutes.
Cool and then frost.

title: calico beans
directions: Drain beans, break up bacon and add everything in a crock-pot. Cook for at least 1 hour.

title: shoe peg salad
directions: Drain corn, beans, peas and pimento. Combine all vegetables in salad bowl.
Mix vinegar, sugar, oil and salt in small bowl. Add to vegetable mixture.
Mix well.
Marinate in the refrigerator overnight.
Approximate Per Serving:
182 calories, total fat 8 g, 36% calories from fat, 3 g protein, 28 g carbohydrates, 3 g fiber, 0 mg cholesterol and 221 mg sodium.

title: fudgies
directions: Mix well and cook as though for pudding.
It will be thinner than regular pudding.
Fill molds.
Eggs may be added for additional nutritional value or for children who are hesitant to eat eggs.

title: chicken divan casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Layer and cut up chicken and broccoli in buttered casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients except bread and cheese and pour over chicken.
Cube bread and mix with grated cheese.
Top casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

title: mango croquettes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add unbeaten egg and mix well. Drop by spoonful in hot oil in a deep frying pan until crispy outside, soft inside.
Serve with ketchup or soy sauce with lemon and crushed garlic.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan, stirring well.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.

title: tomatoes stuffed with peas
directions: Remove stem ends from tomatoes.
Scoop out pulp and seeds.
To stuff each tomato, fill each with 1/4 cup frozen peas.
Dot with 1/4 oleo.
Sprinkle basil on each and top with cheese.
Place tomatoes in pie plate in circular form.
Microwave on medium 6-10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serves 4.

title: talarini
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain grease. Add soup, noodles, corn, mushrooms and half of the cheese. Simmer 10 minutes.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: peppered cheese ball
directions: Mix together and roll into a ball.
Roll it in the black pepper.
Serve with crackers.
