title: broccoli soup
directions: In a soup pot, saute onion and garlic in the oil for 5 minutes, until browned.
Add the water along with the potatoes and boil for 15 minutes, until potatoes are tender.
Add broccoli and continue boiling for 5 minutes.
Blend 3/4 of the soup until creamy.
Return to the soup pot.
Add the spices; heat through and serve.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up 4 slices of bread, any kind and place in greased baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Brown and drain 1 pound bulk sausage meat or links in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Cut links in slices.
Spoon sausage over bread.
Sprinkle with 1 cup grated sharp cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, dry mustard (optional), salt and pepper.
Pour mixture in baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pink strawberry punch
directions: Keep strawberries and pineapple juice frozen until ready to use.
Crush the frozen strawberries and pineapple juice together. Add 2 quarts of ginger ale (add ginger ale last) and 1/2 cup sugar.
Serves 16.
Do not add ice.

title: pig pickin cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour into 3 round greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: barbecue sauce for beef or pork
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan and simmer on low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cream-style corn
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: christmas molasses fruit bonbons
directions: Blend molasses and water. Bring to boil slowly.
Add raisins and bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in the rest of the fruit.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs to creamy mixture.

title: a b c loaf
directions: Place frozen rolls in a greased Bundt pan.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and pudding mix.
Sprinkle over top.
Cut butter in slices over rolls.
Pour pecans over top.
Place pan in cold oven overnight.
In the morning, turn oven on to 350°.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes.
To turn out, do not cool.
Put plate over top of pan and quickly invert pan to turn cake on plate.
The caramel mixture will be very hot.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken bog
directions: Dice chicken, sausage, gizzard, onions and potatoes.
Boil for 1 hour with all other ingredients except rice.
Add rice after boiling.
Serves 3 to 5.

title: catfish stew
directions: Cut bacon in 1-inch square.
Place in pan and fry crisp. Remove from fire and layer potatoes, onions and fish.
Salt and pepper each layer.
Use enough water just to cover ingredients. Sprinkle red peppers over top and add cup of chopped tomatoes. Simmer until potatoes are done.

title: brown mountain cake
directions: Cream
butter; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour and buttermilk, alternating, beginning and ending with flour. Combine water,
cocoa
and	soda, stirring well.
Add to flour mixture, beating
well.
Stir
in vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured cake
pans.
Bake
at
350° for 35 to 38 minutes. Cool in
pans for
10 minutes.
Remove and cool completely on wire racks. Spread
Caramel
Frosting
on
top	and sides and between
layers. Sprinkle
with
grated chocolate and garnish with pecan halves.

title: spiced vinegar
directions: In large earthen crock or glass container with lid, combine all ingredients and stir to mix.
Cover tightly and leave to steep in warm place or in the sun for 3 to 4 weeks.
Strain into bowl, pressing to extract flavor.
Pour through funnel into clean bottle and cork.
Store in cool dark place.
Makes 4 1/2 quarts.
Good to use for seasoning grilled meat or meat marinade.

title: oven shortribs and noodles
directions: Trim ribs and cut in bite size pieces.
Combine dry ingredients in a bag and coat ribs a few at a time.
Arrange meat in a roasting pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 450°, turning meat occasionally for about 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Spoon off and discard fat from pan.
Add water and soup mix.
Cover tightly.
Cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until tender.
Stir noodles into pan juices.
Cover and return to oven for 20 minutes.

title: garlic cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use as dip or spread.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Rub 4 large baking potatoes with shortening; prick.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Increase oven temperature to 400°.
Cut slice from top of each potato; scoop out inside.
Mash potatoes.
Add 1/3 to 1/2 cup milk in small amounts, beating after each addition.
Add 1/4 cup soft butter, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Beat until potatoes are fluffy. Fill potato shells.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel, cube and boil eggplant.
Mix with salt, soup, onion and egg in bowl.
Mix margarine and stuffing mix.
Add 1/2 mix to mixture.
Pour in 2-quart casserole; top with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mess-ghetti
directions: Brown ground beef, drain grease off.
Stir in bell pepper and onion and cook until done.
Stir into meat mixture, the sauce, soup, water, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Let simmer about 15 minutes.
Boil egg noodles and drain.
Mix egg noodles and the meat mixture.
Pour into large baking dish or baking pan.
Top with lots of cheese.
Cover and bake about 15 or 20 minutes at 300°.

title: microwave salmon newburg
directions: Arrange fillets in shallow 1 1/2-quart microwave-type casserole.
Add butter and milk.
Cover and cook 7 minutes or until fish is cooked.
Carefully stir in Newburg sauce mix and microwave 1 minute.
Serve with small red potatoes and vegetable.

title: fiesta chuck roast
directions: You will need 1 oven bag, regular size.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place hen in Dutch oven. Pour the dry rice to the side of chicken. Pour 7-Up/Sprite over chicken.
Dump mushroom soup on top of rice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cream together until fluffy butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs which have been beaten until the color of lemon.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour into prepared 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: stir-fried beef and broccoli
directions: Marinate steak in mixture of 1/4 cup water, soy sauce, sugar, sherry, garlic, ginger and cornstarch for at least 1/2 hour. Drain well, reserving marinade.

title: quick and easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13 inch baking pan.
Mix together the flour, sugar and milk.
Pour mixture into the pan.
Spread peaches including syrup evenly around the pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 - 40 minutes or until the crust turns golden brown.
Let cool for about 10 - 15 minutes before serving.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: cole special butter icing
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients and gradually add the powdered sugar, little by little, alternately with water.
Beat for about 5 minutes.
When used in icing cakes, add a little more water to mixture.
(Used for decorating my cakes.)

title: sweet potato hash browns
directions: In saucepan, place potatoes and enough water to cover.
Heat to boiling; cook for 5 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
In large skillet, heat oil over medium-low heat.
Add onion; saute for 3 minutes.
Add drained sweet potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover; cook for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Increase heat to medium-high.
Add butter and brown sugar to potatoes.
Cook, uncovered, 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Turn occasionally with spatula.

title: purple lady salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Stir in pie filling and pineapple. Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites. Fold in topping and nuts. Chill until firm.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Scrub and rinse potatoes.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but do not cut all the way through.
Put potatoes in a baking dish. Fan slices slightly.
Sprinkle with salt; drizzle with butter. Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake potatoes at 425° for 50 minutes. Remove from oven. Sprinkle with cheeses. Return to oven for another 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Brown meat. Add refried beans. Lay one flour tortilla on cookie sheet. If you line cookie sheet it is less mess. Then add some meat and a handful of cheese. Then layer another tortilla, then add some salsa and cheese, then cover with another tortilla. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted. Makes about 4 medium pizzas.

title: pizza fruit platter
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round pizza pans. Combine the first 6 ingredients and divide batter between 2 pans. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool on rack.
(You may freeze one pizza base.)
Arrange fruits in a circular pattern, starting with strawberries on outer edge and adding bananas, grapes, pineapple and other favorite fruits.
Brush with Apricot Glaze and refrigerate.

title: pumpkin surprise
directions: You may use 3 teaspoonfuls pumpkin pie spice instead of the nutmeg and ginger.

title: dilema
directions: Melt margarine; add flour and pecans.
Pat in pan and bake in oven at 375° for 20 minutes; let cool.
Blend together cream cheese, powdered sugar and one-half of the Cool Whip.
Spread mixture on the crust.
Chill.
Then prepare pudding mix according to package directions.
Place pudding on top of other ingredients, then spread the other half of Cool Whip on top.
Chill and serve.

title: believe it or not cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients lightly until evenly blended. "Do not overmix." Portion with teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet. Press flat with fork dipped in water. Bake at 325° for 7 to 10 minutes, until lightly brown. Let cool a few minutes before removing from pan.

title: deluxe pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar gradually; cream well. Add eggs one at a time, beating 1 minute after each egg.
Add flavorings.
Add flour and milk, beginning and ending with flour. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes in tube pan.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from the oranges and pineapple.
Save the pineapple juice to set the bananas in until all other ingredients are mixed.
After mixing all other ingredients, drain juice from the bananas and mix with other ingredients.
Let salad set overnight for best results.

title: vegetable soup(vegetarian)
directions: Place water and soy sauce in a large pot.
Add vegetables. Bring to a boil.
Add seasonings; simmer over medium-low heat about 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter ups
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter together and add powdered sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Mix thoroughly; will be stiff. Pat out in pan.
Melt flavoring, chocolate chips and Crisco and put on top.
Cut into squares.

title: oatmeal peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, blend butter and peanut butter.
Beat in sugar and brown sugar, then milk, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in the salt and soda, then the flour.
Blend in the oats.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoons onto ungreased sheets.
They spread quite a bit.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown on bottom.
Immediately remove to wire racks.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Heat water and butter to boil.
Remove.
Mix in flour to form a ball.
Add eggs and mix until smooth.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely; set aside.

title: wassail
directions: In a large pan, combine and boil for 5 minutes the water and sugar.
Tie together in a small clean cloth and add the cinnamon, cloves, berries and ginger.
Add the frozen lemonade concentrate, orange juice concentrate and apple cider.
Simmer to blend flavors. Yields 18 servings of 6 ounces each.

title: cobbler delight
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo or butter in baking pan.
Mix flour, sugar and baking powder together.
Add 1 cup milk.
Pour into pan, then add pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan with shortening.
Heat margarine and 1 cup chocolate chips in 2-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly until melted; remove from heat.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to pan along with egg and vanilla.
Stir with large spoon until smooth.
Stir in nuts and chips; spread in pan with rubber spatula.
Bake until center is set, about 30 minutes.
Let cool completely, then cut into squares.
Store tightly covered.

title: sheath cake
directions: Sift together sugar and flour.
Place in saucepan, the oleo, Crisco, cocoa and water.
Bring this to a boil and pour over sugar and flour mixture.
Stir well and add eggs, cinnamon and vanilla. Add soda to buttermilk.
Mix with above ingredients.
Pour into floured and greased loaf pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.

title: cheese strips
directions: Trim crusts, cut each slice in 4 strips.
Dip in melted butter, then in the cheese.
Bake 8 - 10 minutes at 400°.
Cool and sprinkle with paprika.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Drain.
Add 1 teaspoon butter.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form mixture into a "crust" in 10-inch pie plate.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti.
Brown beef, green pepper and onion.
Drain fat.
Stir in tomatoes, paste, sugar and seasonings.
Heat through.
Turn meat mixture into pie plate.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella on top and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix baking mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Make sure all ingredients are mixed well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 450°.

title: party casserole
directions: Save half of Triscuits for topping.
Spread the other half in bottom of casserole.
Drain cans of asparagus, water chestnuts and tuna.
Mix soup and Miracle Whip.
Spread the dressing on top of other ingredients.
Cover with remaining Triscuits.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: bread pudding
directions: In bowl, mix bread, milk and eggs.
Mash and stir.
Add sugar, butter, vanilla, cinnamon and raisins.
Bake in a greased baking pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: white chocolate peppermint
directions: Melt white chocolate in saucepan, crush candy canes into small pieces.
Mix together well.
Line cookie pan with wax paper and spread out evenly.
Place in freezer 10 to 15 minutes or until firm.
Break into bite size pieces.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Simmer tomatoes and garlic until done.
Put through colander and set aside.
Add Wesson oil, peppers, hot peppers and onions to tomato juice and simmer 3 hours.
Combine sugar, salt, tomato paste, oregano and basil and bring to a rolling boil.
Put in hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: multi-grain flapjacks
directions: Process flours, oats, cornmeal, baking powder, baking soda and salt until well blended.
Add butter and process until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Beat eggs and buttermilk together.
Beat in honey.
Stir in flour mixture and optional nuts.
Heat griddle and melt butter to coat.
Ladle the batter to make pancakes and cook until golden on both sides.
Serve with butter and syrup or yogurt and fresh fruit.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: candied papaya coconut bread
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Sift soda and salt with flour and add alternately with buttermilk. Beat well and add fruit and nuts.
Bake 2 hours in greased and floured tube pan at 250°.
Let cool in pan, otherwise it will fall apart.
May use long narrow bread pan instead of tube pan.

title: scalloped broccoli
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Add 1/2 stick butter and cheese. Stir and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Crush crackers with 1/2 stick of melted butter.
Sprinkle on top of broccoli mixture. Bake, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: brown edge wafers
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients. Beat until thoroughly blended.
Makes a very thick batter.
Drop by scant teaspoon on greased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart. Sprinkle with ground blanched almonds or leave plain.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: baked pineapple bread pudding
directions: Tear bread in pieces.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and pour melted butter over it.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix together and finally add the small can of evaporated milk.
Dot with marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: prune nut bread
directions: Combine prunes, orange peel and juice; let stand 1/2 hour. Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, oil and prune mixture; add to dry ingredients, mixing well.
Add nuts.
Turn into oiled 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or use 2 aluminum ring molds. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes in loaf pan, a little less in ring molds.
Remove from pan; cool.

title: brownies
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan over low heat.
Add cocoa and stir. Remove saucepan from heat; add remaining ingredients to it and stir well.
Pour into greased approximately 6 x 8-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven 25 minutes or until done.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add other ingredients (except pineapple juice).
Refrigerate to gel in a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: rice salad
directions: Cream the cheese, sugar and mayonnaise together until smooth. Add rice, fruits and marshmallows.
Fold in Dream Whip and nuts. Pour into dish and chill.

title: sicilian calzones ricotta and onions
directions: Oil cookie sheet or pizza pan.
With rolling pin, roll pizza dough on floured board as thick as pizza.
Saute onions and parsley until golden.
Spread Ricotta on dough.
Top with onions, parsley, Mozzarella, salt, pepper and Romano cheese.
Drizzle with olive oil.
Fold dough to form a pocket (log) and place on cookie sheet.
Cook at 400° for about 1/2 hour.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichoke hearts; chop them up.
Mix with the mayo and cheese.
Put in ovenproof serving dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: meatballs
directions: Beat egg in large mixing bowl.
Add other ingredients and mix. Form into meatballs and fry in pan until browned through, turning often.
Excellent in spaghetti sauce and served with spaghetti or as sandwiches in Italian rolls.

title: chicken-and-sausage gumbo(low-fat)
directions: Place flour in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, or until the color of caramel, stirring flour every 5 minutes.
Brown sausage in a Dutch oven coated with cooking spray over medium heat.
Drain and pat dry with paper towels; wipe drippings from Dutch oven.
Brown chicken; drain and pat dry. Wipe drippings from Dutch oven.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding, sweetened milk, vanilla, dairy whip and water in large bowl.
Mix until well blended.
In serving bowl, layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mixture.
Keep layering until everything is gone.
Chill and serve.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Combine cider
and
corn syrup and heat until butter is melted but not
boiling.
Pour
to 1 1/2 ounces of rum into each serving
cup.
Add
hot cider mixture and sprinkle either of spices or serve with a cinnamon stick.

title: hershey kiss cookies
directions: Sift flour with soda and salt.

title: veggie mix up
directions: Combine ingredients; season and pour sauce over veggies.
Mix well.
Serve with meat of choice or serve alone.

title: aunt leah's carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift dry ingredients.
Combine two mixtures.
Fold in carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into 11 x 13-inch oiled and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: dashprika chicken
directions: Place water, chicken
legs,
celery and onion in medium heavy pot.
Simmer
lovingly
for
hour.
Put
remaining ingredients, except yellow pepper, into pot.
Cook 1/2 hour on low heat.
Make
wheat	flour
stiffening and stir gently into pot. Add yellow	pepper	and
cook
just until tender.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes and a tossed green salad.
Serves 2.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Note:
Should be made day before use.

title: cele's stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops off peppers and remove seeds.
Mix hamburger, egg, onion, rice and chopped pepper tops.
Add salt and pepper.
Stuff green peppers and put in casserole.
Pour tomato juice over all peppers.
Can add water, if needed.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: mushrooms au gratin
directions: Chop mushrooms lengthwise in 1/4-inch slices. In a large frypan, melt butter.
Saute mushrooms until lightly brown.
Cover about 2 minutes. Blend sour cream, salt, pepper and flour.
Stir into mushrooms. Mix in pan and heat, stirring until boiling begins. Remove from heat and pour into shallow pan. Sprinkle with parsley and cheese over top.
Refrigerate until ready to bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: easy-do donuts
directions: In medium bowl blend together sugar, milk, egg and melted butter.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add to liquid mixture and stir lightly; mix in raisins.
Drop heaping teaspoonfuls into shortening heated to 365°.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon in a bag.
Shake warm donuts in bag until coated.

title: pecan slices
directions: Sift flour before measuring.
Blend 1 cup flour and the butter to a smooth paste.
Spread this mixture in a 9 x 12-inch pan; bake in a 350° oven for 12 minutes.
Spread the baked dough with the following mixture:
combine beaten eggs, brown sugar, pecans 2 tablespoons flour, coconut (if desired), baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Stir lemon juice into confectioners sugar a little at a time, until spreading consistency, then ice cookies after they have cooled.
Cut into squares or bars.

title: honey-potato batter bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl; add honey and let stand 15 minutes.
Stir in milk and next 3 ingredients. Gradually add 3 cups flour, one cup at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in enough of the remaining 1 cup flour to make soft dough.
Place dough in 10-inch tube pan coated with cooking spray.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°) free from draft 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until loaf sounds hollow when rapped.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Yields 24 servings (102 calories per slice).

title: easy quiche
directions: Brown meat with pepper and
onion
and drain fat.
Beat eggs, then blend in milk,
mayonnaise and cornstarch.
Combine with meat, cheese and egg mixture.

title: sponge cake
directions: Sift flour, measure and add salt.
In a large bowl, beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar gradually, continuing to beat.
Add vinegar and flavoring; beat, then fold in flour slowly, until all absorbed.
With clean beater, beat egg whites in separate bowl until they hold their shape.
With large wooden spoon or spatula, fold egg yolk mixture into beaten whites, gently; do not beat.
Bake in an ungreased tube pan (10-inch) at 320° for one hour.
After baking, invert immediately.

title: joy juice
directions: Mix all the ingredients in large Tupperware container and fill with water.

title: quick chocolate cake
directions: Mix oleo, shortening, cocoa and hot water and bring to a boil. Then
pour over rest of ingredients that have been mixed together.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in long flat greased and floured pan for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: a peach of a punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend on high for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour into tall glasses.
Garnish with a tablespoon of Cool Whip with a mint leaf.

title: touchdown beans
directions: Mix all together in crock pot.
Cook on low until hot.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Note:
You can also substitute ham, turkey, etc., for the filling.

title: half pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flour. Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: butterfinger bars
directions: Cream sugars and oleo.
Add oats and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt chips and peanut butter in double boiler.
Spread over crust.

title: tomato juice cocktail
directions: Combine all ingredients with tomato juice; simmer for 10 minutes.
Chill and serve or freeze in one pint plastic freezer containers.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: apricot squares
directions: Sift or mix together the dry ingredients.
Work Crisco in like making pie crust.
Mix together eggs, vanilla and milk; add to preceding until it comes together.
Put flour on board and knead lightly to form ball of soft dough.
Divide dough in half (1/2 for bottom and 1/2 for top).
Using 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan, pat, press and work 1/2 of the dough into pan evenly, as best you can. Spread 2 jars apricot filling over dough, then sprinkle walnuts over filling.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine together.
Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients, including chocolate mixture, to beaten eggs. Mix well.
Bake in a 13 x 9 pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: moist pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Stir in pumpkin and water.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Add to cream mixture, mixing well.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Spoon into well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until bread tests done.
Makes 32 servings.
Each serving contains 125 calories and 6 grams fat.

title: vegetable slaw
directions: In a large bowl, mix well oil, vinegar, garlic, marjoram, mustard, salt and pepper.
Add broccoli and peas; toss to mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Add cabbage, carrots and chopped pimiento; toss to mix well.
Garnish with rolled-up strips of pimiento and parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cream cheese log
directions: Mix together and form a log.
Serve with crackers.

title: easy brown sugar icing
directions: Bring to the boiling point (except vanilla) slowly, stirring while cooking.
Test by using the hard ball stage.
Remove from heat, cool slightly and add vanilla.
Beat with a wooden spoon until you can spread.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Saute onion in oil and add garlic.
Stir in flour to make a roux.
Stir constantly as it browns.
Add other ingredients and simmer for approximately 1 hour.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix the soup mix, ground beef, bread crumbs, celery, ketchup, milk and egg.
Press meat mixture into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pig pickin cake
directions: Mix cake mix, Mandarin oranges with juice, eggs and oil; pour into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: italian chicken
directions: In skillet, cook chicken in 1/2 cup of Italian dressing, about 10 minutes or until not pink.
Add bag of vegetables and remaining cup of dressing.
Dash with salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.
Serve over noodles.
Top with grated cheese.

title: mom's mayonnaise for potato salad
directions: Melt butter; add flour and milk.
Boil until thick.
Mix dry ingredients and add to beaten eggs.
Add vinegar.
Add this to white sauce mixture slowly while stirring.
Cook in top of double boiler long enough to cook eggs.

title: cheese stuffed mushrooms
directions: Rinse mushrooms and pat dry.
Remove stems (stems may be used in other recipes).
Place caps on a greased baking sheet.
Combine remaining ingredients, except 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into mushroom caps.
Sprinkle each with reserved cheese.
Bake mushrooms at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Line baking sheet with wax paper.
Mix in a bowl the peanut butter, sugar, butter and vanilla.
Mix with hands until hard. Roll into small balls (approximately 1/2 teaspoon).
Put balls on wax paper and refrigerate.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook sweet potatoes whole in jackets, just until tender.
Drain, peel and cut into 1/2-inch thick slices.

title: fat free fantasy fudge
directions: Mix cocoa, salt and sugar together.
Add milk and corn syrup. Boil this mixture until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Take off fire and beat well with hand mixer until it starts to thicken. Do not overbeat.
Stir in Grape-Nuts and vanilla.
Spray a 9-inch baking dish with nonfat cooking spray.
Pour fudge into dish and let it harden.
Cut into squares when set.
Yields 30 to 36 pieces.
Fat:
Calories:
77; 1 % calories from fat.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: Combine flour and brown sugar in medium bowl.
Cut in butter to make a crumb mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Set aside 3/4 cup mixture for topping.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of 8 x 8 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: chili chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; debone.
Cook noodles in broth and drain.
In skillet, place stick of butter and onion until tender.
Add soups, pimento and jalapeno peppers.
Take casserole dish and add chicken, noodles, soup mixture and shredded Cheddar.
Place in oven at 400° until bubbly.

title: honey ice cream
directions: Beat eggs; add honey, lemon extract, vanilla and salt.
Stir in cream; pour into 1 1/2 gallon freezer.
Fill container with milk, leaving expansion room and freeze as usual.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: Place jello and puddings in a saucepan with 2 cups water; bring to a boil.
Cool mixture.
Add Cool Whip and oranges.
Fold together.
Refrigerate in mold or dish.

title: potato soup(made with watkins cream for soup and sauces)
directions: Use enough water to cover potatoes, onion and celery.
Cover and boil until done (do not drain water).
Make sauces from the directions on Watkins can of cream.
Mix together and serve hot.

title: raisin pie
directions: Steam raisins in water until tender.
Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla, then add raisins. Pour into unbaked crust. Bake at 325° about 1 hour.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix butter or margarine with brown sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Blend in flour, soda and salt.
Form into a roll 2 1/2 inches across.
Chill.
Slice 1/8-inch thick.
Bake at 400° on ungreased baking sheet 8 to 10 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Place cucumbers in ice	water
to
cover in crock.
Let stand until well chilled	and
crisp;
drain.
Bring
3 quarts water, vinegar, pickling salt and	alum to a boil in saucepan. Place 1 grape leaf and 1
sprig
of
dill
weed
in
each
hot sterilized quart jar.	Pack
cucumbers into jars.
Add 1 clove garlic, 1 slice of onion and	1
red pepper to each jar.
Fill jars wit hot vinegar
solution,	leaving
1/2-inch headspace. Seal with 2 piece lids.
Process
in boiling water bath for 15 minutes or
in pressure
cooker
(ten
pound
pressure
for 5 minutes).
Makes 6 to 7 quarts.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Combine ingredients together, stirring well.
Pour into tube or bundt pan.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: easy stuffed peppers
directions: Remove tops and seeds from peppers; steam shells about 5 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients using only 1/2 can of soup; mix well.
Fill peppers with stuffing.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 30 minutes.
Pour remaining 1/2 can of soup over peppers.
Continue cooking 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bull dog gravy - arkansas native
directions: Cook until thickened and serve over baking powder biscuits (hot).
Serves 4. Kids love it and it's cheap and filling.

title: baked buttered shrimp
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook garlic in butter or margarine until it browns.
Remove and discard.
Add bread crumbs, onion, parsley, tarragon, basil, salt, pepper and sherry to butter or margarine. Reserve 1/4 cup of mixture; divide remainder among 8 individual baking dishes.
Arrange shrimp over mixture in each dish. Sprinkle shrimp with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until crumbs are golden.
Edge each dish with hot, seasoned green beans.
Makes 8 servings.

title: arroz con pollo(chicken and rice)
directions: Boil
chicken until cooked.
Remove chicken from bones. Fill a 2 quart pot 1/2 full with water; bring to a boil.	Add chicken and other ingredients. Put on medium heat.	Stir about 2 times before
rice dries, then set on low heat for about 20 minutes (covered).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put broccoli, Pet milk and salt and pepper in casserole pan.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Add grated cheese and onion rings.
Cook for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter and milk.
Boil for 3 minutes (soft ball). Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal. Spoon out onto wax paper.

title: almond lace cookies
directions: In food processor, grind almonds finely.
Add butter and sugar and blend.
Add flour, milk and vanilla and process until just combined.
Drop batter by teaspoons into small rounds 2 inches apart onto a buttered baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 4 to 5 minutes or until golden.
Makes about 12 small cookies.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Beat egg whites and fold in last.
Melt butter.
Add sugar. Beat egg yolks and add. Add pecans, raisins, flour and remaining ingredients.
Cook 3 hours at 250°.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Stir cornstarch into sugar.
Crush 2 cups of strawberries.
Mix sugar and berries in pan.
Cook until it boils, stirring constantly; boil until sauce thickens (about 10 to 12 minutes). Slice the rest of the berries into the pie (baked) shell.
Pour cooled sauce over the top of the fresh berries.
Chill and top with whipped topping (Cool Whip) before serving.

title: tomato juice cocktail
directions: Mix, shake vigorously and serve.

title: barbie cakes
directions: Frosting on them first made a cake and put a Barbie on there.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat 2 eggs.
Add sour cream.
Stir in flour, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in chopped, peeled cooking apples.
Pour into 9-inch deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in small bowl, combine margarine, brown sugar and flour.
After pie has baked for 15 minutes, remove from oven.
Sprinkle prepared mixture over top of pie.
Return pie to oven and bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until filling is set.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make paste with food coloring and cocoa.
Mix vanilla, salt, buttermilk, flour, vinegar and soda.
Add shortening mixture, along with paste.
Do not beat, just blend in.
Bake 30 minutes in 2 (8 or 9-inch) pans at 350°. Let cool and split each layer in half.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Combine with next 3 ingredients.
Blend soup, milk and 1/2 cup cheese.
Stir in macaroni mixture.
Top with rest of cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes at 400°. Use 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Let cabbage and salt stand for 1 hour (press juice out of cabbage).
Add carrot and green pepper.
Boil for 1 minute the vinegar, water, sugar and celery seed.
Pour mixture after it cools over cabbage and freeze.

title: fresh strawberry bread
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add eggs and oil; mix well.
Add strawberries and nuts and mix again.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: baked alaska(use different flavors of ice cream and cake.)
directions: Lay ice cream bricks side by side; measure length and width. Trim cake 1-inch larger on all sides than ice cream measurements. Place cake on a piece of foil.
Center ice cream on cake.
Cover; freeze until firm.
At serving time, beat together egg whites, vanilla and cream of tartar to soft peaks.
Gradually add sugar, beating to stiff peaks.
Transfer cake with ice cream to a baking sheet.
Spread with egg white mixture, sealing to edges of cake and baking sheet all around.
Swirl to make peaks.
Place oven rack in lowest position.
Bake in a 500° oven about 3 minutes or until golden.
Slice; serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix first four ingredients and shape into meatballs.
Make sauce from next four ingredients.
Simmer meatballs in sauce, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: portuguese pork tenderloin
directions: Season flour with salt, pepper and paprika. Roll tenderloins in flour. Saute in butter until golden brown. Add sliced onion and mushrooms; saute for a minute or two. Add wine and rosemary. Cover and cook over low heat for 45-60 minutes, until tenderloins are done. Add lemon juice and parsley just before serving. Makes 4-6 servings.

title: pickled beets and eggs
directions: Drain beets.
Add the beet juice to the ingredients.
Boil until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat and add the beets.
I add peeled, hard-boiled eggs after the beets have cooled, making sure eggs are all covered with the liquid.
Eggs are best if they are made at least a day before you want to serve them.

title: fruit drops
directions: Mix sugar and margarine.
Add eggs.
Stir in buttermilk.
Sift dry ingredients and add.
Add pecans, cut up cherries and dates. Chill for 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° until no imprint when touched.
Makes 8 dozen.
Keep dough chilled and bake as needed.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion and seasonings, stirring to separate meat. Combine all ingredients except cheese. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel nut turtles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place clusters of three nuts each on a buttered cookie sheet.
Place one caramel on top of each cluster of nuts.
Bake in oven for 5 to 7 minutes or until the caramel has softened but still retains its shape.
Remove from oven.
Melt chocolate chips in small saucepan over low heat.
Flatten the caramel squares with the back of a spoon, then pour a little chocolate over each cluster with a spoon.
Cool.

title: easy casserole
directions: In skillet, fry hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Turn into casserole and add soups and noodles; stir until just blended. Bake at 300° until bubbly hot.

title: lime pie
directions: Mix and pour into baked pie shell and chill for 3 hours.
Top with whipped cream.
Sprinkle top with chopped chocolate.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Mix flour and margarine together by hand; add 3/4 cup nuts. Pat in cake pan in bottom and on sides about halfway up.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over baked meat.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Place tomatoes and spices in a heavy saucepan over low heat and cook 20 minutes if using fresh tomatoes (only 10 minutes for canned tomatoes).
Bread crumbs may be added if a thicker stew is desired.

title: white fudge
directions: Boil water and sugar over medium heat to soft ball stage. Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Beat until shine starts to leave.
Quickly pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch cake pan.
Cool part way in fridge.
Cut into squares; refrigerate until completely cooled.

title: twenty four hour fruit salad
directions: Stir first 5 ingredients together, and cook over medium heat until thick, then cool.
Fold fruit into sauce, add whipped cream and mix thoroughly.
Put in refrigerator until next day and add bananas next day.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Crush crackers.
Melt 1 stick butter.
Mix butter and crackers.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: quick broccoli with cheese
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package and drain.
Place in flat baking dish.
Spread butter over top of broccoli and sprinkle with the cheese.
Place under broiler until cheese melts.
Serve.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve on crackers.

title: diabetic beef burgundy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut steak into 1-inch cubes.
In skillet, sprayed with Pam, brown meat slowly.
Transfer to 1 1/2-quart casserole with tight fitting cover.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Serve on toast, rice or noodles.
Remember to add bread exchange.
Yields 4 cups (8 servings).

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with grated cheese the last 5 minutes (optional).

title: egg rolls
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Rinse ground beef with warm water in strainer.
Return beef to stove top.
Add carrots, potatoes and spices.
Cook until carrots and potatoes are done, stirring constantly.
Spoon mixture on egg roll wrapper.
Roll it up and repeat until all wrappers have been used.
Fry in skillet with a little oil until all sides are golden brown.
Makes about 16 egg rolls.

title: garlic grits
directions: Cook grits in salted water for 5 minutes.
Add cheese and melt in grits.
Add butter and melt in grits.
Beat two eggs and the milk and add to grits.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute the onions in
a bit of the bacon grease.
Remove onions from skillet and brown the ground beef;
drain.
Return beef to skillet and
add
the
soup,
sour
cream,
bacon
and onions. Heat through.
Serve over egg noodles or rice.

title: turkey shepherd's pie(weight watchers)
directions: In 10-inch nonstick skillet, heat oil; add onion and garlic and cook over high heat, stirring frequently, until onion is translucent (about 1 minute).

Add turkey, reduce heat to medium-high and cook, stirring with a wooden spoon to break up large pieces, until turkey is no longer pink (about 6 minutes). Sprinkle flour over turkey mixture and stir quickly to combine; cook, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.
Add 1/4 cup water, the wine and broth mix and cook over high heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Stir in parsley; reduce heat to medium-low and let simmer for 3 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream first four ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet about 6 1/2 minutes.
Makes approximately 8 dozen cookies.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Cut each biscuit in 4 pieces.
Roll each piece in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Put half the biscuits into large greased or buttered Bundt pan.
Heat margarine and 1 cup sugar to boiling point.
Pour half this mixture into pieces in the pan.
Continue with the balance of the biscuits and pour remaining margarine and sugar mixture over all. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove from pan.
